Commentary: A little bit of swing to start with. Roach serves a back-of-a-length delivery, outside off. It shapes away a bit. Alex Lees leaves it alone for the keeper.
An outswinger, full and on off. Alex Lees stays inside the crease and defends it out solidly.
Three dots on the trot! Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away. Alex Lees shuffles across and tries to defends it out but ends up keeping the blade close to his body.
A length ball, outside off. Lees shoulders his arms at it.

FOUR! Alex Lees gets off the mark with a glorious stroke. He opens his account in International cricket and also this series. A full-length ball, outside off. Alex Lees plays it late and guides it past the point fielder for a boundary.
Good length, outside off, shaping away. Alex Lees has nothing to do with it.
Jayden Seales starts with a fuller delivery, angled down leg. Zak Crawley looks to flick it away but misses. Joshua Da Silva dives to his left behind the sticks to make a great stop.
A length ball, on the fifth stump line. Zak Crawley covers his stumps and leaves it alone for the keeper.
FOUR! It is a trademark Zak Crawley! A full-length ball, on the fourth stump line. Zak Crawley gets behind the line and drives it down the ground to bag a boundary.
A length ball, angling down leg. Zak Crawley tries to flick it away but misses. The ball brushes his pads and goes to the left of the keeper.
FOUR! Width on offer this time and Crawley does not shy away at all. It is full and wide outside off. Zak Crawley leans in and drives it through the cover region for a boundary. He moves to 8.
Back of a length, outside off. Zak Crawley leaves it alone for the keeper. England are off to a positive start.
Good-length ball, outside off. It holds its line after hitting the deck. Alex Lees shuffles across a bit and shoulders his arms at it.
On a length, outside off, it nips away a touch off the deck. Alex Lees has no interest in playing away from his body.

OUT! LBW! England do not lose a review but they do lose a wicket. Alex Lees' debut innings comes to an end early. Kemar Roach sets up Lees beautifully and gets the better of him. A length ball, around off, comes in with the angle. Alex Lees tries to defend it out on his front foot but gets pinged on the front pad. Kemar Roach appeals and the umpire raises his finger after giving it some thought. Alex Lees is not pleased as he thinks it is bat first and takes the review. The UltraEdge shows no bat is involved. The Ball Tracking shows it is umpire's call on impact as the ball goes to knock the stumps off. In the end, the on-field decision stands and Alex Lees trudges back to the pavilion.
Howout: lbw b Kemar Roach

Commentary: FOUR! Root also gets off the mark with a boundary! Short of a length, outside off. Joe Root hangs back and steers it behind point. The ball races away to the fence.
No ball! A full-length ball, shaping in from outside off. Joe Root stays back and blocks it out watchfully. The umpire though signals a wide, as the bowler oversteps.
Full length, on off. Root blocks it out awkwardly on the front foot.
Back of a length, on the fourth stump line, shapes in late. Joe Root trusts the bounce and shoulders his arms at it.
Jayden Seales bowls from wide of the crease and serves a full-length ball, in the corridor of uncertainty. Zak Crawley covers the stumps and leaves it alone for the keeper.
Good length, on the fifth stump line. Zak Crawley has nothing to with it.
Full length, pitching outside off and moving away sharply. Zak Crawley just watches it sail past him.
Good length, outside off. Zak Crawley does not have any stroke to offer.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! WHAT A STUNNING CATCH BY JOSHUA DA SILVA. England's opening woes continue. They have lost both their openers inside 4 overs. Jayden Seales gets himself into the wicket's column now. A full-length ball, outside off. Zak Crawley stays inside the crease and tries to drive it towards mid on but without any movement. The ball takes the inside edge and stays very low. It scoots past the off-pole and goes to the left of Joshua Da Silva, behind the sticks. He makes a full-stretched dive to his left by hanging his left hand out and luckily for him the ball stays in his glove. Brilliant bowling and even better keeping from Joshua Da Silva. This is a sensational start from West Indies!
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Jayden Seales

Commentary: Well wide of off, Dan Lawrence lets it be. A successful over for Jayden Seales. A wicket-maiden!
Top delivery! A good-length ball, in the corridor of uncertainty. It flies off the deck. Joe Root tries to defend it out but does not get anywhere near the ball.
Full and shaping into the pads, Root hangs back and blocks it out.
Full length, outside off. Joe Root leaves it alone for the keeper.
A full-length ball, on off. Joe Root drives it to the left of the bowler with soft hands. Kemar Roach does really well to bend down and stop the ball.
Good-length ball, outside off, some extra bounce off the deck. Joe Root looks to defend it out but gets beaten on the outside edge. This got a smile on Root's face.
Full length, on the stumps. Joe Root hangs back and defends it to cover. A maiden for Kemar Roach.
Good-length ball but well outside off, swinging away further. Dan Lawrence leaves it alone.
Making the batter play this time! On a length, around off, nipping away. Dan Lawrence pushes it to cover.
An outswinger, outside off. Dan Lawrence lets it go.
On a length, outside off, swinging away. Dan Lawrence covers the stumps and shoulders arms to that one.
Length ball, in the sixth stump channel, Dan Lawrence offers no shot to that one.
Good-length ball, on off, no swing movement this time. Dan Lawrence taps it to point from his crease. Another maiden for Jayden Seales!
A quick single! Length ball, straight and on middle, Root covers the line and tucks it to short mid-wicket for a quick single.
Length ball, outside off. Dan Lawrence watches the ball closely and lets it for the keeper to collect.
On a good length, nipping in, on off. Dan Lawrence blocks it out on the front foot.
Pushed wider this time, outside off. Dan Lawrence continues with his leaving spree to anything that is outside off.
Back of a length, on off. Dan Lawrence pushes it through the cover region for a single.
FOUR! That is nicely played! Full and straight, on middle. Joe Root flicks it through mid-wicket. The timing was exquisite and he gets a boundary for that.
Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away. Dan Lawrence with yet another leave.
On a good length, on off, shaping away a tad. Dan Lawrence gets on top of the bounce and defends it out.
Length ball, outside off, shaping away. Dan Lawrence shoulders his arms.
Another outswinger which is bowled well outside off, Dan Lawrence is not interested in playing those.
Outside off, on a length. Dan Lawrence lets it sail through.

Jayden Seales finally gets one to come back in. An inswinger, outside off, on a good length. Dan Lawrence is taken aback by that and he tries to defend with a full face of the bat. He misses and the ball whizzes past the outside edge.

FOUR! That goes through the third slip! Short of a length, outside off, extra bounce on that one. Joe Root cuts it towards the slip cordon. The ball goes through the hands of the third slip fielder and races away to the fence.

OUT! TIMBER! Kemar Roach wins the battle against Joe Root. England in a spot of bother now as their skipper departs for just 13. This is some start from West Indies. Kemar Roach steams in and bowls a good-length ball, at 133 kph, and angles this one in. Joe Root makes an error of judgement as he decides to leave this one and he shoulders arms. This allows the ball to clip the top of the off stump and Kemar Roach is off to a celebration and so are his team-mates as they gather around him.
Howout: b Kemar Roach

Commentary: Good-length ball, on off. Ben Stokes blocks it out.
Back of a length, outside off, shaping away. Ben Stokes leaves it alone for the keeper.
On a length, wide outside off, moving away. Ben Stokes walks across the stumps but does not offer any shot.
On a good length, outside off, shaping away. Ben Stokes makes a watchful leave.
Lovely outswinger, outside off. Dan Lawrence lets it be.
On a good length, outside off. Dan Lawrence shoulders arms.
Seales shapes away this length ball, outside off. Dan Lawrence with another leave.
Seales with an inswinger this time, on middle. Lawrence plays it through mid-wicket and gets three runs.
Another beautiful inswinger, on off. Stokes shows his full face of the bat and drives it back to the bowler.
A good bouncer! Short ball, on middle. Ben Stokes does well to get away from the line and let it go.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Kemar Roach bowls a loose delivery, full and angling down leg. Dan Lawrence stays back and clips it away for a boundary quite comfortably through the square leg region.
Length ball, on the fifth stump line. Dan Lawrence leaves it alone for the keeper.
Good length, outside off, yet again. Lawrence shoulders his arms at it.
Three dots on the trot! Short and outside off. Dan Lawrence leaves it alone.
A short ball, shaping in late. Dan Lawrence trusts the bounce and shoulders his arms at it. Although the umpire signals a no ball, as the bowler oversteps.

FOUR! Did it carry though? Streaky boundary for Dan Lawrence. A full-length ball, around off, nips away a touch. Dan Lawrence leans in to defend it out but only finds the outside edge. It goes towards Jermaine Blackwood at third slip but does not carry. Blackwood gets low to his left but is unable to stop the ball as well. It races away to the third man.
Length ball, on off. Dan Lawrence defends it out watchfully.
A full-length ball, at 126 kph, Ben Stokes defends it into the deck.
A short ball, nipping away, outside off. Ben Stokes shoulders his arms at it.
Fuller, on off. Stokes pushes it out.
Full length, on off stump. Ben Stokes defends it back to the bowler off the bottom half of the blade.
Could not find the gap! A full-length ball, outside off, shaping across the left-hander/ Ben Stokes' eye lit up with the width on offer but he only punches it towards short extra cover.
WOAH! A full-length ball, outside off, shaping across Ben Stokes, who tries to go for the booming drive only to get beaten on the outside edge.

FOUR! Nicely played! A length ball, outside off. It nips away a shade with some extra bounce off the deck. Dan Lawrence shuffles across and guides it through backward point with soft hands for a boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Dan Lawrence ducks under it with ease.
A short ball, outside off. Dan Lawrence leaves it alone.
Full length, on middle and leg. Dan Lawrence flicks it off his pads towards deep mid-wicket. They take three before the fielder cuts it out.
Good length, on off, shaping across the left-hander. Ben Stokes stays inside the crease and leaves it alone for the keeper.
Fuller, on the pads, Stokes clips it to the left of short mid-wicket. Kraigg Brathwaite was quick to retain the ball and the batters could only take a single.
CLOSE! Overpitched, outside off, moving away. Ben Stokes leans in and tries to defend it out. He misses and the ball zips past the outside edge.
Fuller, on leg. Stokes defends it to the leg side.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Ben Stokes works it towards mid on.
Full length, on off. Stokes defends it back to the bowler with soft hands.
Length ball, on the pads. Stokes stays inside the crease and tucks it to mid-wicket.

Second consecutive maiden for Jason Holder. A length ball, outside off, shaping away from the left-hander. Ben Stokes walks out of his crease and tries to push it inside the line but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length ball, outside off. It flies off the deck. Joshua Da Silva gathers the ball a bit too high.
Length ball, on the pads. Dan Lawrence flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.

A length ball, angling down leg. Stokes tries to flick but misses. It brushes his pads and goes to the right of the keeper. Joshua Da Silva makes a half-stop and the ball goes through him. Dan Lawrence wanted a single but Ben Stokes was not sure about the position of the ball and hence denied the run.
Outside off, left alone.
Length ball, outside off, nips away a touch. Stokes leaves it alone for the keeper.
On a length, on off, Stokes solidly blocks it out.
On a good length, on middle. Dan Lawrence defends it solidly.
Length ball, shaping away from off. Dan Lawrence shoulders arms.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.

OUT! TAKEN! Jason Holder gets his reward for persisting with good line and lengths. He didn't give anything away in his first two overs and finally, gets a scalp. Bowls a good-length ball, on middle and off and shapes it away. Dan Lawrence had no choice but to play. He does so but the ball takes the outside edge and flies to second slip. A big relief for Jermaine Blackwood as well as he missed out on a couple of opportunities off Kemar Roach early on but held onto this one moving to his right. Another bites the dust for England! West Indies right on top!
Howout: c Jermaine Blackwood b Jason Holder

Commentary: Length ball, straightens up after pitching around off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it out off the front foot.
On a good length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow shoulders arms. Another successful over for Jason Holder. A wicket-maiden this time!
Length ball, outside off, coming in. The ball shoots up after pitching. Ben Stokes lets it go.
Full and on leg, Ben Stokes misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. A muted appeal for an lbw but not given.
Nice and full, on off. Stokes defends it out.
Back of a length, outside off. Stokes hops and works it to the off side for a run.
Length ball, outside off. Bairstow lets it sail through.
Drop and run! Short of a length, on off. Jonny Bairstow stands tall and drops it to the off side and scampers through. 50 comes up for England!
Length ball, outside off, shaping away. Jonny Bairstow leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Well bowled! On a good length, around off, nipping away. Jonny Bairstow watches the seam closely and decides to leave.
Outside off, Bairstow defends it out.
Fuller in length, on off. Bairstow pushes it to mid on.
On a length, outside off. Bairstow with yet another leave.
Nice little outswinger by Holder, on off. Bairstow counters it nicely as well. Fourth consecutive maidens for Holder!
Length, angling away, outside off. Stokes lets it go.
Full and slanting away, outside off. Stokes offers no shot.
A length ball, around off. Stokes pushes it to cover for one.
Length ball, on off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it back to the bowler.
Good-length ball, outside off, with some extra bounce. Jonny Bairstow does not go chasing.
Length ball, outside off, shaping in late. Jonny Bairstow trusts the bounces and shoulders his arms at it.
A full-length ball, on off. Ben Stokes gets an inside edge on the pads.
A length ball, at 124 kph, on off. It flies off the deck. Ben Stokes is surprised as he blocks it out awkwardly.
Fuller. wide outside off. Stokes leaves it alone.
Length, outside off, moving away. Ben Stokes has no stroke to offer.
Overpitched, outside off. Ben Stokes leaves it alone for the keeper.
Good length, outside off. Ben Stokes defends it to the off side. Fifth maiden on the trot for Jason Holder.
Length ball, outside off, shaping away. Jonny Bairstow leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Jonny Bairstow shoulders amrs to this length ball which is bowled outside off.
An action replay of the previous delivery! Bairstow lets it sail through.
Good-length ball, on off. Bairstow keeps it out this time to the off side.
Outside off, on a length. Bairstow blocks it to the off side.
Length ball, on off. Bairstow covers the line and pushes it to the on side.
Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away. Stokes is not interested to offer a shot.
A full toss, outside off. Stokes is surprised by that and he fails to put it away. Hits it off the inner half of the bat back to the bowler.
Length ball, outside off. Stokes lets it be.
Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away. Stokes with another watchful leave.
First runs after 19 deliveries! On the pads, Stokes flicks it through mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Touch fuller, outside off. Stokes crunches his drive straight to extra cover.
Length ball, outside off. Bairstow leaves it alone.
Lovely shot! Shorter and wider, outside off. Bairstow punches it through cover-point for a brace.
On a good length, on off. Bairstow blocks it out.
Full and slanting in, on middle. Bairstow flicks it through mid on. Roach gives it a chase and keeps it down to a single.
Comes round the wicket to Stokes and bowls a length ball, outside off. Stokes lets it through.
Full and nipping away, outside off. Stokes shoulders arms.
Outside off, on a length. Bairstow lets it be.
Touch fuller, outside off, shaping away. Jonny Bairstow decides not to offer any shot.
On a good length, on off, shaping away a tad. Jonny Bairstow with a good watchful leave.
Length ball, on off. Jonny Bairstow is solid in his defence.
Length ball, attacking the stumps. Jonny Bairstow works it to mid-wicket.
A single to end the over! On a good length, on middle. Jonny Bairstow hops and clips it to square leg for a single. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 1!
Length ball, pushed well outside off. Jonny Bairstow is not chasing that one.
Good-length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow shoulders arms to that.
FOUR! Absoultely smashed! Short of a length, on off. Jonny Bairstow slaps it away in front of the square. The ball races away to the vacant deep mid-wicket fence in a jiffy.
Better from Seales! Length ball, outside off, shaping away. Bairstow lets it sail through.
Pushed much wider, outside off. Bairstow with an another leave.
On a length, outside off. Left alone by Bairstow.
A length ball, on middle and leg. It flies off the deck. Ben Stokes tries to flick it away but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
A length ball, on middle and leg. Stokes blocks it out watchfully.
FOUR! Ben Stokes freeing his arms now. A length ball, outside off. Some extra bounce off the deck. Ben Stokes gets on top of the bounce and punches it through covers for a boundary.
Full length, on off. Stokes pushes it to cover for a single.
Back of a length, on the body. Jonny Bairstow tries to heave it across the line but misses.
Length ball, on the fourth stump line. Jonny Bairstow shoulders his arms at it.
Full length, on the pads. Ben Stokes clips it through mid-wicket. The batters take three before the fielder cuts it out.
Good length, outside off, shaping away. Jonny Bairstow leaves it alone for the keeper.
Slightly short, outside off, moving away. Jonny Bairstow lets it go to the keeper.
Another one outside off, Jonny Bairstow leaves it alone yet again.
Length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow pushes it through backward point for a brace.

FOUR! Jonny Bairstow would be the happiest man to see it race away to the boundary line. It is a short delivery, on off. Jonny Bairstow tries to pull it away but is a tad early into his shot. The ball flies off the top-edge and evades the effort of two fielders from the slip chasing it towards third man. It lands safely and gets into the fence.
A length ball, outside off. Ben Stokes leaves it alone.
Fuller, wide outside off, Stokes has no stroke to offer.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Ben Stokes pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Short ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow steps across and shoulders his arms at it.
BEATEN! A full-length ball, outside off. It nips away a shade. Jonny Bairstow tries to reach out but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length ball, on off. Bairstow blocks it back to the bowler.
Back of a length, outside off. Ben Stokes has no stroke to offer.
Two dots in a row! A short ball, on off. Ben Stokes hops and blocks it back to the bowler.
A length ball, on middle and leg. Ben Stokes gets to square leg off the inner half. The batters take a quick single.
Good length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow taps it to the right of gully.
Back of a length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow rides the bounce but cuts it straight to point.
Full length, outside off. Bairstow pushes it to the man at short extra cover.
Good length, outside off, nipping away. Ben Stokes leaves it alone.
Short and on off. Stokes pulls it past mid on for a brace.
Full, wide outside off. Left alone.
Back of a length, on off. Stokes pulls it through mid-wicket for two more.
Short and outside off. Blocked out.
Length, outside off. Blocked out.
Seales bangs a bouncer on middle, Jonny Bairstow ducks under it.
An inswinger, on middle. Jonny Bairstow is nearly cut in half. The ball hits the inner half of his blace and drops on the deck.
Length ball sliding down leg, Jonny Bairstow tucks it off his thigh pads to fine leg for a leg bye.
Outside off, on a length. Ben Stokes lets it sail through.
A yorker, on off. Stokes digs it out.
Short ball, on middle. Stokes sees it early and sways away from the line.
A bouncer, outside off. Jonny Bairstow tries to pull it without looking at it. He misses it by quite some distance.
Length ball, angling on leg, Jonny Bairstow looks to clip but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball rolls to the leg side and the batters take a single.
Short of a length, on off. Stokes drops it on the off side for a quick single.
Length ball, outside off. Bairstow pushes it through covers for a single.
Cruched! Length ball, outside off. Stokes hangs back and punches it through covers. Two taken!
Full and on off, kept out by Stokes.
On a length, on middle. Jonny Bairstow tucks it on the leg side.
Length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow taps it to the off side.
First runs off Jason Holder's over! Shorter length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow cuts it through point for a brace.
On a length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow taps it to point.
On a good length, on middle. Jonny Bairstow stays solid in his defence.
Fuller, on off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it out easily.

FOUR! A chance goes abegging! Short of a length, outside off. Ben Stokes looks to cut. The ball goes off the bottom edge through the third slip and gully fielder for a boundary. Alzarri Joseph has a wry smile on his face.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Outside off, on a length. Ben Stokes shoulders arms.
Touch fuller, outside off, angling away. Ben Stokes lets it be.
On a length, outside off. Left alone by Stokes.
Bangs a short ball, outside off. Ben Stokes offers no shot and leaves it for the keeper to collect.
On a length, around off. Jonny Bairstow guides it to point.
Length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it out.
An inswinger, outside off. Jonny Bairstow lunges forward and shoulders arms to that.
On a length, on off. Jonny Bairstow keeps it out.
FOUR! Cut away! A loose ball from Jason Holder. Back of a length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow gets on top of the ball and cuts it through point for a boundary.
A yorker, on off. Jonny Bairstow jams it out.
Good length, outside off, shaping across the left-hander. Stokes leaves it alone for the keeper.
Two dots to start with! On a length, outside off. Stokes it happy to leave it alone.

Nice fielding! A full-length ball, outside off. Ben Stokes drives it to the right of mid off. Kemar Roach runs behind it and cuts it out quickly and only allows the batters to take a single. The stand moves to 50 as well with this single.
Full length, on off. Jonny Bairstow defends it to point.
FOUR! Jonny Bairstow is in the groove. Full length, wide outside off. Jonny Bairstow leans in and drives it through the cover region for a boundary.
A length ball, outside off, Jonny Bairstow leaves it alone. Runs are coming in at a very good rate for England in the afternoon session.
Good length, outside off, shapes away with some extra bounce. Ben Stokes shuffles across and leaves it alone for the keeper.
Full length, outside off. Ben Stokes shoulders his arms.
Outside off, Stokes has no stroke to offer.
Four dots in row! Length ball, on the fifth stump line. Ben Stokes lets it go to the keeper. It is still a game of patience.
Make it five! Outside off, Stokes shoulders his arms at it.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Holder drifts it in. Ben Stokes clips it to mid-wicket and scampers through for a quick single.
On a length, outside off. Stokes lets it sail through.
A length ball, on off. Ben Stokes gets behind the line and blocks it back to the bowler with full face.
Fuller, on off. Ben Stokes defends it to the off side.
On a length, shaping away from the left-hander, from around off. Ben Stokes does not go hunting away from his body.
Full length, outside off, moving away a bit late. Ben Stokes is caught in two minds, as he tries to push it away but it the end drops his blade really well.
Outside off. Ben Stokes leaves it alone for the keeper. A maiden over for Jayden Seales.
A dot to start with! A length ball, outside off. Bairstow blocks it out solidly off the front foot.
Fuller, on off. Jonny Bairstow drives it down the ground. Kemar Roach bends down and makes a half-stop with his left hand.
Three dots on the trot! All three time Jonny Bairstow has played the delivery. This one is on a length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow taps it to point.
Make it four! Fuller, on off. Jonny Bairstow drives it to mid off with soft hands.
Full length, on off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it back to the bowler. Can Roach get his third maiden of the innings?

FOUR! Jonny Bairstow makes sure to ruin a good over for Kemar Roach. It is full and on the pads. Jonny Bairstow stays inside the crease and flicks it through mid-wicket. A fielder gives it a chase but the ball wins the race.
Length ball, on leg. Ben Stokes tucks it to mid-wicket.

EDGED BUT SHORT! Ben Stokes riding on his luck here. A length ball, around off, shaping away a bit. Ben Stokes hangs his blade out. It takes the outside edge and goes towards John Campbell at first slip. Campbell gets low to his right but collects it on a bounce. Jayden Seales was almost into his celebration until his keeper calmed him down.
FOUR! Top shot! Back of a length, on off. Ben Stokes stands tall and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries. Ben Stokes races away to 36. A full-length ball, sliding down leg. Ben Stokes stays back and glances it down to fine leg for four.
A length ball, outside off. Ben Stokes leaves it alone for the keeper.

OUT! TIMBER! Jayden Seales has the last laugh here. A ripper to break a crucial partnership. England lose their fifth wicket and this will hurt them a lot as Ben Stokes was looking in his groove. Coming to the delivery, it is a full-length ball, on off. Jayden Seales gets the ball to swing in late and that beats Ben Stokes completely. Ben Stokes tries to go for the booming drive but the ball takes the inside edge only to peg back the leg stump.
Howout: b Jayden Seales

Commentary: Length ball, outside off. Bairstow drives it but straight to point.
On a length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it out.
Length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow shoulders arms.
On a good length, on off. Jonny Bairstow is solid in his defence.
Another length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow watchfully blocks it out.
Width offered, outside off. Jonny Bairstow plays it to point. The fielder there dives to his left and half-stops it. The batters take a single.
On middle, coming back in, Jonny Bairstow gets cramped for room. He works it to mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller in length, on off. Ben Foakes drives it well to mid on. Kemar Roach there does well to move to his left quickly and stop the ball. Keeps it down to a single.
Length ball, on off. Driven to mid on.
On a length, around off. Jonny Bairstow looks to work it on the leg side but gets an inside edge onto the pads. He starts running as he has no idea where the ball went but Foakes sends him back.
Length ball, on off. Pushed towards covers.
Full and outside off. Jonny Bairstow lets it sail through.

FOUR! Edged and safe again! Length ball, coming in, on off. Ben Foakes tries to defend. The ball kisses the outside edge and goes through the slip cordon. Jason Holder at second slip tries to catch the ball but it evades him and races away into the third man fence. It wouldn't have matter anyway even if it would have been taken as Kemar Roach has overstepped.
Length ball, outside off. Blocked out.
FOUR! This time off the middle of the bat! Overpitched delivery, on off. Ben Foakes plants the frontfoot ahead and drives the ball past mid off for a beautiful boundary.
Short of a length, outside off. Ben Foakes has a poke at it. The ball zips past the outside edge.
Length ball, on middle. Played to mid off.
FOUR! A half-volley, on middle. Ben Foakes plays a lovely drive through mid on for another boundary. He is off to a flyer.
Full length, outside off. Ben Foakes defends it to cover.
Full length, on leg. Jonny Bairstow flicks it to the leg side.
FOUR LEG BYES! Full length, angling down leg. Jonny Bairstow tries to flick it away but misses. The ball brushes his pads and races away to the fine leg fence.
A length ball, on off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it out.
On a good length, on middle, coming into the batter. Jonny Bairstow is taken aback by that and gets pinged on the thigh pad.
Another inswinger, on middle. And once again, Jonny Bairstow gets thudded high on the pads trying to defend.
Full and outside off. Jonny Bairstow pushes it towards covers.
Short of a length, outside off. Ben Foakes punches it through covers for couple of runs.
Length ball, outside off, Foakes leaves it alone.
Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away a tad. Ben Foakes hangs his bat out to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On middle, Foakes defends it out.
On a good length, outside off. Foakes blocks it out.
On a length, outside off, nipping in. Ben Foakes offers no shot.
Holder serves a full-length ball, on off. Jonny Bairstow digs it out solidly.
Back of a length, nips away off the deck, outside off. Jonny Bairstow leaves it alone for the keeper.
Full length, on leg. Jonny Bairstow pushes it towards mid on.
Good length, on the pads. Jonny Bairstow tucks it to square leg for one run.
Full length, on the pads. Ben Foakes gets it to mid-wicket off the inner half.
Full length, angling down leg. Ben Foakes stays back and clips it off his pads. It goes towards deep square leg and batters take two with ease. Ben Foakes is motoring along really well here.
Floated, fuller, on leg. Jonny Bairstow clips it to the leg side for an easy single.
Flighted, fuller and on leg. Ben Foakes defends it past short leg.
Full and outside off. Ben Foakes pushes it to cover.
Tossed up, outside off. Ben Foakes yet again could not beat the fielder at covers with his drive.
Flatter and outside off. Foakes plays it late and chops it towards point.
Around off, blocked out solidly. Just a single off the over, a good start by Veerasammy Permaul.
Full length, on off. Jonny Bairstow drives it to cover.
Fuller, on off. Jonny Bairstow eases it to mid off.
A length ball, on the stumps. Jonny Bairstow defends it to the leg side off the inner half.
Touch fuller, on off. Bairstow presses forward and defends it back to the bowler.
Full length, on off. Jonny Bairstow drives it to cover but is unable to get it in the gap.
Seventh maiden for Jason Holder. This is an incredible stat. A full-length ball, on off. Jonny Bairstow defends it back to the bowler.
Short and on off. Foakes punches it to point.
Slower through the air, full and on off. Ben Foakes defends it out off his front foot.
Fuller, on off. Foakes blocks it out.
Tossed up, full and on middle. Ben Foakes strides forward and blocks it into the deck.
Fuller, outside off. Foakes remains solid in his defense.
Floated, full and on off. Ben Foakes defends it to the left of silly point.
Slower one, way down leg. Jonny Bairstow leaves it alone.
Slower and flatter, on the pads. Jonny Bairstow tucks it to fine leg.
Flighted, full, on middle and leg. Jonny Bairstow defends it to short leg.
Flatter and on middle. Jonny Bairstow works it back to the bowler.
Looped up, full and on off. Jonny Bairstow presses forward and blocks it into the deck.

Fuller, on the pads. Jonny Bairstow flicks it to the leg side. Third maiden on the trot for West Indies. We should have one more over before the Tea break. The helmets are coming on the field, that means there will be fielders up close.
Angled in full and on off. Ben Foakes defends it back to the bowler.
Floated, fuller, on off. Foakes hangs back and blocks it out.
Tossed up, on off. Ben Foakes blocks it to cover.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Fuller and angling down leg. Ben Foakes stays back and flicks it through square leg for a boundary.
Looped up, outside off, turning away. Ben Foakes leaves it alone.
Fuller, on off. Ben Foakes blocks it back to the bowler. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 1.
Length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it to point.
Alzarri Joseph goes wide of the crease and serves a length ball, on the pads. Jonny Bairstow defends it to the leg side.
Full length, on middle and leg. Jonny Bairstow pushes it down the ground with soft hand. The man from mid on runs to left to collect the ball.
A length ball, on off. Jonny Bairstow pushes it out.
Length ball, on the pads. Jonny Bairstow tries to flick it away but misses and get hit on the pads.
Full length, on off, blocked back to the bowler. A maiden to start the final session.
Fuller and outside off. Ben Foakes prods and blocks it out.
On off, blocked out solidly.
Around off, Foakes pushes it out with ease.
Full and on the stumps. Foakes blocks it to point.
Full, on off. Ben Foakes defends it out watchfully.
Two maidens on the trot to start the evening session. Fuller, around off. Ben Foakes defends it out on the front foot.
FOUR! Into the gap. Back of a length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow stands tall, opens the face of the bat late and steers it down to third man for a boundary.
A short ball, on off. Jonny Bairstow pulls it hard towards mid-wicket. The fielder makes a sharp stop to save a certain boundary.
FOUR! Jonny Bairstow moves into his 40s with this boundary. Good length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow stands tall and punches it through covers for a boundary.
Length and on off, blocked out.
Full length, angled into the pads. Jonny Bairstow clips it to deep square leg for a couple.
Length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow pushes it to cover. Straight to the fielder.
Fuller, on off. Foakes defends it back to the bowler.
Full and outside off. Ben Foakes drives it to cover.
On off, blocked out.
Fuller, on the pads. Ben Foakes clips it to mid-wicket.
Wide outside off, Ben Foakes reaches out and pushes it to cover.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Ben Foakes defends it back to the bowler.
On a length, angling into off. Bairstow punches it to covers.

NOT OUT! A length delivery angling into middle and leg this time. Bairstow looks to work it towards the leg side but misses. The ball hits his pads and there is an appeal. However, the umpire is not interested. Windies skipper, takes his time and decide to take the review. The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows no bat involved. The Ball Tracker rolls and it shows that the ball is missing stumps. So Bairstow will continue and West Indies lose their review.
Short of a length, outside off. Chopped to point.
Back of a length, outside off. Bairstow punches it to covers this time.
On a length and angling into middle. Bairstow works it towards mid-wicket and takes a single this time.
This one is on a good length and outside off. Foakes decides to leave it alone.
FOUR! Fifty for Jonny Bairstow! A good innings but his team needs him to carry on. A shorter delivery and tad outside off this time. Jonny Bairstow goes back and cuts it through point for a boundary.
Drifting on the pads this time. Jonny Bairstow looks to work it towards the leg side but misses. The ball hits his pads and a leg bye is taken towards short fine leg.
Fuller outside off. Foakes drives it to covers this time.
Tossed up nicely around off. Ben Foakes gets forward and blocks it off.
Slower in the air, on off. Solidly defended off the front foot again by Ben Foakes.
Tossed up on off. Ben Foakes gets well forward and blocks it.
FOUR! Jonny Bairstow is moving along nicely now! Fifty partnership also comes up. This one is tad short and outside off. Jonny Bairstow cuts it through backward point for a bnoundary.
A fullish delivery on off. Jonny Bairstow drives it to mid off.
Ohh.. this time an inside-edge! Back of a length, around off. Bairstow looks to cut but gets the inside edge onto the turf just away from the stumps.
A fullish delivery, around off this time. Jonny Bairstow drives it to covers.
A full delivery, on off. Bairstow drives it back to the bowler.
Good running this time! On a length, on middle. Bairstow works it to deep square leg and gets a couple.
Tossed up nicely on middle. Foakes works it to mid-wicket.
Slower in the air, on middle. Foakes pushes it back to the bowler.
Loopy delivery, around off. Foakes pushes it to covers this time. Nicely bowled again.
FOUR! Good use of the feet this time! On middle and leg. Foakes skips down the track and works it towards cow corner for a boundary.
Slower and fuller on off. Foakes pushes it to covers now.
Uses his feet again as this is delivered on middle and leg. Foakes works it towards mid on this time.
A length delivery on off at 132 kph. Bairstow defends it towards the leg side.

Angling into middle and leg again. On a length and Bairstow tries to work it towards the leg side but is tad early. He gets the leading edge and the ball goes towards the bowler. Luckily for him he got a bat on this one.
A fullish delivery angling into middle again. Bairstow drives it to mid on.
Goes fuller on off this time. Bairstow drives this off the front foot  towards mid off now.
On a length, on middle and leg. Bairstow works it towards the square leg region and gets a couple.
Back of a length, outside off. Bairstow cuts it to point.
Slightly shorter outside off. Foakes punches it to covers.
Tossed up on middle. Foakes gets well forward and blocks it out.
Slower in the air, outside off. Foakes drives it through covers and gets a couple before the fielder cuts it off.
This one is wider outside off. Foakes pushes it to point this time.
Slower and straighter this time. Foakes blocks it out.
Quicker and flatter on middle. Foakes works it towards mid-wicket.
Seales bangs this one short, around off. Bairstow lets it go.
Another short delivery on off. Bairstow pulls it towards the deep square leg region. John Campbell there runs to his right and dives to save three runs for his team. Just a single taken.
On a length, on middle. Foakes defends it towards the leg side.
A length delivery, on off. Foakes blocks this one solidly towards the off side.
Back of a length, this time on off. Foakes punches it to mid off.
Goes fuller this time on middle at 133 kph. Foakes drives it to mid on. Good partnership this for England.

NOT OUT! Jonny Bairstow survives! This one is flatter outside off. Jonny Bairstow first looks to work it towards the leg side but then decides to cut it. He misses. However, Windies appeal for the caught behind and the umpire raises his finger. Bairstow though reviews it straightaway. The UltraEdge confirms that there is no bat involved so, Bairstow will continue as the decision will be overturned. Disappointment for Windies but Bairstow was sure that he did not get a bat on that one.
Tossed up on middle. Bairstow works it towards the leg side.
On off and flatter. Bairstow blocks it out.
On off, blocked into the deck.
Looped up, on middle and leg. Jonny Bairstow defends it to short leg.
Full and on leg. Jonny Bairstow clips it to square leg.
On a length, around off at 130 kph. Foakes gets forward and defends it towards backward point.
A length delivery, outside off at 133 kph. Foakes punches it to covers this time.
Bangs this one short but wrong line. It is down the leg side and Foakes lets it go.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Foakes leaves it alone watchfully.
FOUR! Lovely shot but this is easy for Foakes! A full delivery on middle and leg. Foakes leans forward and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR! Another superb shot! This one is slightly short on off. Foakes just pulls this one through mid-wicket for another boundary.
A flatter and quicker delivery, on off. Bairstow goes back and blocks it out.
Tossed up this time, on middle. Bairstow gets well forward and defends it.
Fuller on middle. Bairstow sweeps it to deep square leg for a single.
Slightly shorter and around off, turning away. Foakes punches it to cover-point.
Another one that is slower and around off. Foakes punches it to point.
Slower this time, on off. Foakes drives it to covers.
Full length, on leg. Jonny Bairstow flicks it to the leg side.
Length ball, on middle. Jonny Bairstow defends it out watchfully.
Full length, on the pads. Jonny Bairstow defends it to the leg side.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Jonny Bairstow drives it to the left of mid on. The umpire signals a no ball as the bowler oversteps.
Length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow stays back, opens the face of the bat and guides it to the right of first slip. Jason Holder gets low to his right to make a good stop.
Length ball, on the pads. Jonny Bairstow clips it to the leg side.
SHORT! A length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow plays it late and guides it to the man at first slip. It goes off the outer half but does not carry.
Fuller and on off. Ben Foakes drives it through covers for a brace.
FOUR! Nicely played! Tossed up, full, on middle and leg. Ben Foakes comes down the track and clips it through mid-wicket to bag a boundary. He moves to 41.
On off, blocked to the off side.
Short and on off. Ben Foakes cuts it to the right of backward point. Kemar Roach sprints to that side, dives and makes a solid one-handed stop.
Looped up, wide outside off, turning away. Ben Foakes leaves it alone.
Fuller, on middle and off. Ben Foakes presses forward and blocks it back to the bowler with ease.
Full length, on the pads. Jonny Bairstow flicks it to square leg but straight to the fielder.
Overpitched, outside off. Jonny Bairstow drives it on the up but straight to mid off. Another dot.
FOUR! Too straight, too easy for Jonny Bairstow. Full and on the pads. Jonny Bairstow stands back and flicks it aerially over mid-wicket for a boundary.

FOUR! EDGY! What a peach of a delivery. Jonny Bairstow has some lady luck with him now. A length ball, around off, nips in a touch late. Jonny Bairstow prods and tries to defend it out but only manages to get a thick inside edge. The ball scoots past the leg stump and also past the keeper for a boundary at fine leg. The umpire signals a no ball, as the bowler oversteps.
FOUR! Jonny Bairstow is in the groove. Short and on off. Jonny Bairstow pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
On off, blocked out.
Length and on off, defended out watchfully.
On off, defended off the front foot.
Fuller, on off. Foakes pushes it to point.
Angled in, full and on off. Ben Foakes sees out the danger.
Floated, full and outside off. Ben Foakes guides it to short third man for a single.
FOUR! Jonny Bairstow is only dealing in boundaries. Tossed up, full and on off. Jonny Bairstow gets down and sweeps it through mid-wicket along the ground for a boundary.
FOUR! The stand moves to 99. Floated, full and on off. Jonny Bairstow gets low and sweeps it hard through mid-wicket for another boundary. He moves to 80 now.
A length ball, at 124 kph, on off. Ben Foakes defends it out watchfully.

OUT! LBW! This one stays low and it looks plumb to naked eye. Although, Ben Foakes has a chat with his partner and opts to take the review. It is a length ball, on off, nips in off the deck and stays quite low. Ben Foakes is caught inside his crease and fails to flick it away to get pinged on his pads. Jason Holder appeals and the umpire raises his dreaded finger. The review is being taken and the Ball Tracking shows three reds. Ben Foakes valiant innings comes to an end. West Indies right back in the game.
Howout: lbw b Jason Holder

Commentary: Full length, on off. Chris Woakes blocks it back to the bowler.
A length ball, on off. Chris Woakes defends it out watchfully.
Length, on middle and leg. Chris Woakes defends it to the leg side off the inner half.
On a length, on off. Chris Woakes blocks it back to the bowler. A second wicket-maiden for Jason Holder in this innings.
A length ball, on the stumps. Jonny Bairstow defends it out solidly.
FOUR! Really well controlled shot. Back of a length, on off, close to the body. Jonny Bairstow stays inside the crease and whips it through mid-wicket with a short-arm jab. Boundary.
FOUR! Jonny Bairstow's last seven scoring shots have all been boundary. He is on a roll. A length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow plays it late and guides it through backward point for a boundary.
Length, on off. Jonny Bairstow pushes it to cover for a quick single.
Full length, on the stumps. Chris Woakes works it to mid on.
Back of a length, outside off. Chris Woakes leaves it alone for the keeper.
Good-length ball, coming in, on off. Jonny Bairstow tries to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. Holder appeals for an lbw but the umpire says no.
Fuller, outside off. Jonny Bairstow drives it towards covers.
Full again, on off. Jonny Bairstow works it to mid on for a sharp single.
Touch fuller, on off. Driven back to the bowler.
Good-length ball, on off. Woakes pushes it back to the bowler.
On off, tucked to mid-wicket.
On a length, on off. Jonny Bairstow chops it back to the keeper.
Short of a length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow steers it to deep point for a brace.

Length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow guides it to deep point and once again gets two runs. The Barmy Army is cheering loudly for Jonny Bairstow's efforts. This is incredible running. He has been on the crease for so long, but still looks hungrier for more runs. He is now just six runs short of his ton.
Length, on middle. Jonny Bairstow clips it to square leg for one.
Fuller, on off. Woakes pushes it to cover.
On a length, on middle. Woakes works it to mid on.
Fuller in length, on off. Jonny Bairstow drives it to mid off.
Full and on off, Jonny Bairstow flicks it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it out.
Full and on off, kept out.

Full-length delivery that angles into the batter just around off, Bairstow presses forward and tucks his bat in line of his front pad as he allows the ball to hit the blade and roll into the off-side.
On a length, jagging back in, on off. Jonny Bairstow presses forward to defend but is struck on the pad. Height seems to be the issue. It struck him above the knee roll.

Full length, on off. Chris Woakes punches it back to the bowler. Alzarri Joseph gets low to his right and gets his palm to it. The ball goes through to disturb the stumps on the other end. Jonny Bairstow looks to have made his ground. The umpire takes it upstairs to confirm. The replays show Jonny Bairstow was safely inside the crease.
A length ball, around off. Chris Woakes gets an outside edge. It goes to the right of the man at first slip, who collects it on a bounce.

FOUR! Through the slip cordon!  A length ball, outside off, shaping away a hint. Chris Woakes looks to drive it away. It takes the outside edge and goes past the man at first slip to the boundary at third man.
Back of a length, on the fourth stump line. Chris Woakes shoulders his arms to it.
Full length, outside off. Chris Woakes steps across and pushes it to cover.
Full length, outside off. Chris Woakes gets it to mid off off the toe-end of the blade. Just a boundary of the over.
Fuller, outside off. Jonny Bairstow expands his arms and drives it to cover. Not in the gap though.
Length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow taps it to cover.
Fuller, on off. Jonny Bairstow pushes it to cover with soft hands.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Jonny Bairstow clips it to the right of mid on for a single. He moves to 96.
Back of a length, on off. Chris Woakes defends it back to the bowler with ease.
A length ball, on off. Chris Woakes flicks it to the leg side for a single. Just 2 runs off the over.
Full length, on the pads. Chris Woakes clips it to short mid-wicket.
A length ball, coming in from outside off. Chris Woakes hangs back and taps it to point.
Fuller, on off, angled in. Chris Woakes stays back and defends it out watchfully.
Full length, outside off. Chris Woakes hangs his blade out and defends it to cover.
Length, on the stumps. Chris Woakes gets behind the line and blocks it out.
Full length, on off. Woakes bunts it back to the bowler. Second maiden of the innings for Alzarri Joseph.
Flighted, full and on leg. Jonny Bairstow clips it to square leg for a single.
Fuller, on off, blocked out solidly.
On the pads, clipped to square leg for a single.

FOUR! HUNDRED FOR JONNY BAIRSTOW. He has a bright smile on his face after a few punches to the air. Jonny Bairstow soaks himself in the applause from the pavilion and the fans. Full and down leg. Jonny Bairstow gets low and sweeps it to deep square leg for a boundary. The situation demanded it and Jonny Bairstow stepped up to the challenge yet again.
On off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it out.
Fuller, on leg. Jonny Bairstow clips it to the leg side.
Fuller, on leg. Chris Woakes defends it to short leg. After Jonny Bairstow's ton. The Barmy Army are singing in joy.
On off, defended out.
Floated, full and on off. Chris Woakes defends it out.
On the pads, Chris Woakes clips it to deep square leg for a brace.
Fuller, outside off. Chris Woakes leans in and drives it through covers for two more.
Full, on middle and leg. Chris Woakes defends it back to the bowler.
A yorker, on middle. Jonny Bairstow digs it out.
Full and on middle, blocked out.
Loopy ball, full and on middle. Kept out.
Full and down leg, Jonny Bairstow looks to sweep but gets a top edge. It evades the keeper though.
Short and outside off, cut to deep point for a run.
Loopy ball, on leg. Chris Woakes nudges it on the leg side.
Big swing straightaway! Length ball that jags back in a long way on middle. Jonny Bairstow does well to block it out.
On a length, around off. Jonny Bairstow defends it out towards covers.
A huge inswinger, on off. Jonny Bairstow pushes it to mid on for a quick single.
Full and on middle, nipping in. Chris Woakes whips it through mid on. John Campbell gives it a chase and cuts it off at the edge of the boundary. Three taken! 250 up for England as well!
Length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow cuts it to deep point for one.
On a good length, outside off. Chris Woakes defends it out.
Length ball, well outside off. Jonny Bairstow offers no shot to that.
Back of a length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow chops it behind point.
Nice and straight, on middle. Jonny Bairstow is solid in his defence.
Length, on middle. Jonny Bairstow blocks it out.
A peach of a delivery! Length ball, outside off, jagging back in. Jonny Bairstow looks to drive but misses. He gets beaten on the inside edge.
Short of a length, on middle. Pulled to deep square leg for a brace.
Full and angling down leg, Chris Woakes misses his flick. He gets hit on the pads and the batters take a leg bye. An appeal for an lbw by Roach but turned down.
On a good length, shaping away, on off. Jonny Bairstow looks to defend but the ball goes off the outside edge to point.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
On middle, kept out by Bairstow.
On a good length, on off. Pushed towards covers.
This is flicked behind square on the leg side for a single and Jonny Bairstow will keep the strike.
Length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow plays it to the slip cordon.
Width offered, outside off. Jonny Bairstow guides it to sweeper cover and crosses ends.
Back of a length, on middle. Woakes hops and defends it right under his eyes.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Full and outside off. Chris Woakes chases it and drives it through covers for a glorious boundary.
On middle, tucked on the leg side for a single.
Length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow defends it out.
Touch fuller, on off. Chris Woakes keeps it out.
Back of a length, outside off. Chris Woakes blocks it out from the crease.
On a good length, outside off, shaping away. Chris Woakes looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On a length, outside off. Chris Woakes dabs it to gully.
Length ball, on middle. Chris Woakes flicks it uppishly past the diving short mid-wicket fielder for a brace.
Outside off, Woakes with a watchful leave.
On a length, on middle. Jonny Bairstow clips it to square leg for a single. 50 partnership between these two!
Good-length ball, outside off. Woakes shoulders arms.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! An overpitched delivery, outside off. Chris Woakes gets down on one knee and caresses it through covers. Exquisite timing on that one and he bags a boundary for that.
Back of a length, outside off. Chris Woakes keeps it out.
On a length, on middle. Woakes is solid in his defence.
Good-length delivery, on middle. Chris Woakes gets behind the line and defends it back to the bowler off the back foot. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 1!
Good start from Roach! An inswinger, outside off. Jonny Bairstow watches it closely and lets it sail through.
First runs on Day 2! Slightly fuller, on middle. Jonny Bairstow flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Another brace! Back of a length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow punches it off the back foot through covers. He gets another couple of runs.
Touch fuller, on middle. Flicked straight to short mid-wicket.
Well bowled! Full and on off, jagging back in. Jonny Bairstow blocks it out solidly.
Length ball, nipping in, on off. Jonny Bairstow is very solid in his defence. Positive start from England on Day 2!
Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away. Chris Woakes shoulders arms to that.
On a good length, outside off, shaping away. Woakes lets it be.
Back of a length, outside off. Woakes hops and plays it towards covers.
Outside edge is found but it goes through! Length ball, on off, nipping away. Chris Woakes strides forward and looks to push. The ball goes off the outside edge through the gully region for a couple.
On a length, on off. Blocked out.
A dot to end! Length ball, outside off. Woakes leaves it alone.
FOUR! Beautifully played! Short of a length, on middle. Jonny Bairstow swivels and times it perfectly. He pulls it to deep square leg and picks up a boundary.
On a good length, on middle. Jonny Bairstow keeps his eyes on the ball and blocks it out from the crease.
On a good length, outside off, coming back in. Jonny Bairstow keeps it out.
Good-length ball, on off. Another solid block by Bairstow.
A jaffa! On a good length, outside off, jagging in. Jonny Bairstow looks to defend but misses. The ball whizzes past the outside edge.
On a length, on middle and leg. JB works it to deep square leg for a single and keeps the strike.
On a good length, around off, shaping away. Jonny Bairstow lets that one through.
On middle, tucked to mid-wicket for a run.
Length ball, on off. Chris Woakes pushes it to cover.
Good-length ball, on off. Woakes guides it towards gully for a single.
Well left! Good-length ball, closer to the off pole, shaping away. Jonny Bairstow trusts the bounce and lets it go.
Jason Holder's consistency is unmatchable! Another ripper, on off, Jonny Bairstow is beaten by the swing. He looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Back of a length, around off. Chris Woakes stays back and dabs it onto the deck.
A wayward ball, full and outside off. Chris Woakes lets it through to the keeper.
Play and a miss! Loose from Woakes! A full ball, well outside off. Chris Woakes throws his bat at it but the ball goes past his blade.
Roach drags his length back and serves a length ball, around off. Woakes defends it off the back foot.
Good-length delivery, around the fifth stump channel. Chris Woakes covers his off pole and leaves it alone.
Drop and run! Short of a length, around off. Chris Woakes taps it to the off side and scampers through to the other end.
Holder hurls a full ball, outside off. Woakes blocks it off the front foot.
Good-length ball, angling in from outside off. Chris Woakes does not bother playing at that one.
Back of a length, well outside off. Woakes prods and shoulders his arms at it.
Holder pitches it up, outside off. Chris Woakes gets forward and mistimes his drive towards mid off.
A length ball, jagging back in from off. Woakes gets behind the line of the ball and dabs it onto the deck.
Holder goes full and around middle. Woakes lunges forward and flicks it to mid-wicket. Not in the gap though. Another maiden over from Holder.
Seales starts with a full ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow lets it sail through to the keeper.
Well bowled! Good-length ball, around the corridor of uncertainty. Jonny Bairstow looks to defend but he gets an inside edge onto his pad.
Nicely played, not from the middle of the bat though! A full ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow prods and drives it past the cover fielder. The batters take three runs.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Jayden Seales comes into the attack and strikes straightaway! Excellent delivery from Seales to get rid of Woakes. Seales changes his length and serves it short, around off. Woakes hangs back and looks to block it but there is some extra bounce on offer. The ball brushes Woakes' gloves and goes straight to Joshua Da Silva behind the sticks who makes no mistake. England lose their seventh wicket.
Howout: c Joshua Da Silva b Jayden Seales

Commentary: On a length, around off. Craig Overton hangs back to defend it.

OUT! CAUGHT! Brilliant field placement from Kraigg Brathwaite and Jayden Seales strikes twice in his first over on Day 2! This is an excellent catch from Nkrumah Bonner at short leg. Seales serves a short ball, around middle. Craig Overton stays back and looks to nudge it on the leg side. It goes off the splice of his bat, straight to Bonner at short leg. The ball hits him near the rib-cage but Bonner does well to hold onto that one.
Howout: c Nkrumah Bonner b Jayden Seales

Commentary: Leg bye! A full ball, around leg. Jonny Bairstow misses his flick and gets hit low on his pad. The ball rolls to the leg side for a leg bye.
Length ball, angling in, on middle. Mark Wood just about keeps it out.
Good-length ball, around off. Mark Wood keeps it out.

Bye! That missed the stumps by a whisker! Good-length ball, nipping back in from outside off. Mark Wood stays inside the line of the ball to defend but the ball sneaks through his bat and pad. Joshua Da Silva fails to grab it cleanly and concedes a bye.
A length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow defends it to the off side.
Holder goes full and outside off. Jonny Bairstow looks to drive but he miscues it straight to the cover fielder.
Back of a length, outside off. Mark Wood lets it through to the keeper.
Seales goes short again, around middle. Mark Wood looks to pull but he misses. This is good hostile fast bowling from the youngster!
A length ball, angling in from outside off. Mark Wood prods but does not feel for it and lets it sail through,
Back of a length, well outside off. Mark Wood shoulders his arms at it.
Another ball, shorter in length, outside off. Mark Wood leaves it alone for the keeper to collect.
A length ball, around off. Mark Wood gets forward and keeps it out.
FOUR! Holder serves a slower ball, full and outside off. Jonny Bairstow reaches out and carves it past the fielder at cover. The ball races away to the fence.
A length ball, jagging back in sharply from off. Jonny Bairstow gets forward and blocks it onto the deck.

DROPPED! Holder didn't see this coming, probably! Good-length ball, around off. Jonny Bairstow prods and just chips it back to the bowler. Holder bends low to his right but fails to grab it. Bairstow gets a life.
On a length, around off. Jonny Bairstow defends it off the front foot.
A bit fuller, outside off. Jonny Bairstow gets to the pitch of the ball and blocks it towards cover.

Good effort from Kemar Roach at mid on but Bairstow was upto the task and he manages to retain the strike. A full ball, on middle. Jonny Bairstow pushes it to mid on and sets off for a quick run. Roach at mid on runs in and scores a direct hit at the bowler's end but Bairstow was home.
FOUR! EDGY! Back of a length, just outside off. Jonny Bairstow looks to heave it away but it goes off the outside edge and over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Full and outside off. Jonny Bairstow leans and drives it past the cover fielder for a brace.
This is a length ball, around the fourth stump channel. Jonny Bairstow prods and defends it to the off side.

FOUR! Cheeky from Bairstow! 300 comes up for England! Another ball, on a length, just outside off. Jonny Bairstow stays back, opens the bat face and just guides it past the second slip for a boundary.
Back of a length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow taps it behind square on the off side and takes a single. Lovely batting!
A well-directed bumper, around middle. Wood stays back and pulls it along the ground towards deep mid-wicket. A single to end the over.
Good-length ball, outside off. Mark Wood lets it through to the keeper.
A full ball, outside off. Wood prods but keeps his bat inside the line of the ball and lets it sail through.
Swing and a miss! Roach goes full and outside off. Mark Wood throws the kitchen sink at it but fails to get any bat on it.
BEAUTY! Good-length ball, coming on with the angle and straightens just that little bit after pitching. Wood looks to defend off the front foot but the ball zips past his outside edge.
Fuller in length, on middle. Mark Wood pushes it to mid on.
Back of a length, around off. Mark Wood stays back and blocks it out watchfully.
A length ball, around leg. Jonny Bairstow just helps it on its way towards fine leg and rotates the strike.
Back of a length, well outside off. Mark Wood leaves it alone for the keeper to collect it.
Joseph serves a length ball, around middle. Wood covers the line of the ball and defends it onto the deck.

OUT! CAUGHT! The ploy of bowling short has done the trick for West Indies and Alzarri Joseph! This is a well-directed bumper, around off. Wood looks to pull but the ball hurries onto him and it goes off the top edge, in the air towards the point fielder. Veerasammy Permaul there, settles under it and pouches it with ease. England lose their ninth wicket and Alzarri Joseph gets his first of the innings.
Howout: c Veerasammy Permaul b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary: Back of a length, well outside off. Jonny Bairstow lets it through to the keeper.
Leg bye! Short of a length, angling in from off. Jonny Bairstow looks to heave it away but he misses and gets hit on his thigh pad. The ball rolls to the off side and the batters sneak in a leg bye.
A bumper, around off. Jonny Bairstow ducks underneath.
Another short ball, around off. Jonny Bairstow pulls it along the ground towards mid-wicket.
Back of a length, angling down leg. Jonny Bairstow sways away from the line of the ball and lets it go through to the keeper.
A short ball, around off. Jonny Bairstow swivels and pulls it along the ground towards fine leg. He takes a single this time.

FOUR! Edged but it sneaks through the keeper and first slip! Roach is absolutely gutted with that! A full ball, outside off. Jack Leach prods and looks to push it away from his body. It takes the outside edge and goes past the keeper and first slip for a boundary. Joshua Da Silva should have surely gone for it.
A length ball, outside off. Jack Leach leaves it alone this time.
Short of a length, outside off. Jonny Bairstow guides it to third man but does not take a single.
Length ball, outside off. Jonny Bairstow pushes it to point.

OUT! TAKEN! Alzarri Joseph ends the proceedings. Bowls a length ball, on off. Jonny Bairstow goes for the heave. The ball goes off the top edge and goes high up in the air towards gully. Jason Holder settles himself underneath and takes the skier. England are bundled out for 311.
Howout: c Jason Holder b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary: Woakes starts with a back-of-a-length ball, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite stands on his toes and defends it under his eyes.
Back of a length again, with a hint of away swing this time. Kraigg Brathwaite pushes it to the off side.
Shorter in length, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it from the crease without any trouble.
Woakes goes fuller this time, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite does well to block it out. A loud appreciation to Woakes from the slip cordon.

FOUR! Good shot! Chris Woakes is going full trying to find swing. Overpitches it again, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite prods and drives it to long off for a beautiful boundary. West Indies get underway!
Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away. Kraigg Brathwaite makes a leave.
Back of a length, on middle. John Campbell hops and blocks it out.
Full and on off, John Campbell watchfully defends it out.
Length ball, outside off, shaping away. John Campbell lets it sail through.
Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away. John Campbell leaves it alone.
On a length, on off. Campbell defends it back to the bowler.
John Campbell is off the mark! Good-length ball, on off. Pushed to point for a quick single.
That's a ripper! Good-length ball, closer to the off pole, angling across. John Campbell is forced to offer a shot. He tries to defend but the ball zips past the outside edge.
FOUR! First boundary of the Windies' innings! Short of a length, on middle. John Campbell gets on top of the bounce and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
NO BALL! Good-length ball, outside off, swinging in. John Campbell with another defensive shot but the ball goes past the outside edge. Chris Woakes will have to reload as he has overstepped.
FOUR! Woakes goes full this time, on middle. John Campbell flicks it uppishly to deep mid-wicket for another boundary.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Touch fuller, on middle, nipping in. John Campbell keeps it out off the front foot.
Length ball, on off. John Campbell pushes it to cover for a quick single. This is a good start by West Indies. Not allowing the pressure to come onto them.
On a length, on off. John Campbell just about keeps it out.
Good-length ball, outside off, nipping away. John Campbell leaves it untouched.
On a length, around off. John Campbell looks to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge towards gully. Doesn't get carried as it was played with soft hands.
John Campbell works this length ball behind square on the leg side for a single.
On a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it to the off side.
Short of a length, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite hops and taps it to the off side.
FOUR! Easy pickings! A loosener from Woakes, on the pads. Kraigg Brathwaite just tickles it down to fine leg and the ball races away to the fence.
Short of a length, on middle. Blocked out.
Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away. Kraigg Brathwaite shoulders arms to that.

Three taken! Short of a length, on off. An awkward defensive stroke from Kraigg Brathwaite. He just works it softly towards mid off but the ball still manages to go near the fence. The mid off fielder cuts it off. Three runs are taken!
Full and angling across, left alone by Campbell.
Back of a length, outside off. John Campbell punches it off the back foot through covers for a brace.
Length ball, outside off, at 139 clicks. Kraigg Brathwaite guides it to point.
On a length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite taps it to point once again.
Fuller in length, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite leans onto it and drives it through covers for a run.
Length ball, on off. John Campbell is solid in his defence.
Full and angling down on leg, John Campbell misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. A stifled appeal for an lbw but that was clearly going down leg.
Once again it's full and going down leg. John Campbell misses his flick and the ball gets carried through to the keeper.
Nice and full, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite digs it out.
FOUR! Sweetly timed! Fuller in length, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite presents the full face of the bat and drives it past the bowler to long off for a glorious boundary.
On off, blocked out.
On a length, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite keeps it out to the off side.

FOUR! Well clipped! Full and on the pads, Kraigg Brathwaite clips it through mid-wicket. The ball races away into the vacant deep mid-wicket area and into the fence. Both the openers are playing nicely and with positive intent.
Full ball, on middle and leg. Kraigg Brathwaite nudges it to mid-wicket. This is West Indies' highest score after 7 overs in Test cricket since 2014.
On a good length, on off. John Campbell blocks it out.
Short of a length, on off. Pulled nicely but straight to mid-wicket.
Bangs a bouncer, on middle. John Campbell ducks underneath. Good pace from Wood and a well-directed bouncer as well.
Full and spraying on the pads, flicked through mid-wicket for a run.
Short and on middle and leg. Kraigg Brathwaite hops and tucks it to leg gully.
Length ball, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it towards covers.
Loopy ball, outside off. John Campbell steps out and nudges it on the leg side.
Floats it up, on middle, turning in. John Campbell gets struck on the thigh pad. The bal lobs towards short leg and they appeal for a catch but the umpire says no.
Tossed up, on middle, turning in. John Campbell defends it back to the bowler.
Full and outside off. John Campbell keeps it out.
Full and outside off, John Campbell smothers it to the off side.
Quicker delivery, on off. John Campbell defends it off the back foot. First maiden over of this innings.
Bangs a short ball, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite sits under it.
Length ball, angling in, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite is beaten by the bounce and gets struck near the box as he tries to work it on the leg side.
On a length,outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite steers it to deep backward point for a brace.
FOUR! Short of a length, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite hops and rides the bounce. He deliberately cuts it over the gully fielder and bags a boundary.
Good-length ball bowled on the pads, Brathwaite tucks it round the corner to deep square leg where Leach has to cover some ground while stopping a boundary. Two taken!
Back of a length, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite pushes it to mid on. Both the openers have weathered the storm nicely in this morning session. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 2!
Tossed up, outside off. John Campbell prods and defends it to the off side.
FOUR! Innovative and also courageous from John Campbell! Full and outside off. Campbell kneels and reverse-sweeps it through point for a boundary.
Flatter ball, outside off. John Campbell rocks back and tries to keep it out but it goes off the underedge towards the first slip fielder.
Flatter ball, on a length, around middle. John Campbell stays back and eases it to long on for one run.
Flatter and quicker, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite nudges it to mid-wicket.
Floated, on a length, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite taps it to the off side and takes a single. 50 up for West Indies!
FOUR! PUNCHED! Back of a length, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite stays back and slaps it through the backward point region to bag a boundary. Poor start from Woakes!
Good-length ball, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite stays back and turns it to mid-wicket.
Short of a length, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite hangs back and turns it to the leg side. Not in the gap though!
Fuller in length, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite prods and tucks it to mid-wicket.
Good-length delivery, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite looks to block but it takes the outside edge and the ball rolls away through the slip cordon for a couple of runs.
On a length, around middle. Kraigg Brathwaite stays back and tucks it to the leg side.
Flatter ball, around off. John Campbell rocks back and keeps it out.
Floated, full and outside off. John Campbell skips down the track and pushes it to the off side for a single.
Tossed up, around middle. Kraigg Brathwaite keeps it out off the front foot.
FOUR! Easy pickings! A length ball, drifting onto the pads. Kraigg Brathwaite prods and just glances it through the fine leg region for a boundary.
Flatter and quicker, around middle. Kraigg Brathwaite keeps it out.
A bit quicker and going on with the arm from off. Kraigg Brathwaite stays back and blocks it to the leg side.
BEATEN! Fuller in length, outside off. John Campbell looks to drive but the ball beats his outside edge.
Back of a length, angling across the batter. John Campbell lets it through to the keeper.
On a length and way outside off. Campbell does not bother playing at that one.
Woakes serves a length ball, around the corridor of uncertainty. John Campbell leaves it alone.
Fuller in length, outside off. John Campbell lets it sail through to the keeper.
Short of a length, on middle. John Campbell hangs back and blocks it out. A maiden over from Woakes.
Full and on leg. Clipped to mid-wicket.
Tossed up, on off. Blocked out.
A quicker ball, on middle. Brathwaite keeps it out.
Full ball, outside off. Brathwaite defends it off the front foot.
Flatter and quicker, on off. Brathwaite blocks if off the back foot.
A tad short, outside off. Brathwaite cuts it towards point. Not in the gap though.
FOUR! CRUNCHED! Back of a length, outside off. John Campbell stays back and punches it through covers for a boundary.
Full and on middle. John Campbell keeps it out.
Fuller in length, outside off. John Campbell miscues his drive to mid off.
Good-length ball, outside off. John Campbell lets it through to the keeper.
A length ball, just outside off. John Campbell looks to drive but he gets an inside edge onto his pad.
On a length, well outside off. John Campbell plays it inside the line and lets it sail through to the keeper.
Flatter and quicker, on middle. Brathwaite stays back and defends it.
Full and on middle. Brathwaite nudges it towards mid-wicket.
Tossed up, on off. Brathwaite prods and blocks it out.
Flatter and quicker, on a length, outside off. Brathwaite taps it towards point and takes a single.
A full ball, on off. Campbell pushes it back past the bowler and rotates the strike.
Flatter ball, on a length, around off. Brathwaite keeps it out.
A length ball, around off. Campbell sits back in his crease and dabs it onto the deck.
Back of a length, around off. Campbell hangs back to defend it.
Back of a length, around off. Campbell keeps it out.
Full and on off, Campbell drives it back to the bowler.
Length ball, on off. Campbell keeps it out.
Short ball, on leg. Pulled to deep mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Tossed up, outside off. Campbell prods and carves it through the extra cover region for a boundary.
Floated, around off. Campbell blocks it.
This is darted on the pads. Campbell nudges it around the corner and takes a single.
Tosses it up, around off. Brathwaite keeps it out.
SIX! BANG! Excellent shot from the skipper! This is pitched up, around off. Brathwaite skips down and whacks it back over the bowler's head to bag a maximum.
Flatter and quicker, around middle. Brathwaite tucks it to the leg side.
FOUR! Pulled away! West Indies' openers on the march! A short ball from 'round the wicket, around off. Campbell pulls it uppishly over the square leg fielder for a boundary.
Fuller in length, around off. Campbell defends it off the front foot.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Overton strikes and this is a much-needed breakthrough for England! Overton serves another short ball. This time it is angling down leg. Campbell swivels and tries to pull but he only manages a tickle on it and the ball goes through to the keeper. Ben Foakes moves to his right and makes no mistake. West Indies lose their first wicket. Shamarh Brooks is the new batsman in.
Howout: c Ben Foakes b Craig Overton

Commentary: Wide! A short ball, well above the batter's head. Brooks ducks underneath and the umpire calls it wide for height.
Back of a length, around off. Brooks defends it off the back foot.
Good-length delivery, around off. Brooks covers the line and blocks it onto the deck.
Short of a length, around off. Brooks sits back in his crease and defends it cautiously.
Full and on off, pushed to mid on.
Loopy ball, on the pads. Nudged to square leg for a brace.
Tossed up, on off. Blocked out.
On the pads, flicked to mid-wicket.
Keeps it full and on middle, Brathwaite presses forward and blocks.
Shorter, outside off. Tapped to point.
Fuller in length, on off. Brooks leans and drives it towards extra cover.
Full again, on off. Brook uses his feet and flicks it but straight to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Excellent shot! Short and wide, outside off. A freebie really and Brooks gets on top of the bounce and carves it to deep point for a boundary. He gets off the mark as well.
FOUR! Brilliant shot from Brooks again! Stand and deliver stuff! Fuller in length, outside off. Brooks stands tall and drives it past the diving mid off fielder for another boundary.
On off, kept out by Brooks.
On a length, on off. Brooks stays solid in his defence. Two boundaries then from this over.

FIFTY! Length ball, on leg. Brathwaite hops and clips it to deep square leg for a single. His 24th Test fifty. This has been a fine knock from the Windies skipper and he will look to add more runs and convert it into a bigger score.
Good-length ball, on off. Brooks knocks it back to the bowler.
Stokes goes full, on off. Brooks plays it straight to short cover.
Overpitches it again, on off. Brooks drives it back to the bowler.
Touch fuller this time, outside off. Driven towards covers.
Good-length ball, on off. Brooks defends it out.
Short of a length, on middle. Brathwaite clips it on the leg side.
Back of a length, on off. Brathwaite guides it to point.
On a length, on middle. Worked to deep mid-wicket for a run
On a good length, outside off. Brooks shoulders arms.
Another length ball, outside off. Brooks offers no shot to that.
A bumper this time from Wood, outside off. Brooks lets it sail through.
Back of a length, on middle. Clipped behind square on the leg side for one.

Just short! Length ball, outside off, Brooks goes chasing for it. The ball kisses the outside edge but he plays it with soft hands and as a result, the ball falls just short of the second slip fielder.
Short ball, outside off. Brooks lets it sail through.

NOT OUT! Good-length ball, angling in on middle and leg. Brooks looks to tuck but misses. He gets thudded on the pads. England appeal for an lbw but the umpire shakes his head. Root has a chat with Stokes and goes for the review. UltraEdge shows no bat involved. Ball Tracker shows that it is wickets missing. England lose their review and the original decision stands.
Length ball, down the leg side. Brooks misses his flick.
On off, driven to short cover.
On a length, on middle and leg. Brathwaite hops and tucks it away to deep mid-wicket. He crosses ends.
Full and on off, Brooks covers the line and defends it back to the bowler.
Short of a length, on middle. Brooks hops and clips it to mid-wicket for a single.
Short of a length again, on middle. Brathwaite plays it through mid-wicket for a brace. 100 up for West Indies.
On a length, outside off. Blocked out.

OUT! CAUGHT! Brilliant catch by Overton! Another breakthrough for England! Wood dishes out a full ball, outside off, at 147 kph. Brathwaite goes chasing for it. The ball catches the outside edge and flies towards gully. Overton there takes a sharp catch. Wood is off to a celebration. They know the importance of this wicket. Brathwaite played a fine knock but has to depart now. England striking back at the right time! Both the openers are back in the hut now. Nkrumah Bonner is the new batsman in.
Howout: c Craig Overton b Mark Wood

Commentary: FOUR! Short of a length, outside off. Shamarh Brooks stays back and runs it past the gully fielder for a boundary.
Back of a length, around off. Shamarh Brooks keeps it out.
