Short ball, outside off. Brooks sways away from the line.
Good-length ball, outside off. Brooks shoulders arms.
On a good length, outside off. Brooks again makes a leave.
Length ball, tailing back in, outside off. Brooks lets it be.
Short ball, outside off. Bonner leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Short of a length, on middle. Pulled to deep square leg for a single.
Bangs a bouncer again, on middle. Shamarh Brooks sits under it.
Short of a length, outside off. Brooks punches it towards covers for a single.
Once again a bouncer that is left by the batsman.

NOT OUT! Length ball, outside off. Bonner taps it to point. He calls for a single but is sent back by his partner. The fielder scores a direct hit at the striker's end but Bonner was well in. It is taken upstairs though. Replay shows that Bonner made it home well in time. The third umpire however, shows out on the big screen by mistake and then changes it to not out. A little bit of false hopes given to English fans.

FOUR! Vicious delivery from Stokes, short on the off stump, kicks off the turf and hurries Brooks on the backfoot, who drops his bat down but it takes the outside edge and falls short of the second slip as well, runs away down to third-man for a boundary!
Short ball, outside off. Brooks lets it be.
Back of a length, on off. Brooks keeps it out.
A bouncer, on middle. Brooks sits under it.
Short of a length, on middle. Brooks stands tall and blocks it out.

OUT! TAKEN! Since the opening stand of 83 runs has been broken, things have gone in England's favor. Stokes with a beauty this time. Bowls a good-length ball, shaping away from the batter, outside off. Shamarh Brooks has a feel for it. He tries to drive playing away from the body. The ball kisses the outside edge and carries through to Joe Root at first slip. He is all smiles. West Indies lose their third wicket now!
Howout: c Joe Root b Ben Stokes

Commentary: A wayward delivery down the leg side, swinging further away. Nkrumah Bonner leaves it untouched. Ben Foakes dives a long way to his left but fails to collect it cleany. The batters take a bye.
On a length, on middle. Jermaine Blackwood nudges it to mid-wicket.
Bangs a short ball, on middle. Jermaine Blackwood sits under it comfortably.
Good-length ball, outside off, jagging back in. Jermaine Blackwood makes a good watchful leave.
Another short ball, on middle. Jermaine Blackwood ducks under it.

Put down! Fuller, outside off. Jermaine Blackwood gets low and looks to drive. The ball goes off the inside edge and goes towards the left of the keeper. A simiar way of how Zak Crawley got out. Ben Foakes dives to his left but fails to grab the catch. Good attempt from him though!
Good-length ball, around off. Nkrumah Bonner blocks it off the front foot.
A short ball, around middle. Nkrumah Bonner pulls it along the ground towards deep square leg and takes a single.
Back of a length, around off. Jermaine Blackwood stays back and defends it onto the deck.
A full ball, just outside off. Jermaine Blackwood prods and looks to leave it alone but he is a bit late. The ball hits the bottom half of the bat and rolls towards the slip cordon.
Fuller in length, nipping back in from middle. Jermaine Blackwood gets forward and tucks it to mid-wicket.
A full ball, outside off. Jermaine Blackwood leaves it alone.
Wide! A short ball, down leg and above the batter's head. Nkrumah Bonner leaves it and the umpire calls it wide for the height.
Pitches it up, around middle. Nkrumah Bonner prods and nudges it to the leg side.
On a length, around off. Nkrumah Bonner dabs it onto the deck.
Leg bye! A full toss, angling down leg. Nkrumah Bonner misses his flick and the ball brushes off his pad before going to the keeper who half-stops it and the batters get a leg bye.
Fuller in length, around middle. Jermaine Blackwood flicks it through mid-wicket and comes back for the second run.
Another ball, on a length and drifting down leg. Jermaine Blackwood misses his nudge on the leg side. A stifled appeal from Wood but nothing from behind the sticks.
Good-length ball, around off. Jermaine Blackwood defends it off the back foot.
A short ball, around off. Nkrumah Bonner pulls it along the ground towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
A short ball, around off. Jermaine Blackwood ducks underneath.
A full ball, well outside off. Jermaine Blackwood mistimes his drive to mid off.
Back of a length, around off. Jermaine Blackwood stays back and punches it towards cover.
Back of a length, around off. Jermaine Blackwood hangs back and taps it to the off side.
Fuller in length, around middle. Jermaine Blackwood clips it behind square on the leg side and takes a single. He will retain the strike.
Woakes starts with a length ball, around middle. Jermaine Blackwood turns it to mid-wicket.
Fuller in length, outside off. Jermaine Blackwood leans and drives it to the man at extra cover.

FOUR! Edged but Blackwood didn't go hard at it and it was always going to be safe as it was played with softs hands. Back of a length, outside off. Jermaine Blackwood looks to block but it goes off the outside edge, through the slip cordon for a boundary.
Good-length ball, around off. Jermaine Blackwood keeps it out.
Back of a length, well outside off. Jermaine Blackwood leaves it alone.
FOUR! Whipped away! A low full toss, on middle. Jermaine Blackwood clips it through mid-wicket and bags a boundary.
Pitches it up, outside off. Nkrumah Bonner blocks it.
Good-length ball, outside off. Bonner leaves it alone.
Full and outside off. Nkrumah Bonner drives but straight to the fielder at mid off.
Fuller in length, on off. Nkrumah Bonner drives it towards covers.
On a good length, outside off. Bonner shoulders arms.
Good-length ball, on off, this one comes back in. Nkrumah Bonner watches the ball till the last second and makes a good leave.

OUT! CAUGHT! Brilliant review from England and Woakes finally has something to cheer for! He has been pretty ordinary with the ball so far but gets rid of West Indies' vice-captain this time! England are making a grand comeback in this game after leaking runs at the start. Now coming to the ball - This was a length ball, around off that jags back in late. Jermaine Blackwood stays back and looks to flick. He gets an inside edge onto his pad. The ball pops out and goes straight to Craig Overton at gully who takes a sitter. England appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Joe Root opts for a review. The UltraEdge shows spike as the ball passes the bat and the on-field decision is overturned. West Indies are slipping away here!
Howout: c Craig Overton b Chris Woakes

Commentary: Fuller in length, around leg. Holder looks to flick but he gets an insid eedge onto his pad. The ball rolls to the leg side for a leg bye.
On a length, around middle. Bonner gets behind the line and blocks it.
Back of a length, outside off. Nkrumah Bonner taps it to the off side.
Fuller in length, around middle. Nkrumah Bonner pushes it towards mid on.
Woakes drags his length back, around off. Bonner dabs it onto the deck.
Back of a length, around off. Holder stays back to defend it.
On a length, outside off. Holder looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge towards the slip fielder, along the ground.
Good-length ball, well outside off. Jason Holder shoulders his arms at it.
Pitches it up, around off. Holder gets forward and keeps it out.
A full ball, on middle. Jason Holder flicks but straight to the mid-wicket fielder.
Good-length delivery, around middle. Jason Holder tucks it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Easy pickings! A free hit really for Bonner! Woakes serves a length ball, on the pads. Bonner stays back and flicks it behind square on the leg side for a boundary.
Back of a length, outside off. Nkrumah Bonner leaves it alone.
Shorter in length, around off. Nkrumah Bonner covers the line to block it.
This is a length ball, around off. Nkrumah Bonner looks to defend but it goes off the outer half of the blade to cover-point.
On a length, around the off pole. Nkrumah Bonner gets forward and defends it back to the bowler.
Good-length, just outside off. Nkrumah Bonner gets to the pitch of the ball and blocks it.
Back of a length, on middle. Jason Holder hangs back and turns it to mid-wicket.
A length ball, nipping back in from off. Jason Holder looks to block but it goes off the inner half to mid-wicket.
A bit fuller, outside off. Jason Holder gets solid in his front foot defence.
Good-length ball, around off. Holder gets forward and defends it onto the deck.

Leg bye! An appeal for LBW but turned down! This is a length ball that jags back in sharply. Holder skips down a bit and tries to flick but he misses and gets hit on his pad. The ball rolls to the leg side for a leg bye.
Back of a length, around off. Nkrumah Bonner blocks it off the back foot.
FOUR! Edgy! Woakes goes full and around off. Holder sits back and looks to block it with soft hands. It takes the outside edge which rolls away past the gully fielder and into the fence.
Good-length ball, around off. Jason Holder keeps it out off the front foot.
This is on a length, around off. Jason Holder gets to the pitch of the ball and defends it to the off side.
Woakes drags his length back a bit, outside off. Holder does not bother playing at that one.
A full ball, outside off. Jason Holder prods to block it out.
A full ball, drifting onto the pads. Holder clips it towards fine leg and retains the strike by collecting a run.
On a good length, on off. Jason Holder covers the line and blocks it out.
Fuller in length, outside off. Jason Holder drives it towards cover.
Full and on off, Holder clips it away aerially but wide of the mid-wicket fielder. He crosses ends.
Nice line and length, on off. Bonner keeps it out.
Touch fuller this time, on off. Bonner covers the stumps and defends it back to the bowler.

On a length, on off. Nkrumah Bonner looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball rolls to the leg side and the batters cross. England appeal but the umpire shakes his head. They don't opt for the review.
Back of a length, on middle. Bonner tucks it to square leg for a single.
Back of a length again, coming in, on middle. Jason Holder looks to work it on the leg side but gets an inside edge onto the pads.

On a good length, on off. Jason Holder tries to work it on the leg side but again gets an inside edge onto the pads. This time the ball lobs up and falls just short of the mid-wicket fielder. This is superb bowling from Mark Wood.
Length ball, nipping in from outside off. Holder with a watchful leave.
On middle and leg, clipped behind square on the leg side for a single.
Straight and on a length, on off. Nkrumah Bonner blocks it out.
Short ball, outside off. Holder lets it go.
FOUR! Off the edge! Length ball, around off. Holder looks to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge past the second slip fielder for a boundary.
Holder tucks this length ball to deep mid-wicket for a run.
Good-length ball, outside off. Bonner just about keeps it out.
Good-length ball, on middle Bonner defends it off the front foot.
An inswinger, on off. Bonner does well to negotiate it.
An inswinging yorker, at 147 kph. Holder does well to bring his bat down and works it to deep square leg for a single.
Short ball, on leg. Pulled to deep square leg for one.
Good-length ball, on off. Holder blocks it out.
Another good-length ball, on off. Holder defends it out to the off side.
Outside off, left alone.
Fuller in length, outside off. Holder drives it towards covers.
Back of a length, on middle. Bonner covers the line and blocks it out.
Bonner picks the short length early and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Full and outside off. Holder lets it sail through.
On a length, outside off. Holder taps it to the off side.
Length, outside off. Holder offers no shot to that.
Good-length ball, around off, jagging back in. Holder shoulders arms.
A full ball, on middle. Nkrumah Bonner prods and tucks it to mid-wicket.
A full ball, down leg. Nkrumah Bonner misses his flick and Ben Foakes behind the sticks does well to grab it by diving to his left.
A yorker-length ball, angling in from middle. Nkrumah Bonner digs it out to the leg side.
Play and a miss! Back of a length, outside off. Bonner stays back to pull but he gets no bat on it.
A short ball, around middle and leg. Nkrumah Bonner ducks underneath.
Wood goes full this time, outside off. Nkrumah Bonner stays back and looks to drive but he gets an inside edge onto his pad.
Fuller and wider, outside off. Jason Holder leaves it alone.
On a length, around middle. Jason Holder tucks it wide of mid on and takes a run.
Short of a length, outside off. Nkrumah Bonner stays back and punches it to cover.
On a length, around leg. Nkrumah Bonner just helps it on its way behind square on the leg side for a single.
Pitches it up, around off. Jason Holder gets forward to block it.
A bumper, angling down leg. Holder watches it sail through to the keeper.
A full ball, outside off. Nkrumah Bonner looks to drive but it goes off the toe end towards mid off.
A yorker, around middle. Nkrumah Bonner digs it out watchfully.
A bit full, around middle. Bonner stays back to block but it goes off the inner half of the blade towards square leg.
A short ball, outside off. Bonner leaves it alone.
Fuller in length, on middle. Bonner pushes it to mid on.
Good-length ball, outside off. Bonner prods and pushes it to extra cover.
Fuller in length, outside off. Holder lets it through to the keeper.
On a length, outside off. Holder shoulders his arms at that one.
A full ball, outside off. Jason Holder keeps it out towards the off side.
Fuller and wider, outside off. Holder does not bother playing at it.

FOUR! Not the most convincing shot but a welcome boundary nonetheless for West Indies! A short ball, around off. Holder swivels and looks to pull but it takes the top edge and goes over the mid on fielder. Two bounces and over the ropes.
Short of a length, on off. Jason Holder blocks it off the back foot.
Floated, around leg. Nkrumah Bonner nudges it around the corner. Not in the gap though!
Flatter and quicker, around off. Bonner keeps it out on the off side.
A flatter ball, driting onto the pads. Bonner works it to backward square leg.
On a length, around middle. Bonner hangs back and pushes it to mid-wicket.
A full ball, drifting onto the pad. Nkrumah Bonner tucks it to mid-wicket.
Well bowled! Tosses it up, around off and spinning away late. Bonner looks to defend but it goes off the outer half of the blade towards backward point.
Short of a length, on middle. Holder turns it to square leg for a single.
On a length, outside off. Pushed towards covers.
Length ball, on off. Kept out.
FOUR! Well timed! A low full toss, outside off. Nkrumah Bonner leans and creams his drive through covers for a boundary.
This is tucked to mid-wicket for a single.
Good-length ball, on off. Holder blocks it out.
Flatter and quicker, at 95 kph, on off. Bonner keeps it out off the back foot.
On the pads, Bonner is solid in his defence.
Tossed up, on off. Bonner blocks it out.
Loopy ball, outside off. Bonner works it to point.
Tossed up, on middle. Bonner strides forward and blocks it out.
Full and on off, solidly blocked by Bonner. A maiden for Leach!
On a good length, on off. Holder plays it to mid on.
Full and on off, Holder pushes it to cover.
Length ball, on off. Holder stays solid in his defence.
Touch fuller, outside off. Holder drives it but finds the cover fielder.
Length ball, on the pads. Holder clips it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball, on middle. Bonner covers the line and knocks it to mid on.
Full and on middle, Holder plays it back to the bowler.
Full, on the pads. Nudged to mid-wicket.
Quicker one, on leg. Pushed back to the bowler.
On middle, blocked out.
Tossed up, outside off. Holder pushes it to the off side.
Flatter, on off. Holder keeps it out. Second consecutive maiden for Leach!
On a length, on middle. Bonner works it to deep square leg for a single.
Holder drives this length ball nicely to mid on for no run.
An in-slanter, on middle. Holder flicks it uppishly to deep mid-wicket for a single.
A bumper, on middle. Bonner sits under it.
On middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
Length ball, spraying on the pads. Bonner tickles it fine to fine leg. Chris Woakes from deep square leg does well to dive and cut it off. Keeps it down to two.
Leach tosses it up, around off. Jason Holder blocks it off the front foot.
On a length, around middle. Holder gets forward and defends it.
A flatter ball, going on with the arm from off. Holder stays back and tucks it behind square on the leg side.
Flatter, on off. Holder keeps it out.
Tosses it up, around off. Holder blocks it out.
Fuller and wider, outside off. Holder gets to the pitch of the ball and defends it.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Bonner taps it behind square on the off side for a brace.
A quicker ball, on a length, around off. Bonner stays back and guides it past the short third man fielder for a couple of runs.
FOUR! Top shot! Tosses it up, outside off. Holder plants his front foot forward and carves it through the extra cover region for a boundary.
Floated, around off. Holder keeps it out.
Flighted ball, on a length, around off. Holder gets forward and blocks.
Flatter and quicker, around middle. Holder stays back to defend.
Floated, around middle. Bonner blocks it off the front foot.
Slower through the air, full and on off. Bonner gets solid in his front foot defence.
Flatter ball, on middle. Bonner tucks it to the leg side.
An arm ball, going on with the angle from off. Bonner keeps it out watchfully.
Tosses it up, around off. Bonner lunges and defends it.
Nicely tossed up, just outside off. Bonner prods and keeps it out watchfully.

SIX! Well, well! Holder showing some intent here! Root serves a half-volley, around middle. Holder prods and smacks it way over long on for a biggie. That brings up the 50-run partnership between these two.
Tossed up, on middle. Holder blocks it with ease.
Flatter ball, on a length, around middle. Jason Holder tucks it to the leg side. Not in the gap though!
Floated, around off. Blocked out.
This is flatter and quicker, outside off. Holder gets back and lets it go through to the keeper.
Fuller in length, on off. Holder smothers the spin nicely and eases it to long on for one run.
Floated, full and on off. Holder blocks it off the front foot.
This is a flatter ball, around leg. Holder prods and does not bother playing at it. He pads it away.
On a length, around off. Holder defends it.
Leach serves a loopy ball, outside off. Holder taps it towards point.
Leach comes 'round the wicket and serves a wayward ball, down leg. Holder lets it be.
Leach goes back to over the wicket and hurls a flatter ball, around off. Holder blocks it to the off side.
Short of a length, on off. Punched towards covers.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Short ball, on middle. Nkrumah Bonner picks it early and swivel-pulls it to deep square leg for a boundary. Excellent execution!
On a length, on off. Bonner dabs it to third man. Doesn't have legs to go into the fence but will get two.
Short of a length, on leg. Pulled to fine leg for one.
Fuller in length, outside off. Holder drives it to wide of mid off.
On a length, on middle and leg. Holder keeps it out.
Full, on middle. Bonner blocks it off the front foot.
Floats it up, on middle. Patted back to the bowler.
Tossed up, on off. Bonner is solid in his defence.
On off, blocked out to point. Holder sets off for a single but is sent back by Bonner.
Fuller, on off. Pushed towards covers.
Shortish, on off. Bonner blocks it out. Another maiden from Leach! West Indies haven't scored a single run from this end since 1.05 am IST (7.35 pm GMT, previous day).
FOUR! Glorious! Full and wide of off, Holder gets on his backfoot and slices it through point for a boundary.
On middle, blocked on the leg side.
Good length, around off. Holder defends it from the crease.
FOUR! Length ball, outside off. Holder guides it down past the first slip fielder to third man for a boundary.
Length ball, on off. Holder looks to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge to Ben Foakes who dives to his right to make the stop.
On the pads, Holder works it to mid-wicket.
First runs for West Indies from Sir Curtly Ambrose end after 9 maidens! Length ball, sprayed on the pads. Nkrumah Bonner works it to deep square leg for a single.
Back of a length, on middle. Blocked out.
Full and on middle. Holder is watchful in his defence.
On a length, around off. Holder keeps it out.
On middle, Holder clips it through mid-wicket. Calls for two and gets it easily.
On a good length, on middle. Played to mid on.
Tossed up, on off. Bonner lunges forward and plays it to the off side.
Loopy ball, outside off. Bonner with a nice touch as he pushes it through point. Gets two! 200 up for West Indies! They trail by 110 runs!
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Flatter, on off. Bonner plays it very late behind point for a single.
Tossed up, outside off. Holder taps it to the off side.
On off, patted back to the bowler.
Back of a length, around leg. Bonner nudges it around the corner.
Good-length delivery, angling in from off. Bonner dabs it onto the deck.
A full ball, jagging back in from middle. Bonner prods and flicks it to mid-wicket.
Pitches it up, outside off. Nkrumah Bonner leaves it alone.
This is on a length, on middle. Bonner blocks it back to the bowler.
A bit full, on middle. Bonner clears his front leg and pushes it to mid on. A maiden over from Woakes!
Tossed up, on off. Blocked out.
Floated, full and on off. Jason Holder keeps it out.
Flatter and quicker, on off. Holder taps it to point.
Tosses it up, around off. Holder blocks it solidly.
Slower through the air, around off. Holder dabs it onto the deck.
A full toss to start the day's play, on middle and Holder tucks it to mid-wicket.
A length ball, coming with the angle, around off. Bonner defends it to cover. Ben Foakes, the keeper is standing up.
On a length, around off. Bonner defends on the front foot.
Angles a length ball, on the pads. Bonner misses his flick and gets hit on the pads.
Touch fuller, just outside off. Bonner gets a straight bat down to defend.
Bit of seam for Woakes, on a length, around middle. Bonner is solid on his block.
This one comes straight around off. Bonner stays back to block it out.
Stokes serves a fuller ball, way outside off. Holder shoulders arms to this one.
Full ball, outside off. Easy leave for Holder again.
A length ball, slanting around off. Holder prods to defend but gets an outside edge to first slip, Joe Root who collects it well in front of him.
Fullish and on middle. Defended.
Full and outside off. Left alone. The ball does not bounce much and the keeper fumbles a bit. A single is there but Holder is not aware of it.
Jason Holder off the mark on Day 3. Full and on the pads, flicked to deep square leg for a single.
On a length, outside off. Holder lunges and keeps it out to covers and takes a quick single.
Length and outside off. Bonner defends it on the surface.
Length and angling down the leg side. Bonner misses his flick. Ben Foakes, behind the sticks does well to collect it.
A length ball, outside off. Bonner guides it to deep point for a single.
Around off. Blocked out.
Length ball, on middle. Holder blocks it out.
A length ball, drifting on the pads. Bonner pulls it to square leg and takes a single.
Stokes goes wide of the crease and serves a length ball, angling on off. Holder defends with his bat and pad together.
Angling on middle. Holder nudges it to mid-wicket.
Outside off. Left alone.
Fuller ball, on middle. Blocked out.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Ben Stokes has forced an error here and England have got the big breakthrough. This is on a length, outside off and a bit of away swing as well. A line which always keeps batsmen in two minds, to leave or to play. Jason Holder is too late as he has a poke at it and ends up getting an outside edge to Ben Foakes takes it with ease behind the stumps and Stokes is absolutely pumped up.
Howout: c Ben Foakes b Ben Stokes

Commentary: On a length, on off. Blocked out.
WIDE! A short ball, around off. Bonner leaves it alone and Foakes does well to get a hand on it. A wide called as well for height.
Length ball, outside off. Bonner drops it to covers.
Around off, on a length. Kept out.
Angles it on the pads, tucked to deep square leg for one.
Fuller ball, on middle, it nips away late and Silva defends it on the deck.
On middle. Defended out.
A length ball, outside off. Bonner defends away from the body and from upper part of the blade.
Length ball, outside off. Bonner on the front foot, defends it to covers.
Slightly full and on middle. Bonner wrists it to deep square leg for one.
A length ball, outside off. Silva plays it late to catching cover-point.
Full ball, away movement but was way outside off. Easy leave for Silva.
Length and outside off. Defended on the off side.
Wood starts with a fuller ball, straying on the pads. Bonner turns it to deep square leg for one.
Wood makes the ball move in, around middle but Silva is watchful in his defense.
Length ball, outside off. Silva punches it wide of covers for a single. He is off the mark.
Bangs a bouncer, outside off. Bonner bottom edges his punch to point.
Short again and Bonner pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single. The Windies trail by less than 100 runs now.
Good seam position there, fuller and on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Length ball, on off. Blocked out.

Chance! A short ball with extra bounce there, on middle. Nkrumah Bonner miscues his pull shot completely, it goes off the top edge to mid-wicket where Ollie Pope charges forward and dives but fails to take it properly. The ball was dying and Pope had very little time to run forward.
A length ball, outside off, shaping away. Left alone.
Outside off again and Bonner shoulders arms to it.
Length ball, outside off. Bonner taps it to covers for a single.
Fuller this time, outside off. SIlva defends off the back foot.
Short of a length, on middle. Bonner keeps it out on the leg side.
Another solid block from Bonner.
Slightly short, around off. Bonner punches it softly to covers.
Ripper from Wood! Fuller and around off, it lands and nips back in sharply. Bonner is beaten by the movement and gets hit on the pads.
Inward movement again, on a length, outside off. Bonner presses forward and blocks it.
Full ball, straying around middle and Bonner tucks it to mid-wicket. Good probing over from Wood.
Shortish length, on off. Silva on his toes, dead-bats it.
On off, defended out.
Length ball, going down the leg side. Left alone.
Length ball, outside off. Silva defends with soft hands and dabs it down off the outer half of the bat, in the gap through the gully region for a couple of runs.
Fuller ball, angling outside off. Silva prods and blocks it.
Length ball, angling on middle. Da Silva hooks it to square leg for a run.
Back of a length, on off. Da Silva hops and defends it back onto the deck.
What happened here? A slower bumper, at just 117 clicks. Joshua Da Silva has his feet off the ground as he looks to fend it away. The ball though bounces over his head and Da Silva is a relieved man.
Length this time, angled into middle and leg. Da Silva pushes it to short mic-wicket.
A bouncer now, outside off. Silva dodges it easily.
Late movement there, outside off and coming back in. Da Silva offers no shot.
Goes wide of the crease, on a length and outside off. Da Silva steers it to third man for  asingle.
Leg bye! An appeal for LBW but that was going down the leg side. Leach gets drift in the air as he serves it fuller and on the pads. Da Silva misses his flick. It goes off the pads to square leg.
Flatter and on off, pushed to covers.
Now goes back and punches it to point.
Fuller and on off. Bonner leans and pushes it to covers.
Flatter ball, this one straightens off the deck. Bonner prods and defends it.
Slightly full and on middle. Bonner comes forward to keep it out.
Short in length, on off. Da Silva hops and blocks it on the off side.
A length ball, around middle. Da Silva pushes it to mid on.
Wood comes over the wicket and bowls it on a length, on middle. Da Silva shuffles across and tucks it through short leg for a single.
FOUR! Cries of 'catch it' but this went through the gap! Short of a length, on middle. Bonner gets on top of the bounce and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
FOUR! Bonner making the most of the old ball here! Short again, outside off. Bonner hits it aerially and through point for another boundary.
Short in length, outside off. Bonner again wants to pull but fails this time.

Woakes starts off with a fullish delivery, wide of the off pole and this one shapes away nicely. Da Silva with an easy leave though. Also, Woakes has overstepped and starts his new spell with a no ball.
Good-length this time, outside off and the ball holds its line. Da Silva with another leave.
This is angled into middle and leg, looking for the dream outswinging delivery. Joshua Da Silva gets right behind the line to block.
FOUR! Edgy boundary! A bit fuller, around off and there is away movement this time. Da Silva pushes at it and gets an outside edge past the slip cordon for a boundary.
Full again, around off. Da Silva shoulders arms to this one.
Angling in from outside off and leaving the right-hander. Watchful leave by Da Silva.
Joshua Da Silva walks towards the bowler and gets right behind the line of the ball to make the block.
Overton starts off with a length ball, on leg stump and swinging further down. Ben Foakes does well to dive to his left and stop the ball.
Pitched up, in that corridor of uncertainty. Bonner leaves it alone.
Full again, on off. Bonner defends it back towards the bowler.
Around the top of off. Bonner hangs back and bunts it out on the off side.
Fifty for Nkrumah Bonner and this has been a fine, fine knock. Full, angled in from wide of the crease. Bonner pushes it out towards cover and picks up a single.
Full again, around off. Da Silva squeezes it out towards point.
Full and well outside off. No need to play at that one.
Well left! Full and angled into off stump. The ball shapes away at the last moment and Nkrumah Bonner makes a watchful leave. The ball zips through to the keeper as well.
And again! This is a bit further away from the off stump and it's an easier leave for Bonner.
Woakes hits the length hard and angles it from around off. Bonner stays solid in defense.
Fuller this time, on middle and shaping away just a bit. Bonner blocks it out.
Maiden over! Pitched up, close to the off stump and shaping away nicely. Bonner shoulders arms to that one.

Hint of away movement from Craig Overton. Length, on off and just nipping away off the surface. Da Silva gets caught on the crease and gets rapped high on the pads. It is given as a no ball as Overton oversteps.
This is spilled way down the leg side. Good takes from the keeper.
Full and on the pads. Joshua Da Silva works it in front of square on the leg side and picks up a couple of runs.
Nicely driven for two more. Overpitched, around off. Da Silva presses forward and strokes it through extra cover for a brace.
A length ball, outside off. Left alone by Da Silva.
Right on the money this time! Around the top of off. Solidly defended by Joshua Da Silva.
Uppish but in the gap! Short of a length, on off. Da Silva doesn't get hold of the pull shot but manages to hit it well wide of short mid-wicket to collect a couple of runs.
Full and wide, Bonner isn't interested in playing at that one.
Well bowled and well left! This is angled in from wide of the crease and the ball zips away off the surface. Bonner watches it all the way through and leaves it alone.
Fullish delivery, angled into middle. Bonner defends it off the front foot.
Full again but wide of the off pole. Bonner can leave deliveries like that one all day long.
This is pitched up, on off. Bonner is forced to play at that one and defends it out towards mid off.
Pitched up, in that channel outside off but shaping away. Bonner with another good leave. Back-to-back maidens for Chris Woakes.
Huge inward movement this time but after the ball passes the batter. Well outside off, Da Silva with an easy leave.
Length, angled into off. Da Silva keeps it out towards short mid-wicket.

NOT OUT! Brilliant review from Joshua Da Silva and he survives. Fullish delivery, angled in from around off. The ball pitches and nips back in a long way. Da Silva shuffles right across the stumps and his head seems to be falling over. He misses the tuck and gets pinged on the pads. Da Silva reviews it straightaway. UltraEdge shows that there's no bat involved and Ball Tracker shows that the ball was in fact doing a bit too much and missing leg stump by a few inches.
A tad bit short, on off. Da Silva pulls it through mid-wicket for a single.
Full, around off and shaping in. Bonner defends it out.
Full and wide this time, guided towards backward point.
A length ball, well outside off. Da Silva leaves it alone.
Full and angled into the off stump. Da Silva does well to get a bat on it.
This is angled into middle and leg, Da Silva tucks it towards short mid-wicket.
Woakes hits the length hard this time and bowls it around off. Da Silva taps it back onto the deck off the back foot.
Pitched up, around off. Da Silva leans in and nudges it towards point with soft hands.
Back of a length, over off. Joshua Da Silva hangs back and keeps it down on the off side. Yet another maiden for Chris Woakes.

SIX! England's lead is diminishing sooner rather than later. Wood comes back in and starts off with a wayward delivery on the hips. Nkrumah Bonner uses the pace and swings at it. The ball goes off the top edge and flies over the fine leg fence.
This is banged into the deck, on the body. Bonner fends it away on the leg side and collects a run.
Back of a length, on off. Da Silva defends it off the back foot.
Pitched up, on off. Da Silva presents a dead bat at it.
Good-length, over middle. Joshua Da Silva shuffles a bit and tickles it 'round the corner for a single.
Much better from Wood. Length, hitting the top of middle. Bonner blocks it solidly off the front foot.
Pitched up, well outside off. The batter isn't going to play at that one.
On a length, around the top of off. Da Silva hangs back and keeps it out towards short cover.
Angled into off, but leaving the batter after pitching. Da Silva makes a watchful leave.
Lovely shape on that one! Length, angled into middle. The ball nips away off the surface. Da Silva though stays solid in defense.

Now, Chris Woakes does get one to nip back in and it's a peach of a delivery. Woakes goes wide of the crease and angles it in from well outside off. The ball nips back in and Joshua Da Silva gets cut in half. The ball clips the top of the pad and the bowler seems interested. Nothing given and they don't go for the review as the impact might have been outside off. Indeed it was, as the replays confirm the same.
Back of a length, around off. This is pushed away on the off side for a single. The 250 comes up for West Indies.
Shorter in length, outside off. Joshua Da Silva hops on the back foot and punches it towards cover.
Short again, around middle. Da Silva goes deep in his crease to work it through mid-wicket for a run.
Nicely drifted into off, the ball turns away a bit. Bonner leaves it alone in the end.
FOUR! A confident-looking sweep shot from Nkrumah Bonner. Flatter, on off. Bonner gets down on one knee and sweeps it hard and low, past short leg for a boundary.
Too short and wide from Leach. Bonner rocks back and taps it with the spin through the cover region for a brace. The 50 partnership also comes up between these two.
Quicker and shorter, around off. Bonner rocks back and cuts it through cover-point. Craig Overton chases it from cover and keeps it down to a couple. The runs flowing nicely now for the hosts.
Full toss, outside off. Da Silva pushes it to the left of mid off.
Length and on off. Blocked out.
A length ball, angling on middle. Da Silva solidly blocks it.
Fuller ball, outside off, swinging away and Da Silva lets it be.
Short of a length, slanting around off. Da Silva hops and pulls it, not off the middle and hits it over mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Length ball, straying around middle and off. Da Silva prods and defends it.
Flatter ball, around off. Bonner punches off the back foot to deep cover for a single.
Fuller ball, outside off. Da Silva pushes with the spin, through covers for a single.
Angles a fuller ball, on off. Bonner guides it straight to point.
A single as this is pushed through covers.
Slightly short, slower in the air and hint of spin as well. Da Silva lunges to defend but gets an outside edge wide of first slip to third man for a brace.
Strays it on the pads, flicked to square leg for a single.
Short ball, on middle. Da Silva pulls it hard and to the left of deep square leg. Ollie Pope has to run quickly there and puts a dive to save a couple of runs. Good fielding.
Around off, fuller and pushed wide of mid off for a single.
Length ball, angling on middle. Bonner hits it through the line to mid on.
Length outside off, and left alone.
Fuller ball, coming into the right-hander. Bonner with an easy leave.
Alength ball, slanting on middle. Bonner wrists it to square leg and takes a single. That will be Lunch on Day 3.
Flatter ball, on off. Bonner goes back in his crease and punches it through point for a single. West Indies are offf the mark in this session.
Fuller and on middle. Joshua Da Silva keeps it out.
Tossed up, on off. Da Silva drops it on the off side.
Tossed up, drifting on the pads. Da Silva goes back and tucks it towards short leg.
This one lands around leg and spins a touch away. Da Silva is aware and defends it solidly.
Down the leg side and Da Silva leaves it alone.
Bangs a short ball, around middle and leg. Bonner sits under it.
Length ball, outside off. Bonner punches and beats the man at gully for a single.
A short ball but angling down the leg side. Da Silva ducks under it.
Back of a length, on off. Da Silva hops and keeps it out.
A length ball, going down. It does not bounce much and takes the ads off Da Silva who leaves it alone. Good take by Foakes behind.
On middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
Short ball, outside off. Bonner waits and cuts it late past backward point. The fielder gives a chase and slides it back near the ropes. The batters take two runs.
Shorter and on off, pushed to covers.
Fuller and on middle. Bonner dead-bats it.
Tossed up, on middle and Bonner on the back foot, blocks it out. Jack Leach is getting turn here.
Slightly short, on middle. Bonner hits it on the leg side.
Around off, pushed to covers.
Short and on middle, pulled away to square leg for a single. Da Silva is jogging across and that tempts Ben Stokes to have a shy at the bowler's end. No one backing up and they get another single.
Length ball, on off. Da Silva defends it.
Short ball, hitting the pitch hard and Da Silva evades it well.
On middle, on a length. Blocked out.
A short ball and on middle. Da Silva sits under it. A wide given for height.
Craig goes wide of the crease and angles a short ball, on leg. Da Silva tickles it off the gloves and the keeper fumbles to collect it. A single taken.
On a length, outside off, good pace there. Bonner defends with a straight bat but gets an outside edge to point.
Flatter ball, outside off. Left alone.

OUT! LBW! Leach serves a tossed up delivery, angling around middle and leg. Da Silva goes on the back foot to flick it but misses and gets hit slightly high on the pads. An appeal and up goes the finger. Da Silva takes the review quickly and the replay shows no bat involved but Ball Tracking shows the ball is going onto hit the top of the leg pole. Jack Leach is finally rewarded for his persistence.
Howout: lbw b Jack Leach

Commentary: Shorter and outside off. Joseph punches it to covers.
On middle. Blocked out.
Alzarri Joseph is off the mark! Flatter ball, outside off. Joseph punches with an angled bat, wide of first slip and they get a single.
Tossed up, on middle. Bonner stays back to defend it out.
Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
Short again and Joseph ducks under it.
A length ball, angling on the pads, tucked to mid-wicket for a run.
Short ball again but Nkrumah Bonner is not tempted to go for the pull shot. Lets it through to the keeper.
Touch short this time, on leg. Bonner pulls it, off his gloves and to fine leg for a single.

OUT! TAKEN! If Nkrumah Bonner is not tempted, Alzarri Joseph gets into the trap here. Brilliant from England! A short ball again, angling on middle. Alzarri Joseph goes for the pull but gets a top edge to fine leg where Ollie Pope, the substitute fielder comes forward and takes it low. England trying to bundle things quickly. West Indies trail by 29 runs.
Howout: c sub Ollie Pope b Craig Overton

Commentary: Flatter and on middle. Defended out.
Outside off, pushed to covers.
Very full and on middle, pushed towards mid on, not in the gap though.
Tossed up, on middle. Kept out.
Slightly fuller and on off. Bonner steps across and defends it out.

Dropped! What a chance for England! This is full and angling on the pads. Bonner looks to heave it on the leg side but gets a thin inside edge onto the pads and to first slip where Zak Crawley makes a meal of it. First it looked like there was no bat but UltaEdge confirms bat on it.
More short stuff from Overton. Over middle, Roach ducks under it.
And again! This time over middle and leg. Roach with another easy duck.
This time the ball doesn't bounce high enough. This is banged in on middle, Roach looks to duck under it again but the ball just about goes over his helmet.
This is fuller and angled down leg. Roach looks to tuck but misses and the ball dies on the way to the keeper.
Length this time, angled into middle and leg. Roach keeps it down on the leg side.
This is spilled down the leg side, Roach gets no bat on it. Back-to-back maiden overs for the visitors.
Quicker, darted into middle. Bonner strides out to defend.
Quicker and fuller, drifted into middle. Bonner goes on the back foot to keep this one out.
Flatter this time, on off. Defended nicely by Bonner.
Full, around off. This is pushed towards the cover region.
Drifting into middle and leg. Bonner goes on the back foot and keeps it down to short leg.
On middle and leg, Bonner looks to drive but mistimes it to the right of the bowler as Leach makes a good diving stop. Yet another maiden over and the Windies starting to get bogged down here.
Fullish ball, bowled in that channel around off and angling in. The ball holds its line after pitching and Roach gets beaten past the outside edge.
This is banged in over middle and leg. Kemar Roach ducks under it.
Full and on the pads. Roach tucks it away to backward leg.

That's a nasty one for Kemar Roach. Banged into the deck around off. This is at 123 kph and just doesn't bounce that higher. Roach tries to sway away from the line of the ball but instead gets a body blow.
Nice follow-up delivery from Overton. A slower yorker, floated in around off stump. Roach does well to keep it out.
Good-length, on off. Roach stays solid in defense and it will be a fourth maiden on the trot for England.
Full and straight, Nkrumah Bonner digs it out towards mid off and picks up a single.

Nicely bowled! A length ball, on off and this one lands right on the seam and takes off. Kemar Roach looks to push at it but the extra bounce surprises him a bit and the ball goes off the thumb towards the slip cordon. Roach seems to be in some pain here.

How did that miss the off pole? This is pitched up, around off and the ball comes in with the angle. Roach goes on the back foot and gets beaten past the outside edge. The ball somehow goes a whisker over the off stump as well.
Peach! Pitched up, outside off and this one slants in a long way. Kemar Roach gets beaten past the outside edge again and Ben Foakes collects the ball past the leg stump.
Woakes hits the length hard and angles it down the leg side. No shot offered.

Banged in, around the body. Roach tucks it away to deep mid-wicket and there's an easy single on offer. Nkrumah Bonner knowing that it's the last ball of the over, denies him and Roach has a smile on his face. He would have loved to get off the mark here.
Around the top of off, this is pushed towards mid on.
This is fuller and angled into middle and leg. Bonner does well to flick it leg side.
Length, on off. Bonner hangs back and pushes it towards mid off.
Short ball, on the body. This is pulled down to deep backward square leg for a single.
Full and angling into off. Roach plays a solid defensive shot.
This is slanted into the pads. Roach manages to keep it down to the left of the short leg fielder.
On off, blocked out by Bonner.
A length ball, around off. Bonner taps it towards short cover.
Just a tad bit short and this is jabbed down to deep mid-wicket for just a single.
Right on the money from Chris Woakes! Roach stays solid in defense though.
Fuller and trying to slant it into middle and leg. Kemar Roach works it through mid-wicket off the inner half of the bat and picks up a couple of runs to get off the mark.
Pitched up, on middle. Roach blocks it out.
Around off, pushed out on the off side.
Full and on off. Bonner drives it towards mid off and scampers through for a quick single.
Length this time, angled into off. Roach gets right behind the line of the ball to make the block.
On middle and leg, tucked away to mid-wicket.
Stokes hits the length hard and bowls it on middle. Roach manages to keep it down on the leg side.
Good-length, over off. Blocked out.
This is drifted onto middle and leg. Bonner blocks it out.
Flatter this time, on a nagging length and around off. Bonner goes back and across to block.
Quicker, on off. This is pushed back towards the bowler.
Darted into middle this time. Bonner keeps it out.
Around middle and leg, Bonner goes deep in the crease and keeps it down past short leg.
Good from Nkrumah Bonner, picking up the single off the final delivery. Tossed up, on off. Bonner uses his feet and pushes it towards mid off for a quick single.
This is banged in over middle. Bonner pulls it along the ground towards deep square leg and picks up a single.
Fullish delivery, around off. Roach looks to cover drive away from the body and gets an inside edge towards short mid-wicket.
Pitched up, outside off. Roach shoulders arms to that one.
Length this time, slanting into off. Roach defends it out.
Well-directed short ball, over middle. Kemar Roach does well to duck under that one. The ball comes off the shoulder of the batter and that must have stung a bit.
On middle, kept out towards mid-wicket.
Slower through the air, around off. Bonner waits for it and dabs it towards first slip.
On off, turning away. Played with the spin towards covers.
Flatter, angled into middle and leg. Worked towards mid-wicket by Bonner.
A bit flighted, on off. Bonner drives it straight towards covers.
On middle, driven past a diving mid on fielder for a single. West Indies trail by just 20 runs now.
Floated up, on off. Kemar Roach puts out a big stride forward to defend.
Woakes serves a beautiful yorker, on middle and Bonner gets his bat down in time.
Length and on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Length and on middle. Bonner tucks it off the inner half to square leg.
This is on middle. Bonner is happy to show his defensive skills.
Angles it on the pads. Bonner works it to square leg for a single.
Slants a full delivery, on middle. Roach blocks it out.
Flatter and around off. Bonner defends it on the off side.
FOUR! Well played! Tossed up, full and on middle. Bonner sweeps it in the gap to square leg for a boundary.
Around off, it is hit to covers for one.
An arm ball, flatter and angling around middle. Roach defends it on the front foot.
Slides a length ball, on middle. Kept out.
Another solid block to end the over.
Length and on the pads. Bonner flicks it to mid-wicket.
On middle, on a length. Bonner tucks it wide of square leg for a run.
A low dipping full toss, on off, pushed to covers.
Short of a length, outside off. Roach hangs his bat out but the ball goes well over it.
Full and on middle, pushed to covers.
Touch fuller, angling on middle. A straight bat defensive push back to the bowler.
Length ball, at 121 kph, around off. Blocked out.
Length ball, outside off. Bonner defends with hard hands, uppishly and to point.
Short of a length, on middle. Bonner pulls it to deep square leg for a single. Too casual running from Nkrumah Bonner. He looks a bit weary.
Bangs a bouncer now, on middle. Roach lets it through.
On middle. Defended out.
A slower length ball, outside off and nipping back in. Roach taps it to point.
Shorter and on middle, played on the leg side.
Flatter and outside off. Bonner hits it to point.
Tossed up, on off. Bonner drives it to long off for a single. 300 up for the WIndies.
Angles it on the pads. Defended to square leg.
Tossed up, on off. Roach blocks it out.
Fuller and on middle. Kemar prods and dead-bats it.
Short in length, on off. Bonner bends a bit back and defends it to covers.
Length ball, outside off. Bonner drops it to point.
A length ball, outside off. Bonner mistimes his cut to point.
A fuller ball, outside off, the ball just grips there, might have come from the back of the hand. Bonner drives it to covers.
This one nips back in, on middle, pushed to mid-wicket.
Pitches it up, outside off. A solid defensive shot from Nkrumah Bonner. More than 400 minutes now on the crease.
Tossed up, fuller and on middle. Roach lunges and defends it.
Another solid block from Kemar on this full ball.
Full and on middle, pushed to mid on.
On middle. Blocked out.

FOUR! Edged away! This one comes with the angle, fuller and outside off, spinning away after landing. Kemar Roach looks to drive but gets an outside edge, left of first slip for a boundary. Was a chance there.
On middle, pushed back to Leach.
Length and on middle, Bonner turns it to square leg for a single.
A pacy short ball, on middle. Roach sits under it.
Outside off. Left alone.

A huge appeal but mostly from the players behind the stumps! A length ball, around off and nips away a touch off the deck. Kemar Roach looks to defend inside the line but gets beaten on the outside edge and takes his top of back pad on its way to the keeper. Craig Overton knew it.
Short and on middle. Roach evades it.
On the pads, tucked to square leg.
Fuller and on the pads from around the wicket. Bonner whips it to deep square leg for a single.
Tossed up, on off. Roach blocks it out.
A full toss, on middle, pushed to mid on.
Flatter ball, this one skids through, on middle. Roach flicks it uppishly and past short leg.
Tossed up, on middle. Kept out.
Slightly short and on middle. Kemar lunges to defend but the ball takes the shoulder of the bat and goes well wide of short leg. There is a leg slip as well but it goes in the gap.
Tossed up, on middle. Bonner blocks it.
Flatter, holding the line, on middle. Bonner blocks it off the back foot.
A single as this is whipped through mid-wicket.
Flatter and sliding on the pads. Kemar misses his flick.
Served full and on middle. Roach dead-bats it.
Tossed up, on off. Kemar presses forward and defends it out.
This is pushed full and across the off stump. Bonner blocks it out.
On middle, worked past short leg for a single
FOUR! Top shot from Kemar Roach! Full and wide, driven through the cover region for a boundary and now West Indies lead by 1 run.
FOUR! This is poor bowling from the captain. Down the leg side, Roach tickles it fine and picks up another boundary, this time towards the fine leg region.
Fired onto the pads, Roach keeps it down to leg slip.
Around leg, this is nudged on the leg side for a single. West Indies on the ascendancy now.
On off, blocked out by Roach.
A tad shorter, around off. Roach defends it off the back foot.
Quicker and flatter, on off. Roach presses forward and pushes it towards cover-point.
This is around off. Easily blocked out by Roach.
Nicely drifted into middle and leg. Roach keeps it out on the leg side.
Flighted and on middle. Roach defends it off the front foot. Maiden over for Jack Leach.
FOUR! Loose delivery, down the leg side and Nkrumah Bonner takes full advantage. Bonner paddles it past leg slip and into the fine leg fence, moves on to 97 now.
Around leg, pushed towards short mid-wicket.
On off. Blocked out.
This is flatter and on middle. Bonner turns it through square leg for a single.
On off, kept out by Roach.
Full and straight. Kemar Roach defends it off the front foot and that will be Tea on Day 3!
Leach starts off with a flighted ball, around leg. Bonner looks to tuck it away but misses and gets hit on the pads. Half an appeal from the bowler but that's all.

FOUR! Swept away and that's the hundred up for Nkrumah Bonner! What a gritty and patient innings this has been! His second century and both have come on this ground and he receives a big round of applause from the crowd. This is down the leg side, Bonner paddles it into the fine leg fence.
Nicely bowled! On middle and turning away. Bonner gets squared up a bit.
On middle and going on with the angle. Bonner keeps it out.
On middle and again. Solidly defended by Bonner.
Flatter this time, around off. Bonner strides out to defend.
On a good length, over middle. Roach gets behind the line of the ball to block.
Fullish delivery, outside off. Roach lets this one through to the keeper.
This is banged into the deck and angled at the body. Roach fends it away and gets a blow on the arm.
Full and slanted into middle. Roach punches it back to the bowler.

Ooh! That wasn't far away from the off stump. A cross-seam delivery, nipping back in from outside off. Roach makes the leave but it's a bit too close for comfort and Stokes cannot believe that it has missed the off pole.
Around off, Roach presents a dead bat at it.
This is darted onto middle. Bonner keeps it out on the leg side.
Full and Leach is keeping the pace at around 90 clicks. Bonner blocks it out.

NOT OUT! Jack Leach slows this one up ever so slightly and drifts it on a nagging length into middle and leg. The ball goes on with the arm and Nkrumah Bonner is pushed onto the back foot. Bonner looks to work it leg side but the ball skids on and hits the pads. Huge appeal from the bowler but the umpire is unmoved. Joe Root isn't convinced but reviews it anyway. No bat involved and Ball Tracker shows that the ball was just clipping leg stump. Not enough to overturn the decision though.
On middle and leg, flicked away to square leg.
On off, Bonner leans forward to block.
A bit shorter, Bonner hangs back and steers it to backward point.
Flashy from Kemar Roach now. Back of a length, around off. Roach looks to pull it away but gets an under edge and the ball goes nowhere.
Stokes tries to attack the pads but spills it down the leg side.

Not well judged by Kemar Roach. Stokes bangs it halfway down the track and angles it in at the body. Roach takes his eyes off the ball, expecting it to bounce over his head. The ball doesn't rise up at all and Roach gets a blow into the midriff.
A yorker now on off stump. Roach just about manages to jam it out.
On off, blocked out on the off side.
Banged into the deck, on off. Roach is caught on the crease as he tries to fend it away but the ball hits the handle of the bat.
Nicely drifted into middle. Blocked out by Bonner.
Flatter this time, on off. Bonner edges it back onto the deck.
Sliding onto middle and leg. Bonner gets an inside edge towards leg slip.
On middle, this is pushed back to the bowler.

OUT! RUN OUT! A bit of miscommunication between the batters and Kemar Roach has to depart. Quicker and flatter, around off. Nkrumah Bonner just dabs it down to backward point and sets off for a single, trying to keep strike for the next over. Roach is a bit slow to respond and the substitute fielder, Ollie Pope is onto it in a flash. He throws it to the keeper and Ben Foakes whips off the bails in a flash. The third umpire is called in and the replays show that Roach is short of his crease. This could be a huge moment in the context of the match.
Howout: run out (sub Ollie Pope / Ben Foakes)

Commentary: On middle, Permaul strides out to defend.

Ouch! Short and angled into the body. Once again the ball doesn't rise up enough and Nkrumah Bonner misses the pull shot. He gets hit on the thigh pad and is on the ground. Ben Stokes has a little laugh about it but Bonner is fine.
Length this time, over off. Bonner plays it towards mid-wicket.
A bumper now, over middle and leg. Bonner does well to duck under it.
FOUR! In no man's land! Banged in short, around off. Nkrumah Bonner tries to take it on and goes for the hook. The ball flies off the top edge and goes over the keeper's head for a boundary.
Angled into middle and leg, this is flicked through mid-wicket for a single. The lead is now worth 20 runs.

NOT OUT! Ben Stokes thought he had his third wicket but it wasn't meant to be. A length ball, around off and nipping back in sharply. Veerasammy Permaul presents a dead bat at it but gets pinged on the front pad. Stokes appeals and after a long think, the umpire raises the finger. Permaul reviews it in an instant claiming he's got an inside edge. The same is confirmed by UltraEdge and he survives. Stokes looks disheartened.
On middle, kept out by Bonner.
Fullish delivery, this is worked through mid-wicket for a single.
Flatter delivery, close to the off pole. Permaul dabs it onto the off side.
Veerasammy Permaul comes a long way down the pitch and Jack Leach pulls back the length significantly. Permaul just pads it away and there's a stifled appeal from the visitors. Nothing given though.
Darted into middle, Permaul blocks it out.
Around off, Permaul steps out again but gets yorked. He scampers back inside the crease before silly point can have a shy as the stumps.
A length ball, outside off. Bonner shoulders arms to it.
Pitches it up, outside off, driven to covers.
A short ball now, it comes with an angle and nips away a touch. Left alone.
Outside off again. Bonner with an easy leave.
A short ball, around middle. Bonner sits under it.
Full ball, outside off. Bonner lets it be.
A length ball, straight around off. Permaul defends it.
On a length, on middle. Permaul hops and defends it on the leg side.
Short in length, on middle. Permaul pulls it gently to fine leg for a single.
Length ball, outside off. Bonner punches off the back foot to deep covers for a single.
A length ball, angling on middle. Permaul blocks it out.
Length again, Permaul gets inside the line of the ball to keep it out.
A length ball, on middle. Bonner mistimes his pull to square leg.
Around off. Kept out.
Short of a length, on middle. Bonner pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Around off, length and Permaul defends it with soft hands.
On off, on a length. Permaul blocks it on the off side.
Short again, not that short and Permaul hooks it to square leg for a single.
FOUR! Edged away! Touch fuller and outside off. Permaul presses forward to defend but gets an outside edge past the slip cordon for a boundary.
Bangs it hard on the deck, on middle and Permaul misses his pull.
Down the leg side. Permaul misses his flick.
Length and on middle. Permaul blocks it on the leg side.
Almost a yorker but Permaul does well to push it away to mid on.
Short in length, down the leg side. Permaul misses his whip.
Short in length, on middle. Bonner pulls it to deep square leg but doesn't take the single.
On middle, on a length. Bonner dead-bats it.
Length ball angling down the leg side and Bonner pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Length and slanting around middle. Permaul gets a straight bat down.
Slightly short, on middle. Permaul pulls it nicely but straight to mid-wicket.
Short of a length, around off and extra bounce there as well. Permaul hops and defends from the higher part of the blade, to point.
Fullish and outside off, driven to mid off.
A length ball, outside off. Bonner cuts it to deep point for a single.
Woakes hurls in and produces a yorker, on middle. Permaul closes the bat face and squeezes it out to short leg, good stop made there.
A short ball, on middle. Permaul sits under it.
Very full  this time and again Veerasammy shows his defensive attribute.
Length ball, on middle. Permaul bunts it to deep square leg for a single.
Around off, pushed to covers.
Overton comes 'round the wicket, length and on middle. Permaul almost anticipates the length and defends this out.
Outside off. Permaul allows it.
FOUR! Overton misses his line and serves a full toss, on middle. Permaul with a full face of the bat, pushes it past mid off for a boundary.
A length ball, slower and down the leg side. Permaul thinks of the pull but leaves it in the end.
A short ball, outside off. Permaul hangs his bat out and the ball takes the bottom edge to the keeper, on a bounce.
Slower in the air, flatter and on middle. Bonner defends it out.

NOT OUT! Tossed up, fuller and sliding on the pads. Nkrumah Bonner gets on his knee to sweep but misses and gets hit on the pads. An appeal but the umpire is unmoved. England take the review. UltraEdge shows no bat while Ball Tracking shows umpire's call on wickets hitting, again. Nkrumah Bonner survives and the wait goes on for England.
Around off. Blocked out.
Fuller, quicker and on middle. Bonner watches it out.
Around off, fuller and Bonner on the back foot, blocks it.
A loopy ball, outside off. Bonner defends it well away from his body.
A length ball, around off. Permaul is squared up as he defends this one.
Short of a length, outside off. Permaul hops and blocks it out.
Length and around off. Permaul blocks on the off side.
A length ball, straying on middle. Permaul keeps it out.
Short ball, outside off. Permaul defends well inside the line.
Length ball, outside off. Permaul taps it to silly point, who collects it on a bounce.
Fuller ball, spinning around off; Bonner defends on the back foot.
Flatter and on off. Bonner drives it on the front foot to covers.
On middle, blocked out.
Outside off and Bonner guides it to point.
Fuller and on off. Bonner on top, defends it.
Shorter and on middle. Bonner keeps it out.
On a good length, around off. Permaul hangs back and defends it out.
Woakes goes fuller this time, on middle and leg. Permaul strokes it to mid on.
Full and straight, punched to the left of short mid on who does well to put in the dive and cut it off.
Around the top of off, Permaul backs away a bit and taps it towards point.

A short ball, from 'round the wicket and at the body. Veerasammy Permaul takes on the pull shot and hits it towards deep mid-wicket. Jack Leach runs around from the square leg fence and keeps it down to a brace.
This is spilled way down the leg side. Permaul isn't going to play at that one.
Nicely drifted into middle. Bonner puts out a stride forward to defend.
This is pushed through quicker and on off. Bonner goes on the back foot to block it out.
Sliding onto the pads, tucked away 'round the corner for one. The 350 is up for West Indies.
Around off, Permaul makes room and tries to open up the off side but can't get it past extra cover.
Just wide of the fielder at short leg. Around middle and leg, Permaul plays at it with soft hands and keeps it down to the left of short leg.

Ooh, the inside edge saved Permaul! Slowed up, around middle and leg. Permaul strides out to defend but the ball keeps a bit low, takes the inside edge and comes off the pads. The ball goes past the leg stump and as the bowler appeals, the batters come back for the second.
A length ball, on off. Bonner blocks it out.
Very full, on off. Bonner jams it out to short mid off.
FOUR! Really a nothing delivery from Chris Woakes. Banged in halfway down the track, with no venom on it. Nkrumah Bonner pulls it in front of square on the leg side and picks up a boundary.

Ooh, that looked close! Length this time, on off and the ball just nips back in a fraction. Bonner is caught on the crease and is late to get his bat down. He gets pinged on the pads but maybe it was off the inside edge. Woakes appeals and then walks back to his mark. The replays confirm that there was a faint edge on it.
This is outside off, Bonner leaves it alone.
Slanting into middle, punched out by Bonner.
This is tossed up, on middle. Veerasammy Permaul does go for the slog sweep but gets it off the inner half of the bat and into the big gap at mid-wicket. They come back for the second with ease.
On off, Permaul blocks it out.
Nicely floated, on off. Permaul looks for the big heave and gets it off the inner half of the blade yet again. The ball goes past short leg and they get another couple of runs.
Flighted, around off. Permaul defends it out.
On off, Permaul strides out to block.
Aggression again from Permaul. Tossed up, around middle. Permaul steps out and drills it straight to mid on.
Pitched up, on off. Bonner stays solid in defense.

FOUR! Cries of 'catch' but it's well wide of the fielder. A well-directed short ball, at the body. Nkrumah Bonner gets in position early and pulls it aerially to the left of the deep backward square leg fielder for a boundary. The lead goes past the 50-run mark now.
Woakes hits the length hard and bowls it on off. Bonner blocks it out.
On a good length, angled into middle and leg. Bonner hops back to defend.
That should have been an easy single. Back of a length, around off. Bonner stabs it into the gap around point and looks for the single but Permaul is caught napping.
Around the top of off. Bonner presents a dead bat at it.
Flighted, on off. Permaul pushes it out on the off side.
Drifted into middle and leg, Permaul nudges it on the leg side.
Darted into middle. Blocked out.
Around off, Permaul defend sit out nicely.
Quicker one, on off. Permaul defends it off the front foot.
Slightly flatter, around off. Veerasammy Permaul goes on the back foot and punches it towards mid off.
Stokes starts the new spell with a bouncer, on off stump. Bonner sways away from the line of the ball.
Angled into off, the ball just holds its line after pitching. Bonner defends it out solidly.

NOT OUT! Nkrumah Bonner reviewed it straightaway and knew he had got a bat on it. A length ball, on off and nipping back in. Bonner gets caught on the crease and deflects it off the inside edge onto the pads. Ben Stokes though runs away in celebration and the umpire raises his finger. The replays roll in and quite clearly there's a deflection which is then confirmed by UltraEdge. Stokes gasps again and the visitors keep on getting frustrated.
Short and wide, Bonner throws his hands at it but fails to connect.
Full and around off, this is stroked away towards cover.
Back of a length, around off. Bonner leaves it alone.
Good stop! Tossed up, around off and nicely driven towards extra cover by Permaul but the fielder does well to make the stop.
Sliding into middle and leg, Permaul blocks it out.
FOUR! Thumped! Tossed up, on middle. Veerasammy Permaul dances down the track and hammers it right back over the bowler's head for a boundary.
Quicker one, darted into middle. Permaul just about gets a bat on it.
This is pushed through quicker on middle. Permaul makes the block.
Very full, sliding into off. Permaul remains solid in defense.
A length ball, on the pads. Bonner nudges it with soft hands towards short mid-wicket.
A bouncer now, over middle. The ball doesn't rise up much but Nkrumah Bonner does well to duck under it.
Length again, slanting into middle. Bonner defends it out solidly towards short cover.
Good bouncer from Stokes, over off stump. Bonner once again ducks under it.
Very full and wide, Bonner wants to drive but just remains disciplined and leaves it alone.
This is sliding down the leg side. Bonner looks to get a tickle on it but misses. Good take from Foakes down to his left.
Floated up, on off. Permaul drives it straight to silly mid on.
Tossed up, around off. Permaul pushes it firmly towards mid off where Ben Stokes misfields and allows the batters to scamper through for a run.
Sliding into middle. Bonner defends it out.
Bonner looks to use his feet but gets cramped for room. He defends it out once again.
Flatter and outside off, chopped down to backward point for a run.
On off, Permaul strides out to defend.
Length ball, on off. Bonner prods and defends it.
Length ball,angling down the leg side. Bonner helps it away to fine leg but does not take a single.
A pacy short ball, on middle. Bonner sits under it.
Down the leg side. Easy leave.
A length ball, outside off. Bonner guides it to point.
Outside off and Bonner shoulders arms to it.
Tossed up, full and on middle. Permaul blocks it.
On middle. Kept out.
Comes around the wicket and bowls it full and on the pads. Blocked out.
On the pads, flicked low to square leg.
Continues to serve it on the pads. Defeded.
Down the leg side. Permaul misses his flick.
Length and on middle. Bonner drops a straight bat in defense.
Length ball, outside off. Bonner drives it to deep cover. Not taking a single again.
Short of a length, around off. Bonner defends on the up and gets an outside edge past first slip to third man. A single denied.
On middle. Blocked out.
Short in length, outside off. Bonner chops it on the off side.
Short ball now, on middle. Bonner ducks under it.
Length ball, outside off. Permaul punches it to covers.
A short ball, on middle. Permaul rides the pull and hits it to deep square leg for a single.
Length ball, around off, tucked to mid-wicket.
A length ball, outside off. Bonner drives it in the gap, through point for a single. Bonner not taking any kind of chances here.
Around off. Defended out.
Short of a length, outside off. Permaul looks to pull but toe ends his shot and the ball drops well wide of first slip.
Shorter ball, around off and Bonner defends it on the leg side.
Short ball again, around off. Bonner pushes back off the back foot.
Slightly short and outside off. Bonner cuts away straight to point.
An off spin, fuller and outside off. Bonner tries to play it late again but misses.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Finally, Nkrumah Bonner long, long defensive show is over. What an innings this is from him. 355 deliveries faced, wow! A full ball, sliding down the leg side. Bonner looks to flick but seems to miss it. An appeal for caught behind but nothing given. Lawrence convinces Root to take it upstairs and they go for it. UltraEdge shows a small spike as the ball passes the blade and the on-field decision is changed. A soft-dismissal rather to be honest but Bonner was nodding. The change of bringing Dan Lawrence just worked for Root. Worked more than wonders. His second wicket in Test cricket.
Howout: c Ben Foakes b Dan Lawrence

Commentary: A full toss, on middle. Seales watchfully blocks it.
A full ball, outside off. Veerasammy Permaul tries to guide it down but gets an outside edge to first slip where Joe Root dives to his right and takes it on a bounce. Good effort from the skipper.
Length ball, on middle. Permaul pulls it to square leg for a single.
Length ball, outside off. Seales has a poke at it but misses.
Full ball, angling on middle. Seales defends on the leg side.
Fuller and on off. Seales leans and blocks it out.
Length ball, around middle. Seales gets a straight bat down to defend.
A full ball, outside off, turning back in. Left alone.
Tossed up, on off. Permaul prods to block it.
Fuller and outside off. Permaul drives it to deep cover but denies a single. Good thinking from him.
Dan changes the angle as he comes around the wicket. Flatter and on middle. Blocked out.
Tossed up, on middle. Permaul goes back and nudges it to short leg.
A short ball, outside off. Permaul chases this widish delivery as he goes for the cut shot and misses. That will be Stumps on Day 3.
TWO BYES! West Indies are underway on Day 4! Flatter ball, outside off. Jayden Seales leaves it and the keeper fails to grab it cleanly. The batters collect a couple of byes.
Tosses it up, around off. Jayden Seales blocks it off the front foot.

OUT! LBW! That is plumb in front! Leach tosses it up, on a length, just outside off. Jayden Seales prods to defend but he misses and gets rapped on his pad as he plays down the wrong line. England appeal and the umpire agrees. Seales though, opts for a review but the Ball Tracker indicates three reds and Seales is a goner. West Indies are bowled out for 375!
Howout: lbw b Jack Leach

Commentary: Roach starts with a full ball, outside off. Alex Lees leaves it alone.
BEATEN! Roach serves another full ball, outside off, enticing the batter to drive. Lees looks to drive but the ball zips past his outside edge.
Good-length ball, around off. Lees hangs back and taps it to the off side. He scampers through to the other end. England and Lees are underway!
A length ball, around middle. Zak Crawley flicks it to mid-wicket. Not in the gap though!
A full ball, outside off. Crawley lets it through to the keeper.

NOT OUT! Zak Crawley survives and this is a smart review by the Englishman after consulting with Lees! A length ball, nipping back in from middle. Crawley gets across and looks to flick it but he misses and gets pinged on his pad. West Indies appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Crawley reviews and the Ball Tracker shows that the ball would have gone down leg. England retain their review.
A full ball, outside off. Alex Lees leaves it alone.
Good-length ball, around off. Alex Lees prods and blocks it towards cover.
Seales pitches it up, just outside off. Lees gets forward and defends it.
On a length, just outside off. Alex Lees shoulders his arms at this one.
Back of a length, angling across the batter. Alex Lees does not bother playing at it.
Full and on middle. Lees keeps it out.
Good-length ball, around off. Zak Crawley blocks it off the front foot.
This is on a length, well outside off. Zak Crawley lets it sail through.
FOUR! Easy pickings! First boundary of the innings! Roach persists with full-length stuff but strays on the pads this time. Crawley flicks it behind square on the leg side and bags a boundary.
Fuller in length, outside off. Zak Crawley leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Fuller in length, outside off. Zak Crawley looks to defend but it goes off the thick outside edge, and rolls past the gully fielder for a couple of runs.
Back of a length, well outside off. Zak Crawley lets it sail through to the keeper.
On a length, outside off. Alex Lees shoulders his arms at this one.
Good-length ball, just outside off. Alex Lees prods but does not bother playing at it.
Short of a length, outside off. Alex Lees offers no shot to that one.
Nicely played! Shorter in length, outside off. Alex Lees rides the bounce and punches it through the cover region. The batters take three runs.
Seales goes full and outside off. Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
A full ball, around leg. Zak Crawley flicks it through the mid-wicket region and the batters collect three runs.
A stifled appeal for caught behind but it clearly came off the pad. A length ball, angling down leg. Zak Crawley misses his flick and the ball brushes his pad before going to the keeper.
A full ball, outside off. Zak Crawley gets forward and drives it back to the bowler.
Fuller in length, around leg. Zak Crawley tickles it towards fine leg and takes a single.
Another full ball, way outside off. Alex Lees leaves it alone.
A length ball, angling down leg. Alex Lees misses his flick and the ball goes through to the keeper.
Good-length ball, outside off. Alex Lees leaves it alone watchfully.
Good-length ball, around off. Zak Crawley keeps it out.
FOUR! Lovely timing! A full ball, angling in from middle. Zak Crawley prods and flicks it nonchalantly through the mid-wicket region for a boundary.
Good-length ball, well outside off. Zak Crawley gets forward and lets it through to the keeper.
An overpitched ball, outside off. Crawley offers no shot and watches the ball closely.
Another ball, full and outside off. Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
Back of a length, outside off. Zak Crawley lets it sail through to the keeper.
A full ball, around off. Alex Lees prods and defends it to the off side. The batters cross ends.
Roach serves a length ball, nipping back in from off. Zak Crawley gets forward and flicks it from the inner half of his bat towards deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
On a length, around off. Zak Crawley leans and blocks it out.
Good-length delivery, just outside off. Zak Crawley prods and keeps it out.
Well bowled! This is a good-length ball, outside off and angling in late. Zak Crawley looks to defend off the front foot but he cleverly gets his bat away from the line of the ball.
A full ball, on middle. Zak Crawley gets forward and flicks it to mid-wicket.
Holder comes 'round the wicket and starts with a length ball, angling in from outside off. Alex Lees leaves it alone.
A bit fuller this time, angling in from middle. Alex Lees misses his flick and gets hit low on his pad.
Pitches it up, around the fourth stump channel. Alex Lees prods to block it out.
Much fuller this time, outside off. Alex Lees gets forward and defends it to the off side.
Back of a length, angling in from outside off. Alex Lees hangs back to flick but he misses and gets hit on his body.
Holder changes his angle and comes over the wicket this time. A length ball, around off. Lees prods and defends it.
Fuller in length, on middle and leg. Zak Crawley flicks it behind square on the leg side and comes back for the second run.
On a length, around middle. Zak Crawley prods and flicks it with soft hands, along the ground towards square leg.
BEATEN! This is a good-length delivery, just outside off. Zak Crawley has a poke at it but the ball nips away a bit and beats his outside edge.
BEAUTY! Another ball, that jags away late after pitching just outside off. Zak Crawley looks to block off the front foot but the ball zips past his outside edge. This is brilliant bowling from Roach!
Pitches it up, around off. Zak Crawley keeps it out off the front foot.
A full ball, well outside off. Zak Crawley does not bother playing at it.
A full ball, jagging back in from outside off. Alex Lees prods and lets it sail through to the keeper.
That came back in sharply! Fuller in length, nipping back in from middle. Alex Lees prods to flick it but he misses and gets hit on his front pad.
On a length, around off. Alex Lees taps it to the off side and rotates the strike.
Good-length delivery, well outside off. Zak Crawley shoulders his arms at this one.
Much fuller and around off. Zak Crawley keeps it out, off the front foot.
Holder bowls it full and outside off. Zak Crawley leaves it alone for the keeper to collect it.

OUT! LBW! West Indies get the breakthrough and Roach gets Lees LBW again in this match. Very similar wicket to the first innings. Roach comes 'round the wicket and serves a full ball, angling in around middle and leg. Alex Lees looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pad. An appeal and up goes the finger. That looked plumb but Lees thought it might go on with the angle and miss leg, so he reviews it. Bu the Ball Tracking shows three reds and Lees has to make a long walk back.
Howout: lbw b Kemar Roach

Commentary: Length ball, outside off. Left alone.
On a length, around off. Root hops and blocks it out.
Beautiful bowling from Roach! This one drifts on the pads. Root flicks it wide of mid-wicket for a single. He is off the mark.
Well outside off. Crawley with an easy leave.

NOT OUT! A fuller ball, coming in with the angle, around off. Crawley takes a step across and looks to defend but gets beaten on the inside edge and gets hit on the pad. A stifled appeal for LBW but nothing given. After plenty of thinking, Kraigg Brathwaite takes the review.
