And he has lost the review because the impact is outside off, as suggested by the Ball Tracker. So, both the team lose one review early on.
Full and way down the leg side. Root misses his flick.
Fuller and on middle, flicked to deep square leg for a single.
Length ball, angling in and shaping away of the surface. Left alone.
A length ball, slanting outside off. Zak shoulders arms to it.
A length ball, extra bounce and on middle. Crawley misses his defense and gets hit high on the pads.
This one does not bounce much. Fuller and around off. Crawley looks to push but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
A length ball, outside off. Root lets it be.
Fuller ball, angling on off. Root prods and defends.
Touch fuller and outside off. Root watchfully leaves it.
Roach goes wide of the crease and serves it fuller and around off. Root gets his down to block it.
Yet another solid block from Joe Root.
Fullish and on off. Joe lunges and dead bats it.
On middle. Defended out.
On middle, angling on a length. Crawley bunts it to deep square leg for a single.
Holder is generating extra bounce here, on a length, on middle. Root looks to defend but gets hit high on the pads.
Length ball, outside off. Root on the back foot, punches it to covers.
Slightly short and on the hips, Root tucks it to square leg for a single.
Angling on middle. Defended to mid on.
Fuller ball, drifting on middle. Root pushes it to mid on.
Length ball, outside off, good seam position and Root leaves it alone.
Fuller ball this time and outside off. Root lets it through.
Length, outside off. Root shoulders arms to it.
Fuller ball, outside off, coming late with the angle. Root leaves it.
Maiden from Seales! Outside off and Root is happy to leave it.
Leg bye! Angling on the pads. Crawley misses his flick. It goes off the pads to fine leg.
Holder is a bit disappointed! Fuller and angling down the leg side. Root flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Much better! Slants it on middle. Crawley inside the line, blocks it.
Ohh! That will hurt! A length ball, extra bounce and pace, it lands around off and nips back in sharply. Zak Crawley makes a leave but the ball comes back in and hits him near the box.
Outside off. Left alone.
FOUR! Nicely played! Short ball, on middle. Crawley stands tall and pulls it to deep square leg for a boundary.
A fuller ball, outside off, driving length much and Root creams it through covers for a brace.
Length ball, straying on the pads, nudged to deep square leg for one.
Around off. Kept out.
Full ball, outside off. Zak leaves it.
Angles a full ball, on middle, pushed to mid on.
FOUR! Short of a length, on middle. Crawley pulls it, does not time it well but hits it well wide of the fielder at deep square leg.
Starts with a fuller ball, on middle. Root whips it to deep square leg for a single.
Down the leg side. Crawley misses his flick.
On a length, outside off. Defended out.
Length ball, around off. Crawley drops it to point.
Fuller ball, on middle. Crawley drives it hard and to mid on where Kemar Roach makes a good stop.
Length and outside off. Crawley shoulders arms to that one.
Length ball, well wide outside off. Easily left.
On a driving length, outside off and coming back in, it stays very low as well. Root tries to defend but the ball goes under his bat to the keeper.
Length and on middle. Blocked out.
Length and down the leg side. Root tickles it to fine leg for a single. Too many deliveries going down the leg side.
FOUR! Pierces the gap! Fuller ball, outside off. Crawley leans and drives it hard and wide of mid off for a boundary.
Follows with a solid block on the off side.
Angles it from wide of the crease, on a good-length and on middle. Root taps it through mid-wicket for a single.
On middle, on a length. Crawley pushes it to the left of mid on for a single.
Fuller this time, on middle. Blocked out.
Alzarri goes short this time. Root is hurried as he pulls it to fine leg and takes a single. 50 up for England.
Back of a length, on middle, pulled nicely to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Full, on middle and pushes to mid on.
Slightly short and outside off. Zak Crawley rocks back and slaps it through point for a brace.
Tosses it up, around off. Crawley prods to defend but the ball goes off the outer half of the bat towards point.
FOUR! Too short and Zak Crawley makes full use of it! A half-tracker, outside off. Crawley sits back in his crease and smacks it through the cover region for a boundary.

FOUR! Cheeky from Crawley! Permaul tosses it up, around middle. Zak Crawley prods and just paddles it fine through fine leg to bag another boundary. Crawley is not allowing the spinner to settle here.
Floated, full and around off. Zak Crawley gets forward and keeps it out.
Flatter and quicker, on a length, on off. Zak Crawley leans and dabs it onto the deck. England now trail by just 3 runs.
This is on a length, around off. Joe Root blocks it off the back foot.
Full and around off. Joe Root prods and flicks it to mid-wicket.

FOUR! Edgy! A length ball, just outside off. Joe Root gets forward to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and rolls away through the slip and the gully fielder for a boundary. England lead by 1 run now!
On a length, around middle. Joe Root keeps it out.
Play and a miss! Back of a length, outside off. Joe Root hangs back and looks to cut but he misses.
Short of a length, around off. Joe Root stays back and taps it towards point. A dot to end the over!
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Zak Crawley rocks back and punches it towards cover.
Floated, on a length, around off. Zak Crawley taps it to the off side.
Tossed up, around off. Zak Crawley covers the line and defends it.
Short and outside off. Zak Crawley stays back and punches it through the cover region for a couple of runs.
Floated, full and around off. Zak Crawley blocks it.
Fuller in length, around middle. Zak Crawley prods and tucks it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Edgy! A length ball, outside off. Root looks to defend with an angled bat but gets an outside edge past the first slip and to the third man fence.
Fuller now, on middle, flicked to deep square leg for a single.
Length and on middle. Crawley tucks it to mid-wicket where Nkrumah Bonner dives to his right and stops it. He has a shy at the keeper's end but misses.
Outside off. Left alone.
A length ball, nipping in around off. Crawley defends it.
Length and on middle. Crawley blocks it solidly. England lead by 8 runs. That will be Lunch on Day 4.
Good-length ball, around off. Joe Root prods to block it.
A full ball, on middle. Joe Root gets forward and tucks it to mid-wicket.
Holder drags his length back, around off. Root stays back and defends it onto the deck.
Back of a length, angling in from outside off. Joe Root leaves it alone.
Short of a length, around middle and leg. Joe Root hangs back and nudges it around the corner for a single.
A length ball, well outside off. Zak Crawley shoulders his arms at it.
Fuller in length, on middle. Joe Root clips it to deep square leg for a run. That brings up the 50-run partnership between these two!
Fuller and outside off. Crawley shoulders arms to it.
Short of a length, around middle and leg. Zak Crawley turns it behind square on the leg side for a run.
Drop and run! Back of a length, around off. Joe Root taps it towards backward point and takes a quick single.
Joseph goes full and on middle. Zak Crawley looks to drive but it goes off the inner half of the blade towards mid-wicket.
Back of a length, around leg. Zak Crawley stays back and nudges it behind square on the leg side for a run.
A full ball, around off. Zak Crawley prods to block but it goes off the inside edge towards square leg.
Another full ball, around middle. Zak Crawley defends it off the front foot.
Full and around off. Zak Crawley drives it back to the bowler.
A short ball, outside off. Zak Crawley stays back, swivels and pulls it along the ground towards deep square leg for a single.
A length ball, angling in from middle. Joe Root flicks it towards deep square leg for one run.
No ball! Another ball, on a length, around middle. Zak Crawley clips it through mid-wicket and takes single. Jason Holder oversteps and the umpire calls it a no ball.
Good-length ball, around leg. Joe Root tucks it to mid-wicket.
Full and outside off. Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
A full ball, on middle. Zak Crawley prods and pushes it to mid on.
Swing and a miss! Back of a length, outside off. Zak Crawley throws his bat at it but he misses.
Full and outside off. Zak Crawley lets it through to the keeper.
Good-length ball, around off. Zak Crawley keeps it out.
Good-length ball, well outside off. Zak Crawley leaves it alone watchfully.
Back of a length, around off. Joe Root hangs back and dabs it onto the deck. Holder oversteps yet again and the umpire signals no ball.
Fuller in length, outside off. Joe Root drives but straight to the cover fielder.
Holder drags his length back, around off. Joe Root blocks it to the off side.
A full ball, outside off. Joe Root prods and carves it through cover-point by opening the bat face. The batters take two runs.
Back of a length, well outside off. Joe Root leaves it alone.
A full ball, around middle. Root sits back and flicks it past the mid on fielder. Veerasammy Permaul there, gives it a chase and keeps it to just two.
Another ball, on the fuller side, just outside off. Root gets forward and defends it onto the deck.
A full ball, well outside off. Zak Crawley lets it sail through to the keeper.
Good-length ball, around the fifth stump channel. Zak Crawley lets it be.
Joseph goes full and outside off. Zak Crawley does not bother playing at that one.
Back of a length, around middle. Zak Crawley defends it on the leg side.
On a length, around off. Zak Crawley sits back in his crease and blocks it.
Fuller in length, around off. Zak Crawley defends it off the front foot solidly.
A length ball, outside off. Root cuts it but straight to point.
Length again, outside off. Root cuts it wide of third man for two runs.
Length ball, outside off. Root punches off the back foot, wide of third man for a couple of runs.
Length ball, outside off. Root pushes it to the right of point for a single.
Fifty for Zak Crawley! His sixth in Test match and gets around of applause from the ground. A length ball, on  middle. Crawley tucks it to deep square leg for one.
Shorter and outside off. Root covers his stumps and lets it through.
A length ball, outside off, it nips back in and goes past the off pole very closely. Crawley shoulders arms to it.
Length and on middle, tucked to mid-wicket.
Outside off. Zak prods and lets it through.
Outside off again. Left alone.
Fuller and outside off. Crawley drives it through point for a couple of runs.
Length ball, coming in off the deck. Crawley has his stumps covered.
Around off, nudged to mid-wicket.
Pitches it up, on off. Root with a defensive push.
Angles it down on the pads, Root works it to deep square leg for one.
Well wide of off stump. Zak leaves it.
Length ball, outside off. Crawley leaves it alone and the ball dies on its way to the keeper.
Outside off. Crawley almost played at that, draws his bat back in time.
Length ball, on off. Joe stands tall and blocks it.
A yorker, on middle, flicked square on the leg side for one.
Length ball, on off. Defended.
Short of a length, on middle. Crawley is a bit late on his pull shot and misses it.
Length ball, outside off. Crawley shoulders arms.
A yorker to end the over and Root gets his bat down in time.
Length ball, angling on middle. Root dead bats it.
Touch fuller and around off. Root presses forward and defends.
Fuller and just outside off, it jags back in and Root does well to keep it out.
Length ball, outside off. Root guides it to point.
Overpitched, on middle. Root defends it on the leg side.
TWO BYES! Length and outside off. Left alone. The ball does not bounce much again but Joshua Da Silva, the keeper does well to get some fingers on it.
Length again, outside off. Easy leave for Crawley.
Joseph gets the angle here, on a length, around off. Crawley plants the front foot forward and blocks it.
Around off. Blocked out.
Outside off. Left alone.
Bangs the deck hard and keeps it outside off. Nothing for Crawley to worry about.
Short in length, on middle. Crawley pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball, 4th stump channel and Zak lets it through.
Touch fuller and outside off, in that channel again but Crawley is not tempted.
Makes Crawley work here. Length ball, on off. Blocked out. A no ball called for overstepping. 100 up for England!
A length ball, outside off. Crawley taps it wide of point but no run there.
Fuller ball, outside off, stays low and it is left alone.
Around off, on a length. Crawley prods to block it out.
FOUR! A boundary after quite a while! Fuller and on off. Crawley mistimes his drive but gets it past the diving mid on fielder for a boundary.
FOUR! Holder errs with his line. This is full and down the leg side. Root helps it away to fine leg for a boundary.
Touch fuller and on off. Root blocks it.
Fuller again, in the channel. Root strides forward and defends it.
Length, straight on middle. This is hit to deep square leg for a single.
Angles a length ball, on off. Kept out.
This is slower and around off. Crawley watchfully works it to point.
A length ball, around off. Root gets on the front foot and defends it on the deck.
Length ball, on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Full, very full and on middle. Root squeezes back to the bowler.
Length ball, outside off. Root plays with an open faced bat to point.
Plays the same line and to point again.
Fuller and outside off, pushed through point for a single. England with a lead of 46 runs.
Fuller ball, outside off. Root with a solid block on the off side.
Length and outside off. Root plays it to point.
Length ball, angling back late, around off. Root jams it out to point.
Holder changes the angle as he comes around the wicket, and spills outside off. Left alone.
Touch fuller, around off. Root drops it to point.

Very full and on middle. Root pushes it back to Holder. He gets a hand to it and deflects it across on the stumps. Crawley was inside though. Root meanwhile wants a cheeky single but Roach cuts it off.
Seales starts with a full ball, on middle. Zak Crawley clips it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Good-length delivery, around off. Joe Root blocks it off the front foot.
Extra bounce! This is a length ball, just outside off and taking off from a length. Joe Root prods to defend but it hits the shoulder of his bat and goes towards the gully fielder, on the bounce.
On a length, around off. Joe Root defends it to the off side.
Fuller in length, around the fifth stump channel. Joe Root gets to the pitch of the ball and blocks it.
Another ball, full and on off. Root sits back and drives it back past the bowler through mid on. Nkrumah Bonner gives it a chase from mid on and keeps it to two.
Tosses it up, outside off. Zak Crawley pushes it wide of the cover fielder for a single.
A loopy ball, full and on middle. Root drills it back to the bowler.
Floated, on a length and going on with the arm, from middle. Joe Root taps it towards point and settles for a single.

Good tag team effort from Alzarri Joseph and Jason Holder! This is a full ball, outside off. Zak Crawley drives it past mid off. Joseph gives it a chase and dives just in front of the ropes to keep the ball in play. The ball though goes towards the ropes but Holder runs across from long on and pushes it back in play. The batters collect three runs.
Tossed up, around off. Joe Root keeps it out.
A loopy ball, on middle. Joe Root prods and blocks it.
A full ball, outside off. Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery, around off. Zak Crawley defends it to the off side.
Back of a length, angling in from outside off. Zak Crawley lets it be.
Back of a length, just outside off. Zak Crawley dabs it onto the deck.
FOUR! Lovely timing and even better placement from Crawley! This is a full ball, angling in from middle. Zak Crawley gets forward and flicks it past the mid on fielder for a boundary.
A full ball, around off. Zak Crawley looks to drive but it goes off the inner half of the bat towards mid on.
Tossed up, around middle. Joe Root keeps it out.
Slower through the air, on middle. Joe Root prods and dabs it onto the surface.
A bit flatter, around middle. Joe Root rocks back and nudges it around the corner for a single.
An overpitched ball, on middle. Zak Crawley drags it towards long on for a run. That brings up the 100-run partnership between Root and Crawley!
Tossed up, around middle. Root blocks it.
Much slower through the air, around off. Root defends it with ease.
A length ball, around middle and leg. Zak Crawley flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller in length, on middle. Joe Root flicks it through the mid-wicket region for a brace.
Good-length ball, angling in from off. Root gets forward, covers the line and blocks it.
A full ball, outside off. Joe Root lets it through to the keeper.
Back of a length, outside off. Joe Root hangs back and cuts but straight to the point fielder.
Shorter in length and nipping back in from off. Joe Root stays back and defends it onto the deck.
Tosses it up, around middle. Zak Crawley blocks it off the front foot.
Slower through the air, full and on off. Zak Crawley gets to the pitch of the ball and defends it.
Floated, full and on off. Zak Crawley leans and keeps it out.
Another loopy ball, full and on middle. Zak Crawley dabs it onto the deck.
Floated, full and darted on the pads. Zak Crawley flicks it to mid-wicket. Not in the gap though!
Tossed up, down leg. Zak Crawley reaches out, kneels and sweeps it behind square on the leg side without much timing for a couple of runs.

FOUR! Permaul starts poorly yet again! FIFTY for Root! His 54th Test half-century! Short and outside off. Root stays back and slaps it behind square on the off side. The ball races away to the fence. England's skipper is leading from the front here!
Flatter and quicker, on middle. Root flicks it to the leg side for a run.
Flatter ball, on a length, around off. Zak Crawley rocks back and punches it to long off for a single.
Floated, full and on off. Joe Root keeps it out.
Another ball, short and outside off. Joe Root punches it through covers and takes a run.

NOT OUT! Zak Crawley survives! This is a full ball, around middle and leg. Crawley looks to play it across the line but he gets an inside edge and the ball ricochets off his boot, onto the pad and then lobs up towards the first slip fielder who grabs it. West Indies appeal but the umpire is not sure and he refers it upstairs. The replays roll in and it shows that the ball bounced off the surface after hitting the inside edge and then went on to hit the boot of Crawley. West Indies players aren't happy with the decision though!
Fuller and on middle. Blocked out.
Flighted full and on middle. Root reverse sweeps it to third man for a single.
Tossed up, on middle. Kept out.
An appeal for LBW but not given, pitching outside leg precisely. Fuller, flighted and around leg. Zak Crawley misses his reverse sweep and gets hit on the pads.
FOUR! Shorter and outside off. Crawley cuts it hard and to point for a boundary.
Floated, full and on off. Defended.
Flatter and on middle. Root on the back foot, nudges it to square leg for one.
FOUR! Permaul is going for easy runs! Shorter and outside off. Crawley cuts it past point for a boundary.
Tossed up, full and coming with the angle. Zak prods to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Around off, pushed to point.
Tossed up, full and on middle, pushed to mid-wicket.
Floated, full and on middle. Crawley presses forward to block it. That will be Tea on Day 4.
Joseph starts with a length ball, outside off. Joe Root leaves it alone.
Back of a length, around off. Root hangs back and blocks it solidly onto the deck.
Joseph bends his back and serves a bumper, around off. Root swivels and pulls it along the ground towards deep square leg for a single.
Fuller in length, outside off. Zak Crawley lets it through to the keeper.
A length ball, drifting onto the pads. Zak Crawley misses his flick and the ball brushes off his pad before going to the left of the keeper. Joshua Da Silva dives there and stops it cleanly.
Good-length delivery, around middle. Zak Crawley flicks it to deep mid-wicket and comes back for the second run.
Permaul starts with a full toss, around off. Root drags it wide of mid on and takes a single.
FOUR! Veerasammy Permaul continues to struggle with his line and length! This is a full ball, down leg. Zak Crawley gets down on his knee and sweeps it through the fine leg region to bag a boundary.
Flatter ball, on a length, around middle. Zak Crawley blocks it off the back foot.
A length ball, darted on the pads. Zak Crawley tucks it around the corner and takes off for a quick run.

FOUR! Drops it a bit short this time and Root is too good a player to miss out on a scoring opportunity! Flatter and quicker, outside off. Root stays back and cuts it past the backward point fielder for a boundary.
Flatter ball, on middle. Root nudges it to the leg side and takes a run. He will retain the strike.
A length ball, around middle. Joe Root tucks it around the corner and rotates the strike.
A short ball, around off. Zak Crawley mistimes his pull towards the mid on fielder, along the ground.
A full ball, outside off. Zak Crawley leaves it alone.
FOUR! Streaky! A full ball, outside off and enticing the batter to drive. Zak Crawley throws his bat at it and the ball goes well over the slip cordon for a boundary.
FOUR! SMASHED! Short and wide, outside off. Zak Crawley stays back and slaps it through the point region to bag another boundary. He moves on to 94 now!
On a length, around off. Zak Crawley dabs it onto the deck.
FOUR! England have just put a shift to the gears! Tossed up, on middle. Root gets low and sweeps it to square leg for a boundary.
Shorter and outside off. Root pushes off the back foot to point.
Fuller and around off. Root paddles it to fine leg for a single. A 150-run stand between these two.
Tossed up, on off. Crawley lunges and blocks it out.
Tossed up, on middle. Defended out.
Fuller and on middle. Zak keeps it out.
Length ball, outside off, hint of inswing. Root covers his stump and lets it through.
Fuller ball, outside off, skidding through and stays low while coming back in. Root misses his push.
Touch fuller and on off. Root mistimes his push back to the bowler.
On middle. Root pushes it nicely, straight back but Joseph blocks it with his boots.
Length ball, outside off, stays low again. Root misses his cut.
Good over from Alzarri Joseph! A length ball, on off. Blocked on the off side. A maiden!
Tossed up, full and coming with the angle. Defended out.
Flatter and on middle, tucked to square leg for one.
An arm ball, on middle. Root dead bats it.
Fuller and on off. Joe caresses it through covers for a single.
A slider, outside off. Crawley misses his cut.
On off, Blocked out.
Length ball, around off. Root drops it in front of point for a single.
On middle, on a length and drilled to mid on.
Leg bye! A full ball, angling on the pads. Crawley misses his flick and gets hit on the pads. An appeal but that was slanting way down. A leg bye taken in the process.
Short of a length, outside off and extra bounce there as well. Root defends away from the body and it takes an outside edge to gully where the fielder collects it on a bounce.
Full and on off, pushed to mid off.
Around off, on a length. Blocked out.
Fuller and outside off. Crawley leans and drives it to deep cover for a single. He moves to 96 now.
Tossed up, on middle. Root leans and defends it.
Tossed up, around off. Root comes down the track and looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads
On middle. Defended solidly.
Tossed up, on middle, swept to fine leg for a single.
Slightly short, outside off. Crawley punches it to deep point for a single.
Fuller and slanting on the pads, flicked to deep square leg for a single. Crawley moves to 98 now.
Around off. Root plays it to point for one more.
Short in length, outside off. Crawley misses his pull. Another ball which stays a bit low.

Century for Zak Crawley! Gets a big hug from the skipper! His second in Test cricket. What a knock this has been from the youngster! A much-needed one for his form as well. This is full and on middle, whipped through mid-wicket for a couple of runs. He gets a round of applause from his teammates as well as the Barmy Army.
Length and on off. Defended out.
Another length ball, on off. Blocked out.
An appeal for LBW but not given! Tossed up, fuller and on middle. Root comes down the track and looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. Windies appeal but nothing from the umpire.
Shorter and outside off. Kept out.
On middle, hit to mid-wicket.
Floated, full and on middle. Root sweeps it to fine leg for a single.
Tossed up, on off. Crawley prods and blocks it out.
On middle. Crawley plays it to deep square leg for a brace.
Short in length, on middle. Root pulls it well along the ground to square leg for one.
Short ball now, angling on leg. Crawley lets it through.
Another short ball and it is left alone.
FOUR! A fuller ball, down on the pads. Crawley flicks it, there is a leg gully but he hits it wide of the fielder there for a boundary.
Shorter and on middle. Crawley hooks it wide of deep square leg for a brace.
Short of a length, on middle. Crawley miscues his pull and gets hit on the gloves. The ball drops dead on the deck. England lead by 131 runs now.
Flatter and quicker, on off. Root stays back and pushes it through covers for a run.
Tosses it up, around off. Zak Crawley blocks it off the front foot.
A bit quicker, around off. Zak Crawley hangs back and punches it to cover.
Slightly shorter in length, outside off. Zak Crawley slaps it through cover-point and takes a single.
Another ball, quicker and shorter in length, outside off. Joe Root hangs back and taps it to point for a run.
Flatter and quicker, around off. Zak Crawley keeps it out.
Seales comes 'round the wicket and serves a short ball, around leg. Joe Root swivels and pulls it towards fine leg for a single.
Bye! Back of a length, down leg. Zak Crawley misses his pull shot and the keeper fails to grab the ball cleanly. The batters collect a bye. 200 comes up for England!
A bumper, around leg. Root shuffles across and pulls it along the ground towards deep square leg for a run.

FOUR! Just wide of the keeper! Shorter in length, down leg. Zak Crawley looks to help it on its way towards fine leg but he only a gets a tickle to the left of the keeper. Joshua Da Silva dives there but the ball goes past him for a boundary.
A short ball, on middle. Zak Crawley pulls it to deep square leg for a brace.
A bumper, around off. Zak Crawley mistimes his pull towards mid-wicket.
Back of a length, around off. Joe Root hangs back and guides it straight to the man at gully.
On a length, outside off. Joe Root taps it towards extra cover.
Back of a length, outside off. Joe Root stays back and cuts it to through the point region for a couple of runs.
Play and a miss! Short of a length, outside off. Joe Root looks to cut hard but he misses.
Good-length ball, around off. Joe Root defends it towards cover.
This is a length ball, outside off. Joe Root stays back and pushes it through covers for a couple of runs,
Flatter ball, on middle and leg. Zak Crawley nudges it behind square on the leg side for a single.
No Ball! Flatter ball, on middle. Joe Root nudges it around the corner and takes a single. No ball called as Bonner has overstepped.
No Ball! Tosses it up, on middle. Crawley prods to defend but it goes off the inside edge towards deep square leg for a run. Another no ball as Bonner oversteps yet again.
Slower through the air, well outside off. Joe Root pushes it to the off side and takes a single.
NO BALL! Nkrumah Bonner oversteps on the first ball of the day! A flatter and shorter delivery on off. Zak Crawley pushes it to covers.
This is fuller and outside off. Zak Crawley looks to drive but gets the bottom of his blade.
A fullish delivery, outside off. Zak Crawley lets it go.
This is again full, on off. Zak Crawley drives it to covers this time.
Slightly shorter and on off. Zak Crawley goes back and punches it to long off for a single.
On a length, around off. Zak Crawley gets forward and blocks it towards the off side.

Direct hit and Zak Crawley would have been back to the dressiong room! A full delivery on middle. Zak Crawley drives it to mid on and sets off for a quick single. The fielder there collects the ball and has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. A single in the end.
A full delivery, on off. Root drives it to covers this time.
Another fullish delivery, on off. Root is well forward again and pushes it towards the off side.
A length delivery, around off. Root defends it towards the point fielder this time.
A fullish delivery, on off. Root drives it to covers this time. Tidy over to start by Roach.
Starts with a full delivery, on off. Zak Crawley drives it to mid off.

NOT OUT! Huge shout but Zak Crawley was way out of his crease there! A length delivery on middle and leg. Zak Crawley skips down the track and looks to flick it but misses. The ball hits his pads and there is an appeal but the umpire is not interested. Windies skipper, though, decides to take a review. Th replays roll in and the Ball Tracker shows that the ball is missing stumps. So the decision stays and Zak Crawley will continue.
A length delivery on middle. Zak Crawley blocks it out.
A length delivery on middle and leg this time. Zak Crawley works this past square leg for a single now.
A length delivery, on off at 128 kph. Root blocks it out towards the off side.
On a length, on middle and this one nips back in a little. Root looks to work it away but gets the inside edge onto this pads. The ball rolls towards square leg and a single is taken.
Goes fuller on off. Root uses his wrists and works it towards mid-wicket.
Another full delivery, on off. Root steers it towards backward point this time.
Overpitched on off. Root drives it to mid on and calls no immediately. There is a slight misfield but no run taken.
Roach goes full again but wider outside off. Root drives it to deep point for a single.
Slower delivery this time. Full and on off. Zak Crawley looks to drive but gets the inside edge onto his pads.
A length delivery, outside off. Zak Crawley slaps it towards sweeper cover for just a single.
NO BALL! A full delivery on middle and leg. Zak Crawley looks to drive it but gets the inside edge onto his pads again. Holder has overstepped this time.
Another inside edge! A length delivery, on off. Zak Crawley looks to push it away off the front foot but gets the inside edge onto his pads.

OUT! BOWLED! What a delivery by Jason Holder! He takes the pitch out of the equation this time and nails a perfect yorker! Not much the batter can do with it and Zak Crawley walks back after a brilliant innings. This is pacy and a yorker-length delivery on off. Zak Crawley looks to dig it out but misses. The ball shatters the off pole and a wicket for Windies early in the day.
Howout: b Jason Holder

Commentary: A good-length delivery, on off. Dan Lawrence defends it towards the off side.
This time drifting on the pads. Dan Lawrence works it towards fine leg for a single.
A slower length delivery, outside off. Root takes a step or two forward and defends it towards the off side.
Back of a length, on middle. Root works it towards fine leg for a single.
This is full on middle. Root leans forward and drives it to mid on.
A length delivery, outside off and slower in pace at 110 kph. Root steers it toward deep backward point for a couple.
Ohh...very full on middle this time. Root digs it out towards mid-wicket.
Another couple of runs! A length delivery, outside off. Root square drives it to deep point and comes back for the second run. He is into the 90s now.
Provides the width again, outside off. Root pushes it towards covers for a single.
A length delivery, on middle. Dan Lawrence works it towards mid-wicket and gets a single.
FOUR! Ohh..some intent from Dan Lawrence! A length delivery, around off. Dan Lawrence skips down the track and gives himself some room. He then slams it over extra-cover for a boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Dan Lawrence pushes it towards the off side and takes a quick single this time.
This is fuller on middle. Root flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
A fuller delivery, on leg. Dan Lawrence works it towards mid-wicket for a single. Holder is not happy with the fielder there.
A slower fuller delivery, on middle. Root nudges it towards fine leg for a single.
Excellent running again! A length delivery on middle end leg. Dan Lawrence makes room and pushes it towards mid on for a quick single.
Dan Lawrence walks across towards the off side. Alzarri Joseph serves this wider outside off. Dan Lawrence looks to get a bat on it but misses.
This is short and outside off. Dan Lawrence cuts it to deep extra-cover and take three runs.
Full and wider outside off. Root goes chasing for it but gets beaten.
A length delivery, outside off again. Root cuts it without much timing towards backward point for a single.
NO BALL! Very full and down the leg side. Dan Lawrence walks across again and looks to flick it but misses. Alzarri Joseph has overstepped there.
WIDE! This is full and outside off. Dan Lawrence looks to get a bat on it but misses.
A length ball, outside off. Dan Lawrence cuts it to deep cover for a single.
A length delivery, on off. Root pushes it towards the off side.
This one is full and down the leg side. Dan Lawrence skips down the track and looks to flick it but misses.
On a length, on off. Dan Lawrence blocks it towards the off side.
Goes fuller this time on off. Dan Lawrence drives it to covers.
SIX! Ohh...a maximum now! So England are going for it! A length delivery on middle.  Dan Lawrence makes room and tonks it over long off for a maximum.
A length delivery on middle. Dan Lawrence looks to work it towards the leg side but gets a leading edge towards the off side.
Back of a length, on middle. Dan Lawrence skips down the track and heaves it towards mid-wicket.
Overpitched on off. Root drives it to deep extra-cover and gets a couple.
FOUR BYES! A wayward delivery this! A full toss down the leg side. Root looks to flick it but misses. Joshua Da Silva dives to his left to stop it but fails and the ball races away towards the fence.
A length delivery, on off. Root pushes it towards covers.
Slightly fuller on off this time. Root pushes it towards deep cover for a single.
A length delivery, around off. Dan Lawrence makes room and throws his bat at that. The ball goes towards the third man region for a single.
A length delivery, on off. Root drives it back to the bowler.
The lead is now 200! A length delivery, on middle. Dan Lawrence gets across and works it towards fine leg for a single.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Root works it right of square leg for another single.
Back of a length, on leg. Dan Lawrence makes room and mistimes his cut shot towards the off side.
Back of a length, on middle. Dan Lawrence works it towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! So runs are flowing now for England! Back of a length, on middle. Dan Lawrence makes room and slams it over extra-cover for a boundary.
Back of a length, around off. Dan Lawrence works it towards the leg side.
A length delivery, on off. Root drives it to covers this time.

Century for Root! What a player this man is! It doesn’t matter whether he bats at number 4 or number 3, he continues to shine with the bat. This one is full and outside off. Root squeezes it to deep point for a single. He will look to step on the gas now!
A length delivery, around off. Dan Lawrence looks to heave it away across the line but gets the inside edge onto his pads.
A length delivery, outside off. Dan Lawrence gets across and looks to work it towards the leg side. He gets the leading edge towards the off side.
A length delivery, on off. Dan Lawrence makes room and lifts it towards long off. The ball falls short of the fielder there and a single is taken.
WIDE! A length delivery and a tad too wide outside off. Root goes chasing for it but misses.
A length delivery, outside off and this one nips back in. Root looks to drive but gets beaten off the inside edge of his blade.
FOUR! Veerasammy Permaul is greeted with a boundary! A flatter delivery on leg. Dan Lawrence reverse-sweeps it through backward point region for a boundary. Fifty partnership up.
Fuller and tossed up down the leg side. Dan Lawrence looks to sweep it but misses.
Flatter on leg this time. Dan Lawrence looks to sweep again but misses. The ball hits his pads and a leg bye is take towards square leg.
Down the leg side. Root looks to sweep but does not make any contact.
Fuller delivery on middle and leg. This time Root sweeps it to fine leg for a single.
Another delivery on leg stump. Dan Lawrence sweeps it to fine leg for another single.
A full delivery, outside off. Dan Lawrence gets across and goes for a helicopter shot. The ball goes towards mid on pocket for a single.
A length delivery on middle and leg. Root looks to reverse-sccoop it but gets the inside edge onto his body for a single towards the leg side. There is a stifled appeal but nothing more.
A perfect yorker this time on off. Dan Lawrence just about manages to dig it out.
A length delivery and wider outside off. Dan Lawrence gets across and hits it to long on for a single.
Very full on off and a hint of reverse-swing there. Root looks to clip it away but gets the inside ede onto his pads.
A full delivery, outside off. Root drives it to deep point for a single.
A fuller delivery on leg stump. Root looks to sweep it but misses and the ball hits his pads.

FOUR BYES! This time the ball beats everyone! This is full and down the leg side. Root tries to sweep it but misses. Joshua Da Silva behind the stumps misses it too and the ball races away towards the fence.
Continues with the same leg stump line. Root sweeps fine towards long leg for a couple.
Slightly shorter on middle this time. Root goes back and works it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Slower in the air and around leg again. Dan Lawrence makes room and defends it.
FOUR! Good shot this time! A fuller delivery on leg. Dan Lawrence makes room and lifts this inside-out towards deep extra-cover for a boundary.
Goes full on off. Root drives it to covers.
A very full delivery, around off. Root gets the inside half of his blade as he looks to hit it away. The ball goes towards square leg for a single.

OUT! TAKEN! Soft, soft dismissal for Dan Lawrence! A handy cameo comes to an end. This is full and outside off. Dan Lawrence looks to drive it towards the off side and opens the face of his blade a little. However, he finds Veerasammy Permaul at point and he takes an easy catch. He has surely given a good boost to this English innings.
Howout: c Veerasammy Permaul b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary: FOUR! An edge first up for Stokes but a boundary to start for him. A good-length delivery around off and angling across. Stokes pushes at it but gets a thick outside edge. The ball flies towards the third man region for a boudary.
Back of a length, around off. Stokes pushes it towards point.
300 up for England and lead is now 236! A length delivery, around off. Stokes pushes it towards deep cover for a single.
This one is slower on off from 'round the wicket. Stokes works it towards mid on for a single.
Full delivery on middle. Root tucks it towards backward square leg for a single. A bit of mix-up there between the fielders but extra run not taken.
A length delivery, on off. Stokes tries to heave it away but gets the inside half of his blade to fine leg for a single.
A short delivery on middle this time. Root pulls uppishly this time but short of the fine leg fielder for a single.
A slower length delivery, on off. Stokes works it towards the leg side for a quick single.
This is full and down the leg side. Root looks to clip it away but misses.

FOUR! Second new ball is available now but Windies have not taken it and Stokes starts the over with a boundary! A low full toss, on off. Stokes makes room and plays it inside-out overs covers for a boundary.
This is full and down the leg side. Stokes lets it go.
On the pads this time. Stokes looks to work it towards the leg side but misses. The ball hits his pads and a leg bye is taken towards the leg side.

OUT! KNOCKED HIM OVER! So Root departs now while trying to up the ante. Credit should also go to Alzarri Joseph, he has been very proactive with his bowling today. He sees Root getting across here and serves this very full on middle and leg. Root misses and the ball shatters the stumps. So Windies are chipping in with wickets and with lead now 246 batters will continue to keep going here. End of another supern knock by the English skipper, truly deserves all the applauds.
Howout: b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary: A length delivery, on middle. Jonny Bairstow works it to square leg for a single.
Back of a length, on leg. Stokes works it to fine leg for a single.
A length delivery, around off from 'round the wicket. Stokes slashes hard at it but misses.
Back of a length, around off. Stokes skips down the track and hits it to covers.

OUT! CAUGHT! Stokes departs now and this has been an entertaing morning with wickets and runs both plenty on offer. A length delivery, around off. Stokes dances down the track and looks to go big downtown. However, he miscues it. The ball goes in the air towards long off and Shamarh Brooks there runs slightly forward and takes an easy catch.
Howout: c Shamarh Brooks b Kemar Roach

Commentary: On a length, on middle. Jonny Bairstow works it to deep square leg for a single.
A length delivery on middle and leg. Foakes works it to fine leg for a single.

A very full delivery, outside off. Bairstow digs it out to gully and looks for a single but is sent back. The fielder there fires a direct hit at the batter's end but Jonny Bairstow is back into his crease as the replays confirm it.

OUT! CHOPPED ON! Another one bites the dust! Alzarri Joseph gets his third wicket! A length delivery, around off. Foakes looks to drive it towards the off side but gets the inside edge of his blade. The ball shatters the stumps and England lose their sixth wicket. England have got good anount of runs in their kitty but they need to be careful here. The lead is 250 now.
Howout: b Alzarri Joseph

Commentary: Beaten! A good-length delivery, around off. Woakes looks to defend it but the ball seams away and beats the outside edge of his blade.
A length delivery on middle. Chris Woakes works it towards deep backward square leg for a single.
A fullish delivery, on off. Jonny Bairstow blocks it out.
A length delivery, outside off. Jonny Bairstow steers it towards third man for a single.
A length delivery, outside off. Woakes lets it go this time.
A full delivery on leg. Bairstow flicks it to fine leg for a single.
A fullish delivery, on off. Woakes drives it back to the bowler.
A full delivery on middle. Woakes works it towards the deep mid-wicket region for a couple.
Drifting on the pads again. Fuller this time. Woakes flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Goes shorter this time, around leg. Bairstow works it towards deep backward square leg for a single.
On a length, on middle and leg. Woakes pushes it towards mid on for a single.
Back of a length, on off. Woakes pushes it towards covers for a single.

FOUR BYES! This is fuller and down the leg side. Jonny Bairstow looks to clip it away but misses. The ball goes left of Joshua Da Silva who has no chance to stop this one. It races away towards the fence.
A length delivery, on off. Bairstow defends it towards the off side.
This time fuller and outside off. Bairstow squeezes it to backward point.
A length ball, on off. Bairstow pushes it to covers.
Fuller and down the leg side this time. Jonny Bairstow looks to flick it but misses.

NOT OUT! Back of a length, around leg. Woakes looks to pull it but misses. The ball is close the the glove and Windies appeal. The umpire though is not interested. West Indies take a review. The replays roll in and the UltraEdge confirms there is no edge. So Woakes will continue.
A length delivery on middle. Woakes pulls it to fine leg for a single.
A fuller delivery on middle. Bairstow punches it to long on.
A length delivery on middle. Woakes works it towards deep square leg for a single.
Shorter delivery, around off. Bairstow tries to pull this. He gets the inside edge past stumps towards fine leg for a couple.
A length delivery on middle. Jonny Bairstow works it towards the leg side,
Back of a length, on off. Woakes pulls it to long on for a single.
A length delivery, on off. Bairstow gets the inside edge of his blade onto the pads as he looks to work it away.
Slightly shorter on middle. Woakes pulls it to fine leg for a single.
A length delivery, on off. Bairstow blocks it out.
Another length delivery, around off. Jonny Bairstow pushes it to deep cover for a single.
A length delivery on off. Woakes punches it to long on for a single.
FOUR! Good shot this time! A fullish delivery on middle and leg. Woakes clips it fine towards long leg for a boundary.
This time it is fuller on middle. Woakes works it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
A length delivery, on middle. Bairstow blocks it out.
Goes fuller on off. Bairstow drives it to long off for a single.
This time it is full again but on middle. Woakes works it towards mid-wicket.
A length delivery, on off. Woakes makes room and pushes it to long off for a single.
This time full on middle. Woakes makes room and drills it to long on for a single.
FOUR! Short delivery this time and it provides a boundary! A short delivery on middle. Bairstow pulls it fine towards long leg for a boundary.
Starts with a wayward delivery! A length delivery and down the leg side. Kraigg Brathwaite looks to clip it but misses.
Drifting on the pads this time. A length delivery on middle and leg. Kraigg Brathwaite works it through mid-wicket and gets three runs. Windies and their skipper are underway!
Back of a length, around leg. John Campbell works it towards backward square leg for a single.
A good-length delivery and outside off. A bit of away movement there and Kraigg Brathwaite leaves it alone.
On a length, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite clips it towards mid-wicket.
Back of a length, on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite works it to square leg this time.
A quicker delivery on off and turning into John Campbell. He works it towards the leg side.
A bit fuller this time on off. John Campbell defends it towards the off side.
Quicker and flatter this time on middle. John Campbell blocks it out.
On middle and leg and turning into John Campbell. He works it towards backward square leg this time.
Huge appeal but not given! A nicely tossed up delivery, around off. John Campbell pushes forward to defend but gets hit on the pads. An appeal there but the impact is outside off.
A flatter and quicker delivery on middle. John Campbell blocks it out.
Fullish delivery on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite plays it back to Chris Woakes.
Again fuller on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite drives it to mid on this time.
A good-length delivery, outside off. This one holds on its line and beats the outside edge of Kraigg Brathwaite's blade as he looks to defend.
A full delivery and down the leg side. Kraigg Brathwaite looks to clip it but misses.
A good-length delivery, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite solidly blocks it out.
Another good-length delivery on that off stump line. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it comfortably. Another maiden over.
A quicker and fuller delivery on off. John Campbell blocks this off the front foot.
On middle and fuller again. John Campbell defends it out nicely again.
Pushed quicker on off. John Campbell blocks it out.
Another one darted on middle and off. John Campbell is solid in his defence.
Slightly shorter and quicker again, on off. John Campbell goes back and blocks it out.
Tossed up nicely on off this time. John Campbell gets forward and blocks this off the front foot. Safely negotiated. That will be Lunch on Day 5.
Woakes starts off with a length ball, around middle and leg and swinging down the leg side.

An appeal from the keeper but no one else is interested. Woakes tries to attack the pads but serves it down the leg side yet again. Brathwaite looks to flick but the ball just brushes the pads on it way to the keeper. Ben Foakes takes a nice grab down to his left.
Fuller this time, angled into the pads. Brathwaite keeps it out on the leg side.
On a good length, around off. Brathwaite taps it towards covers.
Length again and there's a bit of width on offer this time. Kraigg Brathwaite hangs back and punches it off the back foot through point for a single.
Woakes comes around the wicket to the left-hander and serves a full ball, well outside off. This one swings away and Campbell makes an easy leave.
This is pushed through on middle. Brathwaite pushes it towards mid on.
On middle again, flicked away towards mid on.
A bit of flight this time from Leach, bowls it on off. Brathwaite strides out to defend.
Quicker and flatter, angling into middle. Brathwaite keeps it out.
Nicely drifted into middle and leg, turning away a bit. Brathwaite defends it off the front foot.
On a length, on middle. Brathwaite with a front foot punch this time towards mid on.
Full and angled into off stump. Campbell puts out a big stride forward to defend.
Leg bye! A length ball, angled on the pads. John Campbell looks to tuck it away but the ball goes off his pads towards backward square leg. Stifled appeal from Woakes but the batters get a leg bye.
Positive shot from Brathwaite! Back of a length, on off. This is firmly punched through covers for a couple of runs.
This is bowled into the channel around off. Brathwaite watches it all the way through and leaves it alone.
Around the top of off, punched past mid off by Brathwaite. Ben Stokes gives chase and keeps it down to just a single this time.
Pitched up, outside off. Campbell shoulders arms to that one.
A nice bit of drift into middle and leg, slower through the air as well. Brathwaite defends it out.
Fuller and on the pads, Brathwaite clips it off his legs and picks up a couple of runs through square leg.
On off. Solidly blocked out.
Good running! Pushed through on middle, Brathwaite uses his feet and heaves it off the inside half of the bat towards wide mid on and sets off for a quick single.
John Campbell looking to be a bit aggressive now. On middle, Campbell steps out and pushes it back to the bowler.

DROPPED! A difficult chance but once Zak Crawley gets there, he should be holding on to that one. Tossed up, outside off. John Campbell looks for the slog-sweep across the line and ends up getting a top edge. The ball loops up over first slip. Crawley swirls around, turns and stretches but puts it down. Single taken.
Fullish delivery, around off. Left alone.
Around the top of off, kept out towards point.
Short this time, on the body. This is pulled through mid-wicket for a single.
Overton hits the length hard and bowls it over off stump. Brathwaite hops back to defend.
Full and straight, Brathwaite looks to present a dead bat at it but the ball just holds into the surface, taking him by surprise.
Even fuller this time, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite jams it out to the cover region.
This is darted in from outside off. Campbell walks across and flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Around off, Campbell presses forward and just bunts it out on the off side. The batters sneak in a single as well.
On middle, Brathwaite with a big stride forward to make the block.
Shorter this time, on off. Brathwaite goes on the back foot and defends it back onto the deck.

FOUR! Risky but effective! Around middle and leg, Kraigg Brathwaite goes against the spin and takes on the man at mid on. Brathwaite clears him with ease and picks up the first boundary of this innings.
Just held back a touch by Leach and bowled on off. Brathwaite defends it out.
Full, close to the off pole and looking to skid the ball through the defense. Campbell manages to get some bat on it.
Pitched up, around off. Campbell pushes it out on the off side.
This is angled into middle. John Campbell presses forward and defends it out with soft hands.
A short ball, around the hips. Campbell hops and plays a controlled pull shot along the ground towards deep square leg. He picks up a single.
Full and straight, this is nicely worked through mid-wicket for one more.
Angled in from outside off but moves away late. John Campbell makes a watchful leave.

FOUR! The skipper is taking on Jack Leach here. Fuller, darted into middle. Kraigg Brathwaite goes through with the shot and with a little bit of help from the wind, clears Ben Stokes at mid off with ease. Another boundary for him.
Around middle and leg. Blocked out.
This is drifted into leg stump, Brathwaite dabs it down towards shirt leg.
Slower through the air, around off. Brathwaite stays solid in defense.
Quicker one, on middle and sliding on with the angle. Brathwaite defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up and this is pushed straight towards silly mid on.
A length ball, around off. Campbell nudges it down towards backward point.
A well-directed bouncer now, around off and at a good height. John Campbell does well to get his head away from the line of the ball.
Good-length ball, on middle. Campbell blocks it out.
Length again, around off. Campbell plays it with an angled bat and towards backward point.
Overton comes from over the wicket and angles it across the off stump. Campbell leaves it alone.
Short again, on the body. Campbell hops and keeps it down towards mid-wicket and strolls across for a single as well.
On off, pushed towards mid off.
Flatter, on off. Defended off the back foot by Campbell.
Tossed up, well outside off and on a rough patch. This one seems to be turning in quite a fair bit and John Campbell skips down the track. The ball comes off his pads and rolls onto the off side.
On middle and leg, tucked away to square leg.
Tossed up, on middle. Campbell defends it under the eyeline.
On middle again, John Campbell uses his feet to push it towards mid on and scampers through for a quick single.
On a good length, angling into middle and leg. Campbell nudges it towards mid-wicket and turns the strike over.
A bouncer now, over middle and this one doesn't rise up much. Brathwaite ducks under it.
Around the top of off, Brathwaite hops back to block it out.
This is shorter and angled on the body. Kraigg Brathwaite swivel-pulls it to deep backward square leg for a single.
Length, on off and this is pushed out towards covers.
Fuller this time, on off. Campbell stays solid in defense.
Ohh...that was close! A good-length delivery, around off and this one nips into Kraigg Brathwaite a little. He decides to leave it alone and the ball goes just past the off pole.

This time drifting on the pads. Kraigg Brathwaite looks to clip it but misses. The ball hits his pads and there is a stifled appeal there. However, the umpire is not interested and the batters run a leg bye towards the fine leg.
A good-length delivery, outside off. John Campbell leaves it alone.
Another delivery on that good length and outside off. John Campbell lets it go.
This time angling into middle and leg. John Campbell clips it through mid-wicket and comes back for the second run.
In that channel around off and seaming away a tad this time. John Campbell leaves it alone watchfully.
On a length, on middle and this time a bit of extra bounce. Kraigg Brathwaite looks to work it towards the leg side but gets hit on his gloves and a single is taken towards the leg side.
A good-length delivery, outside off. John Campbell leaves it alone.
Another delivery on that good length and outside off. John Campbell lets it go again.
This time it is fuller on middle. John Campbell is quick to get his bat down and pushes it to covers.
Back of a length, around off. John Campbell rides the bounce and punches it to covers.
On the shorter side again, this time angling into middle and leg. John Campbell pulls it to deep backward square leg for a single.
A length delivery, on off. John Campbell drives it to mid on this time.
Goes fuller on off. John Campbell drives it back to the bowler.
On a length and angling into middle. John Campbell clips it to deep square leg for a single.
This time a length delivery on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it towards short mid-wicket.
Slightly shorter this time, outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite cuts it to point. Alex Lees moves to his left and tries to stop it but the ball goes through him and the batters take three.
Back of a length, on middle. John Campbell blocks it out solidly.

What on earth is that! A quicker delivery on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite strangely goes for a wild swing across the line but misses it completely. Luckily for him, the ball goes over the stumps back to the keeper.
Shorter and quicker again outside off. Kraigg Brathwaite looks to cut it but misses.
Slower in the air, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite gets forward and blocks it out.
A flatter delivery on off. Kraigg Brathwaite punches it to covers this time.
Tossed up nicely on off this time. Kraigg Brathwaite gets well forward and defends it.
FOUR! Nicely played this time. On the pads and Kraigg Brathwaite leans forward and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Slightly shorter and flatter around off. John Campbell cuts it through cover-point for a single.
A flatter delivery on off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out.
Goes quicker and flatter on off. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it out off the front foot yet again.

An appeal for stumping but Kraigg Brathwaite is well in there and the umpire doesn't even send it upstairs! A fuller delivery, around off. Kraigg Brathwaite lunges forward to defend it and probably plays for the turn there but the ball goes straight and beats the outside edge of his blade. The keeper collects the ball and whips the bails off in the flash. However, Kraigg Brathwaite's back leg is inside the crease and no damage done.
Tossed up nicely on middle and leg. Kraigg Brathwaite defends it out nicely this time.
A tossed up delivery, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite gets forward again and blocks it.
A flatter delivery, around off. John Campbell defends it towards the off side.

Goes for a big shot this time and it goes in the air but falls in the vacant region. This is tossed up around off. John Campbell lifts this towards the deep extra-cover region and miscues it but the falls in the vacant rehion and couple of runs are taken.
FOUR! This time a much better shot! This is full and outside off. Campbell leans forward and drives it through covers for a boundary.
A flatter delivery on middle. John Campbell works it towards mid-wicket.
Slightly slower in the air and John Campbell skips down the track but ends up just pushing it to covers.
Quicker this time on off. John Campbell blocks it out.
On middle and turning into Kraigg Brathwaite. He turns it towards short leg.
Tossed up delivery on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite gets well forward and blocks it.
Slightly shorter on off. Kraigg Brathwaite goes back and pushes it towards the off side.
This time Root drifts on the pads. Kraigg Brathwaite tucks it towards fine leg and gets a couple.
Fuller and quicker on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite flicks it to deep square leg for a single.

NOT OUT! England lose their review! A flatter delivery on middle from 'round the wicket. John Campbell looks to paddle sweep but the ball just kisses his glove and goes towards the fine leg region. The batters run couple but there is a huge appeal in the meanwhile by the English skipper. The umpire though is not interested and the Root takes a review. The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows that there is a glove involved. So no damage done in the end.
Tossed up, on a length. Brathwaite defends it off the splice of the bat.
This is dragged down, around middle and leg. Brathwaite with a firmly hit pull shot but straight to backward square leg.
A flatter delivery on middle. Kraigg Brathwaite works it towards the leg side.
Tossed up on off. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it out.
Another delivery on the off stump line and Kraigg Brathwaite gets well forward and blocks it.
Slightly shorter on off. Kraigg Brathwaite punches it to covers for a single.
Drifting on the pads. Kraigg Brathwaite looks to tuck it towards the leg side. The ball brushes his pads and a leg bye is taken towards the fine leg region.
Slightly shorter angling into middle. John Campbell pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Kraigg Brathwaite nudges it to fine leg for another single.
An effort ball this time by Stokes! Bangs this short on off.  John Campbell initially tries to pull it but then decides to let it go.
A length delivery on middle. John Campbell works it towards the leg side.
On a good length and around off this time. John Campbell lets it go comfortably.
A flatter delivery on middle and leg. Kraigg Brathwaite works it towards the backward square leg region.
Tossed up nicely on off;. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks this off the front foot.
Slower and loopy again, on off. Kraigg Brathwaite gets well forward and blocks it out.
On off and fuller. Kraigg Brathwaite blocks it.
Slightly shorter on off. Kraigg Brathwaite goes back and defends it comfortably.

NOT OUT! England lose out on another close chance! An arm ball this time on middle and leg. Kraigg Brathwaite goes back and looks to work it towards the leg side but misses. The ball hits his pads and there is an appeal. However, the umpire says no. England decide to take review. The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows no bat involved. The Ball Tracker rolls and it shows umpire's call on wickets hitting. So the original decision stays and England are left disappointed yet again.

OUT! LBW! Third time lucky for England and they have the breakthrough. A length ball, angled into the pads and this one skids through. Kraigg Brathwaite gets caught on the crease and gets pushed onto the back foot. He misses the flick and and gets pinged on the pads. Ben Stokes runs away in appeal and the dreaded finger is raised. Surprisingly Brathwaite doesn't review it. The replay shows that it would have been umpire's call anyways. Now, can England press the issue?
Howout: lbw b Ben Stokes

Commentary: Length again, skids off the surface and stays a bit low. Brooks does well to get a bat on it.
Pitched up, in that channel around off and the ball just holds its line. Brooks gets beaten past the outside edge.
Angled into the pads, tucked away leg side.
Fullish delivery, around off and this is played towards cover-point.
Full and wide, squeezed away to backward point. A wicket-maiden for Ben Stokes.
Flatter delivery, around off. Blocked off the back foot.
Around off again. Campbell watchfully keeps it out.
Tossed up, on off. Campbell strides out to defend.

OUT! TAKEN! That is a lazy shot from John Campbell and he has handed over the advantage to the visitors! Floated up, around the off pole. Just when the skipper has got out, Campbell tries to be aggressive and swipes across the line. He tries to clear mid on but the tallest man on the field is stationed over there. Craig Overton reaches over and takes a good catch. Finally some rub of the green going Jack Leach's way. ​​​​​England in command here.
Howout: c Craig Overton b Jack Leach

Commentary: Nicely bowled! Quicker, darted into middle and turning away. Bonner blocks it out.
On middle, this is kept down on the leg side.
A short ball, on middle and leg. Brooks ducks under it and the umpire calls it one for the over. Stokes cannot believe it as the ball hardly rose.
Goes fuller this time, looking to skid one through the defense. Brooks stays solid in defense though.
On off, blocked out with authority by Brooks.
This is pitched up, outside off and shaping away a bit. Shamarh Brooks shoulders arms.
Length this time, angled onto the pads. Brooks defends it back towards the bowler.

Sliding down the leg side, Brooks looks to flick but misses. Foakes dives down to his left and pouches it nicely. The visitors appeal but it's a stifled one. The replay confirms that the deflection was off the pads.
Flatter, around off and tapped towards silly point.
Down the leg side, looking to get Bonner bowled 'round his legs.
On middle. Blocked out.
quicker, darted into middle and leg. Bonner strides out to defend.
And again! Pushed through on middle. Bonner stays solid in defense.
A touch shorter, on off. Bonner pushes it out on the off side. Maiden over for Jack Leach.
On a length, around off. Left alone by Brooks.
Pitched up, outside off. Shamarh Brooks with an easy leave this time.
On the pads, tucked away through square leg for a single. The runs have dried up completely and with two new batters at the crease, the visitors will fancy their chances now.
Every now and then, Stokes is bringing out the short ball. This is well-directed, over middle. Bonner ducks under it.
Around the top of off. Bonner defends it off the front foot.
Back of a length, angled into off. Nkrumah Bonner hops back to tap it back onto the deck.

NOT OUT! That is a waste of an appeal from England! Quicker delivery, on middle and sliding on with the angle. Shamarh Brooks looks to nudge it out on the leg side but gets rapped on the pads. Leach appeals but the keeper doesn't seem interested. Joe Root does review it and Ball Tracker confirms it was missing the leg stump by a fair bit.
On middle. Blocked out.
Nicely tossed up, full and around off. Brooks leans in to defend.
Fuller delivery on middle. Brooks works it towards mid-wicket.
Slower in the air on middle. Brooks gets well forward and blocks it out.
Slightly shorter and flatter on off. Brooks goes back and blocks it.
Pitched up, around off and there's just a hint of reverse swing there. Nkrumah Bonner makes a watchful leave.
Length this time, angling into middle. Bonner nudges it onto the leg side.
Full and skidding into middle and leg, tucked away straight to short mid-wicket.
A half-volley on the pads, worked towards mid-wicket.
NO BALL! On off, this is pushed towards mid off. Ben Stokes has overstepped here and a no ball is called.
Banged in, over off. Nkrumah Bonner ducks under the short ball.
Full and close to the off pole. Nkrumah Bonner makes another good leave.
On a length, drifted onto middle and turning away. Brooks blocks it out.
On off, this is played with the spin towards extra cover.
Quicker and flatter this time, sliding on with the arm. Brooks does well to get a bat on it.
Pushed through quicker, on off. Brooks presses forward to defend.
FOUR! Nicely put away! Drifted down the leg side, looking to turn it from outside leg stump. Shamarh Brooks gets down on one knee and sweeps it behind square on the leg side for a boundary.

OUT! TAKEN! You could hear Zak Crawley saying 'that's a nice shot' on the previous delivery and now he takes a really sharp catch to make this match even more interesting. Beautifully bowled by Jack Leach yet again. Flighted, on off with a bit of drift in. The ball pitches, grips and turns away enough. Shamarh Brooks presses forward to defend but gets the outside edge and Crawley gets low quickly to grab the ball before it hits the ground at first slip. England get another wicket and that too on the cusp of the Tea interval.
Howout: c Zak Crawley b Jack Leach

Commentary: Pitched up, on off and this is firmly driven towards mid off by Nkrumah Bonner.
A length ball, on middle. Bonner keeps it out on the leg side.
Around the hips, kept down towards leg gully.
Good-length, over middle. Bonner stands tall and defends it out.
Around the top of off, blocked back onto the deck by Bonner. He is yet to get off the mark.
Full and straight, punched back firmly towards the bowler who gets a boot on it. Craig Overton starts the final session of the Test match with a maiden.
Around the pads, this is nicely dabbed down through square leg for a couple of runs. Jermaine Blackwood is off the mark straightaway.
Pushed through on off, keeping really low. Blackwood does really well to get his blade down in time. The visitors appeal but the umpire remains unmoved.

OUT! LBW! That is a terrible shot from Jermaine Blackwood and he pays the ultimate price! On a length, sliding into leg stump. On a length, sliding into leg stump. Blackwood goes for the big swipe across the line and fails to connect. He gets pinged on the back leg and the visitors go up in unison. The finger is raised in a flasg and Blackwood reviews it. UltraEDge shows there's no bat involved and Ball Tracker shows up three reds. Jack Leach is turning the game on its head.
Howout: lbw b Jack Leach

Commentary: On middle. Blocked off.
Sliding down leg, padded away by Holder.
Pushed through on middle. Blocked out.
Full and at the toes, clipped away to mid-wicket.
Short ball, over leg stump. Bonner ducks under it.
A good length ball, around off. Bonner pushes it out on the off side.
Length, on off. Blocked out by Bonner.
Good-length, close to the off stump. Bonner nudges it down with soft hands on the off side.
A touch fuller, on off. Bonner just keeps on blocking away deliveries. He has now faced 30 balls and is yet to get off the mark.
Quicker delivery, at 93 clicks and on middle. Blocked out.
Around off, Holder strides out to defend.
This is darted into middle and leg. Holder pushes it back to the bowler.
On off, kept out by Holder.
Floated up, on off. Holder reaches out and pushes it towards mid off for an easy single.
Slowed up a bit and drifted into middle. Bonner watchfully blocks it out.

Uppish but safe! A juicy full toss, on middle and leg. Jason Holder strokes it past Jonny Bairstow at catching mid-wicket and picks up a couple of runs. That was a near-impossible chance, being so close in.
On middle, this is flicked away through square leg for a single by Holder.
The keeper is up to the stumps now. This is angled into the pads. Bonner keeps it out on the leg side.
A touch fuller, on off. Bonner strides out looking to push it through covers but gets it off the inside half towards silly mid on.
Finally, Nkrumah Bonner is underway. Around middle and leg, flicked off the inside edge towards backward square leg for one.
Around off, played towards covers by Holder.
Around off, defended out.
Quicker and fuller, darted into middle. Bonner does well to keep that one out.
Flatter, on off and at 90 clicks. Bonner taps it onto the deck.
On middle, Bonner nudges it out.
Down the leg side, there's no one behind square on the leg side and Nkrumah Bonner goes for the hard sweep. He fails to connect and gets hit on the pads.
Around middle and leg. Kept out by Bonner. Maiden over from Leach.
Stokes hits the length hard and bowls it on off. Holder bunts it out on the off side and after a bit of hesitation does go through for the single.
On off, punched towards the cover region.
Good-length, over middle. Bonner hops on the back foot to block.
Full and pushed wide of the off stump. Left alone by Nkrumah Bonner.
Back of a length, around off. Bonner keeps it out on the off side off the back foot.
Ooh, that must have stung! A good short ball, around shoulder height and at the body. Nkrumah Bonner looks to take on the hook shot but decides against it and chooses to get a body blow instead.
Tossed up on middle. Holder gets well forward and blocks it.
This time around off. Holder puts a big stride forward and defends it towards the off side.
Tossed up again, on off. Holder defends it out.

This time a big appeal but the umpire says no. This is pushed quicker on middle and leg. Holder gets forward to defend but misses. The ball hits his pads and there is an appeal. However the umpire is not interested and Root decides to not take a review. The replays confirm that it was missing leg.
Slower in the air, on off. Holder blocks this off the front foot.
Another lovely delivery on off. Holder is solid in defence.
Beaten this time! A good-length delivery, around off. Bonner pushes for it but the ball straightens after pitching and beats the outside edge of his blade.
Back of a length, on off. Bonner blocks this off the back fooot.
FOUR! Good shot this time and this will ease some nerves! A shorter delivery on middle. Bonner pulls it towards the deep square leg region for a boundary.
A length delivery, on off. Bonner blocks this off the front foot.

Ohh...extra bounce this time! Back of a length, around off. Bonner is back to defend it but the ball bounces a tad more that he expected. It catches the top of his blade and loops in the air towards gully. It falls in the vacant region and no damage done.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Bonner leaves it alone this time.
Back of a length, on off. Holder goes back and blocks it out.
On a length, on off. Holder defends it solidly yet again.

A good-length delivery, outside off. Holder presses forward to defend but gets beaten off the outside edge. Foakes is up to the stumps and collects it to whip the bails off quickly. No damage done though.
A length delivery, on off. Holder solidly defends this now.
Another length delivery, on off. Holder is right behind it to block it yet again.
This time a bit wider outside off. Holder opens the face of his blade and guides it towards the backward point region for a single.
Back of a length, on off. Holder defends it towards the off side for a single.
On a length, on middle. Bonner blocks it solidly towards the leg side.
A length delivery, on middle at 136 kph. Bonner defends it with the straight bat yet again.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Bonner leaves it alone comfortably.
A good-length delivery, close to off this time. Bonner defends it towards the off side.
On a length, on off. Bonner is solid on his front foot defence this time. Clocking is ticking away for England. 27 overs remaining now.
A length delivery on middle. Holder works it towards the leg side.
Beaten! A good-length delivery, around off. Holder presses forward to defend but the ball beats the outside edge of his blade.
A length delivery, on off. Holder this time blocks it off the front foot.
A length delivery, on middle. Holder works it towards the mid-wicket region.

FOUR! A length delivery and around off. Holder steers it towards the third man region. Zak Crawley makes a valiant effort as he runs behind it and dives to stop it. However, his body touches the ropes as he tries to keep the ball in the playing area and the umpire signals this as a boundary.
A length delivery, on off. Holder blocks this off the front foot solidly.
Back of a length, on off. Bonner rides the bounce and blocks this out.
Back of a length, on middle. Bonner works it right of  short leg and the fielder there dives to stop it.
Goes short this time on middle. Bonner ducks under it.
FOUR! This time again short but at a friendly hieght this time. Bonner rocks back and pulls this firmly towards deep backward square leg for a boundary.
On a length, on off. Bonner blocks this off the front foot.
Bangs this one short on middle. Bonner ducks under it comfortably. 25 overs to go. Six wickets still needed for England to win this one.
Slightly shorter around off. Holder pushes it towards the poit region for a single.
On off and quicker. Bonner blocks this towards silly point.
Tad slower this time on off. Bonner defends this off the front foot.
Slightly shorter and turning away from off. Bonner punches it to covers.
On off and turning away again. Bonner pushes it to the cover fielder yet again.
A bit flatter and quicker on off this time. Bonner stays deep in his crease and blocks it.
Tossed up nicely on off. Holder presses forward to defend it.
Fuller on middle. Holder pushes it to mid on.
Nicely bowled yet again, loopy delivery on off. Holder defends this off the front foot.
This time a bit shorter on middle and leg. Holder works it past mid-wicket for a single.
On off and a bit of turn and drift there. Bonner goes back and blocks it out.
Well bowled again! On off with a bit of drift and turn. Bonner is deep in his crease and defends it towards the off side.
Flatter on middle. Holder works it towards mid-wicket.
This time fuller on middle. Holder pushes it to mid on.
Loopy delivery on off. Holder is well forward to block this.
Slightly slower in the air, on off. Holder defends this off the front foot nicely again.
A leading edge this time. Holder tries to work this full delivery on leg towards the on side. The ball catches the leading edge of his blade and goes right of the bowler.

An appeal for LBW! However, the umpire turns it down, This is flatter and on middle and leh. Holder goes back and ends up leaving it. The ball hits his pads and there is a big appeal. The umpire says no and English players discuss for a long time and in the end they decide to not take a review. The replays though show that Holder was gone for all money if they have taken a review.
This is around off and floated nicely in the air. Bonner leaves it alone but it is too close to the off pole for the comfort.
On middle and leg and turning into Bonner. He works it towards the leg side.
This time it is wider outside off. Bonner puts his front foot forward and lets it go.
Full toss this time on off. Bonner pushes it towards the mid on region and the fielder there has failed to collect it. It allows a couple for the batting side.
On off and middle. Turning into Bonner.  He works it towards the leg side.
This is tossed up, outside off. Bonner leaves it alone again.
This is floated full and on middle. Holder drives it along the ground towards mid on.
Flatter and sliding onto the pads. Jason Holder rocks back and knocks it 'round the corner for a couple of runs.
FOUR! Pleasantly timed! Around leg stump, Holder drives it past a diving Joe Root at mid-wicket for a boundary.
Slowed up, on middle. Holder presents the full face of the bat and defends it out.
At the stumps again and Holder clips it towards deep mid-wicket for two more.
Around the pads, this is eased off the back foot towards mid-wicket. Just 20 overs left in the day and England still need 6 wickets.
This is flighted, well outside off. Bonner isn't going to play at that one.
On middle, defended under the eye line by Bonner.
FOUR! Lawrence overpitches and serves a full toss, on off. Nkrumah Bonner just strokes it past silly point and the ball races away into the fence. The 100 is now up for the Windies.
Tad shorter, outside off. Bonner works it off the back foot towards cover-point.
Lawrence now goes over the wicket and tries to turn it back in from around off. Bonner gets right behind the line of the ball to block.
This is a bit quicker, drifted down the leg side and left alone.

NOT OUT! Jason Holder survives and England lose yet another review. This is bowled a bit quicker, around off, drifting in with the wind. The ball pitches, grips the surface and turns away sharply. Holder strides out to defend but gets beaten past the outside edge with that peach of a delivery. The visitors seem interested and the review is taken. UltraEdge shows that there's a flat line as the ball passed the bat.
On middle, Holder presses forward to defend.
Flatter this time, around middle. Holder rocks back to defend.
Around middle, kept down towards short leg.
Bit quicker and around off. Holder defends it towards the off side.
Slightly flighted, around off and turning away. Holder leaves it alone.
This is on a nagging length and angled across the off stump. Bonner doesn't play at it.
