FOUR BYES! Off the rough! Tossed up, around leg. The ball hits a rough patch and turns sharply down the leg side, beating the batter and the keeper as well. The ball runs away into the fine leg fence.
On middle. Blocked out.
On off. Bonner stays solid in defense.
Half an appeal this time. Quicker, around middle and leg and going on with the angle. Bonner gets caught on the crease and gets hit on the pads.
Around off, this is pushed out onto the off side.
Drifted into off, the ball juts holds its line. Holder presents a dead bat at it.
On off, tapped on the bounce to silly point.
Fuller this time, around off. Holder keeps it down towards silly point.
Around off again, turning away a bit. This is blocked off.
Flighted, around off and played with the spin towards the left of the bowler.
Quicker one, on off. Jason Holder does well to keep it down in front of silly point. Another maiden over from Jack Leach.
Overton starts off his new spell with a bumper over leg stump. Bonner has enough time to duck under it.
FOUR! Short and wide, punished by Nkrumah Bonner. This is shorter and outside off. Bonner hangs back and slaps it into the point fence.

Ooh, that could have been curtains for Nkrumah Bonner! Short again, at the body. This one just holds in the pitch a bit. Bonner looks to keep it down on the leg side but the ball comes off the handle of the bat and falls safely past Jonny Bairstow at silly point.
Short again, around leg. Bonner pulls it past square leg and picks up a single.
Another bouncer, over the stumps. Holder ducks under it.
Good-length, around off. Holder hangs back and steers it towards third man. The fielder from inside the ring gives chase and keeps it down to two.
On a length, around middle and turning away. Bonner can just keep blocking those deliveries all day long.
Quicker and fired into middle and leg. Bonner does well to keep it out.
Flatter this time, on off. Bonner bunts it out on the off side.
On off. Bonner blocks it out.
This is pushed through on middle. Nkrumah Bonner strides out to defend.
Quicker and a bit shorter, around off. Nkrumah Bonner hangs back and chops it through the slip cordon and picks up a single.
This is banged in short, going down the leg side. Bonner ducks under it with ease.
FOUR! Overton tries to hit the length hard but angles it onto the pads. Bonner tucks it away fine and picks up a boundary down to fine leg.
Length, sliding down the leg side. No need to play at that one.
Nkrumah Bonner's concentration in this Test match has been amazing. Good-length, on off and this is dabbed down to silly point.

NOT OUT! Just as we praised Bonner's concentration, he almost got out. Length again, around off and nipping back in sharply off the surface. Bonner goes deep in his crease to defend but the ball raps him on the pads. There is a huge appeal and the umpire eventually raises his finger. Bonner reviews it straightaway and the replay confirms that there was a huge inside edge onto the pad.
A touch fuller, on off and there's a hint of reverse swing again. Nkrumah Bonner stays solid in defense.
Floated, around off and this is drilled through silly point for a couple of runs.
Flatter, on off. Holder defends it out.
And again! Attacking the stumps but Holder watchfully blocks it out yet again.
Quicker and flatter, around off. This is blocked onto the off side.
Tossed up, on off. Blocked out.
Drifted into middle and leg and the ball just holds its line. Holder looks to turn it leg side but inside-edges it in front of the fielder at short leg.
A length ball, outside off and Bonner doesn't play at it.
Fuller this time, around off and straightens after pitching. Nkrumah Bonner makes yet another well-judged leave.
This is angled into middle and leg. Bonner keeps it out on the leg side.
On a driving length, around off. This is firmly pushed towards short cover.
This one came back in a long way. Length, on off and nipping back in. Nkrumah Bonner fends it away well.
And again! Around middle and Bonner manages to block it out on the leg side.
Full and on the pads. Jason Holder clips it nicely through mid-wicket and the batters even come back for the third. Good running.
A length delivery, on middle. Bonner works it towards mid-wicket.
A good-length delivery, on off. Bonner blocks this solidly.
Goes fuller on middle this time. Bonner blocks this nicely yet again.
Back of a length, on middle. Bonner goes back and defends it out.
A length delivery, around off. Bonner defends this out towards the off side.
A length delivery on middle. Holder works it right of mid on.
Back of a length, around leg. Holder looks to clip it away but misses.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Holder leaves it alone watchfully.
On a length, on middle. Holder works it towards square leg for a single.
A length delivery, on middle. Bonner is solid on his defence.
Another length delivery on middle. Bonner defends it towards the leg side. All eyes on skipper, Root now as nothing seems to be happening now for England but will Root give it up anytime soon?
Tossed up on off. Holder defends this off the front foot.
Slightly shorter and quicker on off. Holder goes back and blocks it out.
Loopy delivery on off. Holder puts a big stride forward and defends it.
On middle this time. Holder pushes it towards the mid on region. The ball rolls towards the long fence but the fielder cuts it off. The batters run three.
Slightly shorter and around off. Bonner cuts it towards backward point for a single.
A flatter delivery on off. Holder blocks it out solidly. 8 overs to go.
This is fuller and down the leg side. Bonner looks to clip it away but misses.
Back of a length, on off, Bonner blocks this solidly off his crease.
A length delivery, on off. A solid block again by Bonner.
A length delivery on middle. Bonner defends it towards the leg side. Stokes is struggling here. There is no point making him bowl here, risking an already risk-prone star player.
NO BALL AND FOUR! Short and wide outside off. Bonner cuts hard and gets this through backward point for a boundary. Stokes has overstepped here.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Bonner leaves it alone.
On a length, outside off. Bonner lets it go.
Flatter and quicker on off. Holder blocks it off.
Slower in the air, on off. Holder defends this off the front foot.
Loopy delivery on middle. Holder defends this off the front foot.
On middle and tossed up again. Holder puts his big stride forward and defends it.
Quicker and flatter on off. Holder defends this solidly off the front foot.

NOT OUT! Quicker and flatter around leg. Holder looks to clip it away but misses. The ball hits his pads and it deflects towards the first slip fielder. Zak Crawley dives to his right and takes a good catch. English players appeal but the umpire takes his team and refers this towards the third umpire. The soft signal is not out. The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows no bat involved. So Holder will continue. Also, Joe Root and a couple of other English players are having a bit of an animated discussion with umpire Joel Wilson as they are not happy with the decision.
Stokes continues to steam in and bangs this one short on middle from 'round the wicket. Bonner ducks under it.
Back of a length, around leg. Bonner lets it go this time.
Back of a length, on off. Bonner rides the bounce and defends it towards the off side.
Back of a length, on off. Bonner goes back and blocks it solidly.
One needs to applaud Stokes here! He is still running and putting in effort. Bowls another short ball on middle. Bonner ducks under it. Though it seems his energy is getting wasted here.
FOUR! Good shot and both the batters are looking quite comfortable here now. Back of a length, outside off. Bonner cuts it through backward point for a boundary.
Tossed up on off this time. Holder is solid in his front foot defence.
Slower in the air, around off. Holder defends this off the front foot yet again.
Slightly shorter around off. Holder goes back and pushes it towards the off side.
On off and fuller. Holder blocks this off the front foot.
A fuller delivery on middle. Holder is well forward in his front foot defence.
Tossed up on middle. Holder with a solid front foot defence yet again.
Slightly shorter around off. Bonner chops it to point.
Loppy delivery on middle. Bonner looks to defend but gets the inside edge towards the leg side.
On middle and turning into Bonner with some good bounce. Bonner goes back and leaves it. The ball hits his body.
This is fuller around off. Bonner is solid on his front foot defence.
Quicker and flatter around off. Bonner leaves it alone.
Slightly shorter around off. Bonner cuts it towards backward point.
A flatter delivery, around off. Holder punches it to covers.
Tossed up nicely on middle. Holder gets well forward and blocks it out.
Goes fuller again on off. Holder with a solid front foot defence yet again.
FOUR! This time he gets a boundary! A fuller delivery on middle. Holder drives  it towards the long off region for a boundary.
A flatter delivery on middle. Holder works it towards mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Another boundary! This one is pitched on off and turning away. Bonner gets the outside half of his blade as he pushes for it. The ball goes through the third man region for a boundary.
Tossed up on off. Holder plays it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off. Holder with a solid front foot defence.
Tossed up on middle. Holder works it towards mid-wicket.
Off and fuller. Holder gets well forward and blocks it out.
Quicker and flatter on middle. Holder works it towards the leg side.
A flatter and quicker delivery, outside off. Holder lets it go.
Tossed up nicely on middle by Leach. Bonner gets well forward to defend it. The ball goes off the inside half of his blade towards the leg side.
